{"id": "70937", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=70937", "title": "Llewellyn Set", "text": "The Llewellyn Set is a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;light armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Llewellyn Set offers a well-rounded blend of protection, resistances, and moderate &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; for a relatively low &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;. It does, however, come at the cost of being harder to upgrade than other standard light armor sets due to it requiring &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt; for reinforcement.\nHistorical notes.\nPrior to &lt;a href=\"Patch%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Calibration 1.15&lt;/a&gt;, the pieces of the Llewellyn Set did not offer any &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "55588", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55588", "title": "Llewellyn Shield", "text": "The Llewellyn Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;small shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nCommon drop from the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Soldier\"&gt;Stone Soldier&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Drangleic%20Castle\"&gt;Drangleic Castle&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Llewellyn Shield, much like the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Shield\"&gt;Watcher's Shield&lt;/a&gt;, sees widespread use in the game for what it provides: great defenses, high &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;, and moderate &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;, all for a very low &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;. Its only setback is that it lacks a 100% damage reduction against &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Damage\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; attacks, but its well-balanced &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; defenses more than compensate for this."}
{"id": "134844", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134844", "title": "Llewellyn Shield (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Llewellyn Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Small Shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Horace%20the%20Hushed\"&gt;Horace the Hushed&lt;/a&gt;. It can be obtained by killing him at any point in the game, including in &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nA very popular Small Shield, the Llewellyn Shield boasts respectable stability and high overall physical and elemental absorption across the board, being somewhat less able to deflect &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; than anything else. The cost of this is that it ties with the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Iron%20Shield\"&gt;Eastern Iron Shield&lt;/a&gt; as the second-heaviest Small Shield in the game, and that it requires more investment in &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to wield than any other Small Shield, tying with the &lt;a href=\"Dragonhead%20Shield\"&gt;Dragonhead Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nDue to its excellent defenses and possessing the fast &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parrying&lt;/a&gt; frames that all Small Shields share, it is an ideal shield for players who wish to block attacks as well as parry them.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with standard ."}
