{"id": "104410", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=104410", "title": "Locations (Dark Souls)", "text": "The land of &lt;a href=\"Lordran\"&gt;Lordran&lt;/a&gt; is the setting for \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". It was once home to the &lt;a href=\"Gwyn%2C%20Lord%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Lord Gwyn&lt;/a&gt; and the ancient lords, but in recent times it has fallen from grace and lies in ruins.\nFor the purposes of the game, the land is split into twenty four separate locations. \"Dark Souls\" is an open world game, and as such many locations can be visited in no particular order. Because there generally isn't a fixed sequence, the order of most locations listed below \"roughly\" follows the narrative of the main questline for the sake of convenience. \nArtorias of the Abyss.\nThe \"&lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Artorias of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;\" DLC takes place in the land of &lt;a href=\"Oolacile\"&gt;Oolacile&lt;/a&gt;, far back in the past. It includes the following locations:\n3D Map.\nThis integration requires JavaScript. If you are seeing this message on Desktop view, try refreshing the page or clearing your browser's cache. If you are using the mobile view, switch to desktop mode or click [&lt;a href=\"https%3A//sketchfab.com/3d-models/dark-souls-map-b75a883eb9c94104beb170c98dc5216c\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;]."}
