{"id": "150536", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150536", "title": "Lockout", "text": "Lockout is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nWhen held, the doors are shut tight and the wielder's movement is slowed to walking speed. While in this stance, all incoming attacks from the front are automatically blocked with added &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; (likely 10 points added to stability).\nThe weak attack charges forward like a battering ram, staggering and pushing back any enemies caught in its path and then inflicting 1.6 times the weapon's Attack Rating at the end of the charge.\nThe strong attack fortifies the wielder's position by anchoring the doors into the ground, creating a shockwave that staggers all nearby foes (though dealing no damage). The wielder becomes completely immobile while in this mode, however stability is further increased and all blocked damage is completely negated, even &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. Stamina is completely locked and will not regenerate under any circumstances while the fortification is active. The weak attack of the skill can be performed to exit fortification as an alternative to releasing the stance."}
