{"id": "138446", "revid": "1188343", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=138446", "title": "Londor Pale Shade", "text": "The Londor Pale Shade is a &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dark spirit&lt;/a&gt; and summonable &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;phantom&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nPale Shades, colloquially known as \"Harlots of Death\", are assassins of the &lt;a href=\"Sable%20Church\"&gt;Sable Church&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Londor\"&gt;Londor&lt;/a&gt;. They are undying &lt;a href=\"hollow\"&gt;hollow&lt;/a&gt;s who perform atrocities in the name of their sect, covering their darkly shriveled appearance with a &lt;a href=\"Sneering%20Mask\"&gt;golden sneering mask&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Manikin%20Claws%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Manikin Claws&lt;/a&gt; are their weapon of choice.\nThey long for the day when a &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;chosen champion&lt;/a&gt; is foretold to come and bring the glory back to their land.\nConsequences of player's actions.\nDepending on the player's standing with Londor, the Londor Pale Shade will be either an ally or an enemy. Should the player be in good graces with Yuria of Londor, the Pale Shade can be summoned as a white phantom and will assist in the fight against the area's &lt;a href=\"Boss%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;. However, if the player angers Londor in any way, he will invade the player instead.\nThe player may fall in ill favor of Londor through the following situations:\nOf these situations, it is only possible to regain Londor's favor if Yuria is angered but not dead, and the player absolves sin at the &lt;a href=\"Velka%2C%20the%20Goddess%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Statue of Velka&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\n&lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Kiln%20of%20the%20First%20Flame\"&gt;Kiln of the First Flame&lt;/a&gt;\nStrategy.\nEarly in the fight, the Londor Pale Shade will cast &lt;a href=\"Affinity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Affinity&lt;/a&gt; and surround himself with five &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dark&lt;/a&gt; orbs that will launch and home toward the player if approached.\nHe comes armed with the &lt;a href=\"Manikin%20Claws%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Manikin Claws&lt;/a&gt; and will attempt to start his attacks by performing a slow, strong attack, and then follow with normal ones. He does not have much &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;, however, and will stagger easily with each attack of most weapons, allowing for many subsequent hits until &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; runs out.\nAt long range, his offensive capabilities are even more limited, resorting only to throw &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Throwing%20Knife%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poison knives&lt;/a&gt; in quick succession.\nEquipment.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nFarron Keep=\nFarron Keep Perimeter=\nIrithyll of the Boreal Valley=\nPontiff Sulyvhan=\nKiln of the First Flame=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "48678", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48678", "title": "Lone Hunter Schmidt", "text": "Lone Hunter Schmidt is a &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Phantom&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nLone Hunter Schmidt is a white phantom available for summoning before\u00a0&lt;a href=\"The%20Rotten\"&gt;The Rotten&lt;/a&gt; boss battle in the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Gulch\"&gt;Black Gulch&lt;/a&gt;. His summoning sign can be found along the wall near the boss door.\nIn combat, Schmidt will use his &lt;a href=\"Bows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt; to attack from a distance. He does not deal much damage and does not have a lot of defense. Schmidt will not avoid any fire in the area, which will quickly kill him.\nScholar of the First Sin.\nIn \"\", Lone Hunter Schmidt's summoning sign can be found next to &lt;a href=\"Bashful%20Ray\"&gt;Bashful Ray's&lt;/a&gt; summoning sign, near the &lt;a href=\"Razorback%20Nightcrawler\"&gt;Razorback Nightcrawler&lt;/a&gt;s.\nIn \"Scholar of the First Sin\", Lone Hunter Schmidt can be summoned as a &lt;a href=\"shade\"&gt;shade&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Amana\"&gt;Shrine of Amana&lt;/a&gt;. His shade sign can be found inside the hut after the &lt;a href=\"Ogre\"&gt;Ogre&lt;/a&gt;, past the second bonfire. He is capable of using his bow to do respectable damage to the &lt;a href=\"Lindelt%20Cleric\"&gt;Archdrakes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Amana%20Shrine%20Maiden\"&gt;Shrine Maidens&lt;/a&gt; from a distance."}
{"id": "45781", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45781", "title": "Lonesome Gavlan", "text": "Lonesome Gavlan\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Merchants%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;merchant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". He is voiced by , who also voiced &lt;a href=\"Greirat%20of%20the%20Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Greirat&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nHis location in No-man's Wharf is moved slightly. After ringing the bell and dropping down from a series of platforms, enter the leftmost building and proceed to the third floor. He will be standing beside the pulling ring that opens the gate connecting the two main wharf areas.\nPlot.\nGavlan is the only merchant to whom the player can sell items, similar to &lt;a href=\"Kingseeker%20Frampt\"&gt;Kingseeker Frampt&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;. On interacting with him after purchasing 16,000 souls worth of merchandise, he will give the player the &lt;a href=\"Gyrm%20Greataxe\"&gt;Gyrm Greataxe&lt;/a&gt;."}
