{"id": "130382", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130382", "title": "Longbow (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Longbow is a &lt;a href=\"Bows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe \"Dark Souls III\" iteration of the Longbow does not diverge significantly from its previous cousins. It is a very standard bow tailored towards builds that level &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; over &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, with respectable range that allows it to be used to hit targets far away. With only the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Bow%20of%20Pharis%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Bow of Pharis&lt;/a&gt; outranging it of all regular bows, this makes the Longbow ideal for aggro-ing individual targets from far away.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "130753", "revid": "4511886", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130753", "title": "Longfinger Kirk", "text": "Longfinger Kirk, also known as the Knight of Thorns, is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nA knight clad in the &lt;a href=\"Set%20of%20Thorns%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Set of Thorns&lt;/a&gt; and one of &lt;a href=\"Rosaria%27s%20Fingers\"&gt;Rosaria's Fingers&lt;/a&gt;. He invades as a &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dark spirit&lt;/a&gt;, and comes armed with a &lt;a href=\"Barbed%20Straight%20Sword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Barbed Straight Sword&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Spiked%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Spiked Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nBehaves very offensively and will frequently use his sword's\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Stance%20%28Straight%20Sword%29\"&gt;Stance&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in order to break through the player's defenses. His sword also has the ability to inflict &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nCan deal contact damage thanks to the thorns that cover his armor. While the damage itself is minimal, it will also drain some &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;, which may end up staggering the player and leave them open for following attacks.\nLocation.\nIf the player is embered, he invades as a &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dark spirit&lt;/a&gt; in the cloister of the main hall of the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;, shortly after exiting the rooms with a &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20Knight\"&gt;Cathedral Knight&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Deep%20Accursed\"&gt;Deep Accursed&lt;/a&gt;.\nKirk will not invade if the player has already killed the &lt;a href=\"Deacons%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Deacons of the Deep.&lt;/a&gt;\nStrategy.\nInvades once the player reaches the central cloistered area on the first floor of the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;cathedral&lt;/a&gt;, spawning on the opposite corridor. A &lt;a href=\"Thrall\"&gt;Thrall&lt;/a&gt; will be patrolling on the left side, so it is advised to take it out first lest it meddles during the fight.\nThe player may start attacking Kirk at a distance as soon as he finishes spawning, although after being hit once or twice he will start evading most attacks.\nWhile coming equipped with a &lt;a href=\"Spiked%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, Kirk will rely more on an offensive approach. Since he keeps his defenses down for most of the fight, the player may take the first step and receive him with a two-handed attack. He will frequently use &lt;a href=\"Stance%20%28Straight%20Sword%29\"&gt;Stance&lt;/a&gt; in an attempt to break through the player's defenses. Lure him into attacking and make him miss, then counterattack.\nWhen attacked, he will often roll in the player's direction in an attempt to inflict contact damage thanks to the thorns that cover his armor. The damage is minimal, although it does drain some &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;; evade to the side. If he manages to inflict damage, don't lose composure and gain some distance, as attacking him at this moment usually means taking more damage from his armor due to being in close proximity to the player.\nThrowable weapons like &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Knife%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;knives&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"kukri\"&gt;kukri&lt;/a&gt;s are useful against him during the fight.\nIt is possible to cheese Kirk by running back up to the ledge where the first &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Slave\"&gt;Giant Slave&lt;/a&gt; can be fought. Kirk can not path to this spot and will stand underneath the ledge instead, where the player can launch spells at him with impunity. Spells that move the player forward will not work as they will knock the player off the ledge, and it is recommended to bring &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Estus%20Flask\"&gt;Ashen Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt;s to maximize the amount of casts available."}
{"id": "3321", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3321", "title": "Longsword", "text": "The Longsword is a &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nAs the archetypical straight sword, the Longsword features slightly lower base damage, the same \"Quality\" scaling values as most other Straight Swords, a versatile moveset, and low stat requirements. Although it will perform admirably in any situation, its jack-of-all-trades nature means it will likely be outperformed by other &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Straight Swords&lt;/a&gt; that have higher base damage. \nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "33393", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33393", "title": "Longsword (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Longsword is a &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nAn important distinction needs to be drawn between PvE and PvP when discussing how effective different weapons are in dark souls 2, and the longsword is one of the more stark examples of such. \nIn PvE, straight swords are on average one of the weaker weapon classes due to low base damage, low &lt;a href=\"Counter%20Attack\"&gt;counter damage&lt;/a&gt;, and the more heavily resisted slashing damage type, and the longsword is a mediocre example even within its class. It deals lower damage than the &lt;a href=\"Broadsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;broadsword&lt;/a&gt;, which is available just as early, leaving its thrust attacks as its only redeeming feature. Those thrusts, however, have a hidden penalty to counter damage, leaving it with no strong use cases compared to its contemporaries. \nEven worse is the common \u201cnew player trap\u201d fire longsword, which can be picked up rather early in the game. Fire is the most resisted element in the game by a wide margin, reducing it\u2019s value as an infusion. At that early point you don\u2019t yet have access to a spell buff, meaning your method of increasing damage would be a resin, which cannot be applied to an elementally infused weapon. Additionally, infused weapons are even less efficient for damage from scaling than uninfused melee weapons. As a result, using even a simple uninfused longsword early on would be more effective, without mentioning more effective weapons in general. \nIn PvP straightswords are generally one of the more effective weapon classes, and the longsword sits near the top of the bunch. Its versatile moveset and low stat requirements make it easy to fit into many builds, while giving the player plenty of options on how to attack or respond. The reduced counter modifier on thrust attacks is significantly less important as a factor, and scaling damage gains slightly more importance in PvP as a whole. It\u2019s not the best all around, but its moveset is second to none, standing as one of the most effective and efficient weapon options.\nTrivia.\nA reskinned Longsword was available as a promotional weapon for the &lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20the%20Ivory%20King\"&gt;Crown of the Ivory King&lt;/a&gt; DLC for two weeks after the patch on September 30th, 2014. It was offered again as a promotion for for a week after the &lt;a href=\"Scholar%20of%20the%20First%20Sin\"&gt;Scholar of the First Sin&lt;/a&gt; patch released on February 5th, 2015. The Longsword, along with the other reskinned weapons that were released for the other DLCs, were all obtained from the unique chest in the basement of the mansion in &lt;a href=\"Majula\"&gt;Majula&lt;/a&gt;."}
