{"id": "131110", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131110", "title": "Lothric Knight Greatshield", "text": "The Lothric Knight Greatshield is a &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Lothric Knight Greatshield is the first available greatshield in the game, a massive tower shield with 100% &lt;a href=\"physical%20damage\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt; absorption. It is relatively light for a greatshield, and has respectable &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;, absorbing up to 71% of stamina damage when fully upgraded. However, its high &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement prevents it from being easily used in the early game, though this can be circumvented by two-handing the shield with at least 24 Strength.\nThe Lothric Knight Greatshield has the highest &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; absorption of all shields in the game, tied with &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Greatshield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Havel's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, but has moderate elemental defenses otherwise and in particular falls short in terms of &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; absorption. This can make it useful against caster enemies, such as the &lt;a href=\"Sage%27s%20Devout\"&gt;Sage's Devout&lt;/a&gt;s located in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt; and especially against the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Sage\"&gt;Crystal Sage&lt;/a&gt;. One may also get use of it when going through the &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Archives\"&gt;Grand Archives&lt;/a&gt;, another location where Magic damage is abundant.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "133868", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133868", "title": "Lothric Knight Greatsword", "text": "The Lothric Knight Greatsword is an &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Lothric Knight Greatsword is a powerful and well-rounded ultra greatsword that is very strong on a myriad of builds.\nUtilizing the horizontal ultra greatsword moveset, it &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scales&lt;/a&gt; primarily with &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, making it most effective when &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infused&lt;/a&gt; with a &lt;a href=\"Sharp%20Gem\"&gt;Sharp Gem&lt;/a&gt;, however it can still perform strongly with any other infusion, moreso since it requires a hefty investment in &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to wield. As well, it has innate &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage, allowing it to deal damage through &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt;, and because it can still be buffed this Lightning damage can be further augmented by applying a &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Pine%20Resin%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Gold Pine Resin&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Pine%20Bundle\"&gt;Gold Pine Bundle&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis innate Lightning damage also makes the Lothric Knight Greatsword very useful for &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;-oriented builds as well. When infused with a &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Gem\"&gt;Lightning Gem&lt;/a&gt;, the weapon gains extreme amounts of Lightning damage that scales well with the player's Faith, making it a very fearsome weapon indeed. And when infused with a &lt;a href=\"Blessed%20Gem\"&gt;Blessed Gem&lt;/a&gt;, both the physical damage and the Lightning damage will scale with the player's Faith, while simultaneously providing background health replenishment. And finally, on a build with high investment in physical stats as well as Faith, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Blade\"&gt;Lightning Blade&lt;/a&gt; can be cast on the weapon if it has been given a physical infusion, allowing it to utterly devastate any foes unlucky enough to be hit by it.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with standard ."}
