{"id": "98846", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=98846", "title": "Loyce Shield", "text": "The Loyce Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in .\nCharacteristics.\nUnexceptional as a shield in almost all regards, and even though the health regeneration is a welcome addition, at 2 HP every 3 seconds, it's not worth the &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; and lack of performance. Still, it can be useful for extensive exploration sessions, while the player is occupied scouting the area and combat is not expected. It's better if equipped as a secondary shield for switching it quickly if necessary, if one can put up with the extra weight."}
{"id": "98885", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=98885", "title": "Loyce Soul", "text": "A Loyce Soul is a in .\nAvailability.\nObtained by slaying &lt;a href=\"Charred%20Loyce%20Knight\"&gt;Charred Loyce Knight&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"The%20Old%20Chaos\"&gt;The Old Chaos&lt;/a&gt;. They can also be collected in co-op as a phantom. Due to their low drop rates, wearing &lt;a href=\"Item%20Discovery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Item Discovery&lt;/a&gt; gear is highly recommended.\nUse.\nLoyce Souls do not yield any souls upon consumption, instead they can be given to &lt;a href=\"Alsanna%2C%20Silent%20Oracle\"&gt;Alsanna&lt;/a&gt;, who will reward the player depending upon the amount of souls they have collected. The souls cannot be traded.\nFarming.\nAt first, players will more than likely notice that they will receive almost always the equipment (&lt;a href=\"Charred%20Loyce%20Set\"&gt;armor set&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Charred%20Loyce%20Shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Charred%20Loyce%20Greatsword\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt;) of these Charred Knights of Loyce, this is because the equipment itself has a higher chance to drop, which often overrides the chance of the Loyce Souls to drop. \nHowever, the loot pool for all equipments are limited per playthrough, which means that after obtaining a certain item from a specific enemy, a certain amount of times, those items will stop dropping from its respective source, therefore, the faster a player can acquire those items, the faster it is to find the Loyce Souls. \nIn shorter terms, the Loyce Souls start dropping much more regularly after the Charred Knights dropping a specific number of items. \nThe best way to farm the knights is during the fight against the &lt;a href=\"Burnt%20Ivory%20King\"&gt;Burnt Ivory King&lt;/a&gt;, as players will be backed up by any rescued &lt;a href=\"Knight%20of%20Eleum%20Loyce\"&gt;Loyce Knights&lt;/a&gt; (as well as summons such as &lt;a href=\"Lucatiel%20of%20Mirrah\"&gt;Lucatiel of Mirrah&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Twiggy%20Shei\"&gt;Twiggy Shei&lt;/a&gt;), and also due to the fact that the Charred Loyce Knights themselves will spawn more frequently (roughly 10-11 per cycle depending on how long the portals remain open). Once enough Charred Loyce Knights have been slain and the Burnt Ivory King's portal appears, the player may egress from the arena via using the &lt;a href=\"Aged%20Feather\"&gt;Aged Feather&lt;/a&gt;, and repeating the process as many times as necessary; if phantoms were summoned, be sure to use a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Separation%20Crystal%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Black Separation Crystal&lt;/a&gt; first. As these Charred Loyce Knights are treated as boss minions and not as spawned enemies, they will always appear during the boss fight no matter how many times they are killed.\nAfter defeating the Burnt Ivory King, the area of &lt;a href=\"The%20Old%20Chaos\"&gt;The Old Chaos&lt;/a&gt; becomes opened indefinitely and players may farm the Charred Loyce Knights that spawn from the portals. Keep in mind, however, that unlike the knights fought during the boss battle, these knights can be de-spawned after killing them enough times. This may force players to join the &lt;a href=\"Company%20of%20Champions\"&gt;Company of Champions&lt;/a&gt;, making the knights significantly tougher."}
