{"id": "38585", "revid": "1087082", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38585", "title": "Lucatiel of Mirrah", "text": "Lucatiel of Mirrah is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". She appears in four different locations, with her dialogue affected not by the location but by how many times she has encountered the player before; if her dialogue has been exhausted in all four locations, she will relocate to &lt;a href=\"Aldia%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Aldia's Keep&lt;/a&gt; for a fifth and final encounter. She can be summoned as a &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;phantom&lt;/a&gt; for as many as five different boss fight. \nAn undead human from &lt;a href=\"Mirrah\"&gt;Mirrah&lt;/a&gt;, she came to &lt;a href=\"Drangleic\"&gt;Drangleic&lt;/a&gt; in search of her brother &lt;a href=\"Aslatiel%20of%20Mirrah\"&gt;Aslatiel&lt;/a&gt;, who himself had travelled to Drangleic after turning undead, and is terrified at the prospect of losing her memories and turning &lt;a href=\"hollow\"&gt;hollow&lt;/a&gt;. She is also a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\" through the name and description of &lt;a href=\"Lucatiel%27s%20Mask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;her mask&lt;/a&gt;, which appears as equipment.\nLocations.\nLucatiel can be found for the first time in any of the following locations and she will deliver different dialogue depending on the number of times she has previously been met:\nAfter meeting her in all of the aforementioned locations, she will appear for the last time at the first bonfire in &lt;a href=\"Aldia%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Aldia's Keep&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nLucatiel has a rather androgynous appearance, with long, blonde hair wrapped in a ponytail, but her most distinctive feature is the metal bearded mask she uses to cover her face. Lucatiel will temporarily remove the mask after the player has gone through her entire dialogue when meeting her for the second time. This will reveal that although she is in human form, half her face has &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;ed, showing that she's cursed.\nLucatiel is somewhat of a loner and usually prefers to stay away from people. However, she shows great respect and admiration to those who are brave enough to speak to her and she is always willing to offer her assistance to those in need.\nAlthough Lucatiel mostly remains calm and collected, she becomes incredibly distressed with the idea of going hollow and losing all of her memories. At one point, she even claims that she would be willing to kill the player if that means that she will be able to get rid of the curse. However, in the end, Lucatiel comes to terms with herself and accepts that she will eventually go hollow.\nLucatiel wields the &lt;a href=\"Mirrah%20Greatsword\"&gt;Mirrah Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Mirrah%20Shield\"&gt;Mirrah Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nLucatiel was born into a family of peasants in &lt;a href=\"Mirrah\"&gt;Mirrah&lt;/a&gt;, an unprivileged part of the society of this kingdom. In order to ensure the well-being of her family, Lucatiel and her brother joined the army. At an early age, she and her brother took up fencing together and, eventually, Lucatiel's skills on the battlefield allowed her to become a knightess of the Order.\nAlthough Lucatiel was a skilled combatant, she was no match for her brother. She claims that her brother was a far better swordsman than she was, as she was never able to defeat him. At some point in her life, her brother disappeared without a trace. Lucatiel thought that her brother might have fallen victim to the &lt;a href=\"undead%20curse\"&gt;undead curse&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter she contracted the curse of undeath, Lucatiel went to &lt;a href=\"Drangleic\"&gt;Drangleic&lt;/a&gt; as it was rumored that the cure could be found in this land. With time, she became certain that her brother must have come here too. Lucatiel later confides that she feels the curse is taking over her, and that her memories begin to fade away, starting with the oldest.\nPlot.\nWhen Lucatiel is found for the first time, she will introduce herself and explain her motives for being in Drangleic. She will also offer her assistance to the player during their journey.\nDuring her second encounter, Lucatiel will tell the player about her past in Mirrah. She will then take off her mask, revealing her half hollowed appearance, and give the player a &lt;a href=\"Human%20Effigy\"&gt;Human Effigy&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe third time she is met, she tells the player about her fears of losing her memories and of her brother. Lucatiel will explain how he is a better swordsman than her and she confesses that her brother, who is another victim of the curse of undeath, might be in Drangleic. She then gifts the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Steel%20Protection%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Ring of Steel Protection +1&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe fourth time that the player finds Lucatiel, she is very confused and distressed over the curse, and says she would do anything to get rid of it, even if it meant killing the player. After exhausting her dialogue, she will be available as &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;phantom&lt;/a&gt; for another boss fight and will move to the next area.\nLastly, Lucatiel can be found in a shack at the first bonfire of &lt;a href=\"Aldia%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Aldia's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. She will be distressed if the player has not summoned and kept her alive for three boss fights, and begs the player to remember her name, as she may not. Lucatiel will disappear from the game after this encounter. If the player has summoned Lucatiel and kept her alive for three of the four summonable boss fights in the base game, she will thank the player for keeping her sane, and bequeath her &lt;a href=\"Lucatiel%27s%20Set\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and &lt;a href=\"Mirrah%20Greatsword\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt; to the player. This is necessary for unlocking her &lt;a href=\"Lucatiel%20of%20Mirrah%23Achievements/Trophies\"&gt;achievement/trophy&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter meeting her in Aldia's Keep, she will disappear from the game, and her final fate remains unknown, leaving it up to the player's own interpretation.\nAn &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;invader&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Aslatiel%20of%20Mirrah\"&gt;Aslatiel of Mirrah&lt;/a&gt; later appears just before entering Aldia's Keep itself. He wears the same armor and weapon set as Lucatiel, which suggests that her brother indeed went hollow exploring &lt;a href=\"Drangleic\"&gt;Drangleic&lt;/a&gt;.\nOverview.\nAs of Patch 1.04, Lucatiel received an immense buff to her defense, making her capable of withstanding most of hits thrown at her.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Gulch\"&gt;Black Gulch&lt;/a&gt; she has now complete immunity to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nHer AI remained the same though, which means she could still get stuck in the environment on her way to the boss or fall to her death accidentally.\nLocations.\nLucatiel can be summoned at the following locations:\nHer summon sign is found beyond the gate in the shortcut leading to the boss fight. \nHer summon sign is found past the shortcut on the dock. &lt;a href=\"Bradley%20of%20the%20Old%20Guard\"&gt;Bradley of the Old Guard&lt;/a&gt; can be summoned for this fight as well. \nHer summon sign is located at the bottom of the elevator of &lt;a href=\"Sinners%27%20Rise\"&gt;Sinners' Rise&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Sellsword%20Luet\"&gt;Sellsword Luet&lt;/a&gt; can be summoned for this fight as well. \nHer summon sign is found in front of the fog gate of this boss.\nHer summon sign is located by the &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Hidden Chamber&lt;/a&gt; bonfire. &lt;a href=\"Bashful%20Ray\"&gt;Bashful Ray&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lone%20Hunter%20Schmidt\"&gt;Lone Hunter Schmidt&lt;/a&gt; can be summoned for this battle as well.\nHer summon sign will appear in the &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Cathedral\"&gt;Grand Cathedral&lt;/a&gt; near the iron chest only after she is talked to at &lt;a href=\"Aldia%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Aldia's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Twiggy%20Shei\"&gt;Twiggy Shei&lt;/a&gt; can be summoned for this battle as well."}
{"id": "3928", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3928", "title": "Lucerne", "text": "The Lucerne is a &lt;a href=\"Halberds\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Lucerne can be obtained from a corpse in an ancillary chamber in &lt;a href=\"The%20Catacombs\"&gt;The Catacombs&lt;/a&gt;, past the second &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt;, and guarded by 2 &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Scimitar-wielding Skeletons&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Lucerne\u00a0shares the same damage profile of the &lt;a href=\"Halberd\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt;, but only deals &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28Damage%20Type%29\"&gt;Thrust Damage&lt;/a&gt; making it capable of gaining &lt;a href=\"https%3A//darksouls.fandom.com/wiki/Damage_%28Dark_Souls%29%23Counter_Damage\"&gt;Counter Damage&lt;/a&gt; bonus and an excellent candidate to use along with &lt;a href=\"Leo%20Ring\"&gt;Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt; for a further boost to Counter Damage. \nLike all Halberds, if the attack doesn't connect with an enemy, the user will stumble and seem to not be able to handle the weight. If the hit connects, the stumble animation does not come into play and the user moves as normal, this means that this weapon gets &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29%23Sweet%20Spot%20Damage%20Bonus\"&gt;Sweet Spot&lt;/a&gt; Damage Bonus.\nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "54703", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54703", "title": "Lucerne (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Lucerne\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Halberds%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Chancellor%20Wellager\"&gt;Chancellor Wellager&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Drangleic%20Castle\"&gt;Drangleic Castle&lt;/a&gt; for 4,800 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThis weapon has very little going for it, mostly because it is trading its damage and reach for its \"Shield Piercing\" ability when a strong attack is dealt. For most weapons this would be fine, however, this is a Halberd, and its strong attack moveset is not only extremely telegraphed and slow, but also has a very small hitbox, when one handed. When two handed it does have an advantage, as it will deal an attack that makes the player spin twice, easy to block and could surely cause players be surprised.\nAs such this is a weapon that should be used only when two handed and primarily against enemies or players who are extremely reliant on &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt;. However, if the player wants weapons capable of dealing damage through shields, then the &lt;a href=\"Reapers\"&gt;Reaper&lt;/a&gt; class of weapons is much more advised as any attack will go through shields. "}
{"id": "130261", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130261", "title": "Lucerne (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Lucerne is a &lt;a href=\"Halberds%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound on a corpse at the &lt;a href=\"High%20Wall%20of%20Lothric\"&gt;High Wall of Lothric&lt;/a&gt;, in the courtyard guarded by patrolling &lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Knight\"&gt;Lothric Knight&lt;/a&gt;s, just before encountering &lt;a href=\"Vordt%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Vordt of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Lucerne is an interesting halberd, in that all of its attacks deal &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt; damage despite possessing no actual thrusting attacks. As its entire moveset is comprised of swings, it fills in a unique niche of being capable of inflicting Thrust damage on groups of enemies. While it lacks the reach of dedicated thrusting weapons like &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Spears&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pikes\"&gt;Pikes&lt;/a&gt;, it can still be quite powerful in the right hands, especially if combined with a &lt;a href=\"Leo%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nOf particular note is that when using its &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;weapon art&lt;/a&gt;, the weapon's protruding beak is able to bypass &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Shields&lt;/a&gt;. This can be useful when dealing with shielded foes.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with ."}
{"id": "130195", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130195", "title": "Luck", "text": "Luck is a &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It determines the player's &lt;a href=\"Item%20Discovery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Item Discovery&lt;/a&gt; and the effectiveness with luck scaling weapons, such as the &lt;a href=\"Man-grub%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Man-grub's Staff&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Anri%27s%20Straight%20Sword\"&gt;Anri's Straight Sword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Gem\"&gt;Hollow-infused&lt;/a&gt; weapons, as well as increasing &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; build-up.\nItem Discovery determines the likelihood of an enemy dropping items. The higher it is, the easier it is to get drops. \nUnlike other offensive stats, luck &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; is not displayed on the weapon's stat screen.\nAs with every other stat in the game, it also increases the player's defenses. As well, leveling Luck will increase the player's &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; resistance."}
