{"id": "132586", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132586", "title": "Lycanthrope", "text": "Lycanthropes are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nVile beasts wrapped in chains with a wooden cross strapped to their backs, Lycanthropes are dormant until disturbed, at which point they fly into a feral rage. While most are encountered in the marshlands of the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;, a single Lycanthrope can be found locked in a cell in the &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nLycanthropes are initially passive and will ignore the player until they either attack them or step directly into their field of view. They are fast and aggressive creatures that primarily attack with a series of rapid slashes, though they will also use a ground pound at very close range. They also have a grab attack that drains the player's &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Points%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt; whilst granting them a small damage buff.\nAlthough aggressive, Lycanthropes are easy to stagger. Despite their size, they have a surprisingly small amount of HP and can be killed quickly if the player uses an aggressive approach. One-handed attacks might prove the solution if the Lycanthrope's speed outstaggers you while two-handing."}
{"id": "138514", "revid": "4511886", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=138514", "title": "Lycanthrope Hunter", "text": "Lycanthrope Hunters are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\n&lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;ed villagers wandering aimlessly on the road that leads to the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;cathedral&lt;/a&gt;. They carry large and sharpened tree branches which they use like spears.\nWhile they don't have a considerable amount of health and can be staggered easily, they can, in return, inflict a surprising amount of damage, either by stabbing at the player, charging at them from long distances, or by impaling their weapons on the ground with great force.\nThey are usually encountered in large groups and it is not rare suddenly finding oneself surrounded by many of these foes, as other hunters in the vicinity will frequently join in to an ongoing battle.\nSome hunters can initially be encountered in a passive state, hidden amongst the woods' dense foliage or even immersed in their own endeavors, and will not attack unless one passes nearby.\nLocation.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;. Lycanthrope Hunters heavily populate the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices%23Bonfires\"&gt;Crucifixion Woods&lt;/a&gt; all along the left shore of the marsh that leads from the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices%23Bonfires\"&gt;Halfway Fortress&lt;/a&gt; toward the keep's ruins.\nStrategy.\nWhile their decayed appearance may initially imply otherwise, Lycanthrope Hunters should not be taken lightly, as they can deal a surprising amount of damage and will most likely attack in groups. They have a very long aggro range and may commence their charges from very far away and keep rushing toward the player for a considerable distance. Additionally, the weight of the large branches they carry allow them to drain large amounts of &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; with each hit, potentially being able to &lt;a href=\"Guard%20Break\"&gt;break the player's guard&lt;/a&gt; easily if their attacks are blocked.\nHunters are susceptible to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; and will panic for a few seconds when they take any fire damage, preventing them from moving or attacking.\nThe first groups of hunters encountered can be found traversing from the marsh toward the keep's ruins. It is advisable to draw-in those who fall behind with ranged attacks to dwindle their numbers.\nThey are susceptible to &lt;a href=\"Alluring%20Skull%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Alluring Skulls&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rapport\"&gt;Rapport&lt;/a&gt;, which can be used if the player suddenly finds themselves in a precarious situation."}
{"id": "5241", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5241", "title": "Mace", "text": "The Mace is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Mace uses the same move-set as the &lt;a href=\"Club\"&gt;Club&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Reinforced%20Club\"&gt;Reinforced Club&lt;/a&gt; without the jumping strong attack. The Mace is heavier and does more base damage than the Club but has lower initial scaling. This weapon will deal comparable damage with Reinforced Club, so picking between the two is up to user preference based on ReClub's innate bleed and the difference in movesets. \nLike all &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Hammers&lt;/a&gt;, if an attack doesn't connect with an enemy, the user will stumble and seem to not be able to handle the weight. If the hit connects, the stumble animation does not come into play and the user moves as normal. This animation means that this Hammer gains &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29%23Sweet%2520Spot%2520Damage%2520Bonus\"&gt;Sweet Spot&lt;/a&gt; Damage bonus.\nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "45609", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45609", "title": "Mace (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Mace is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "130271", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130271", "title": "Mace (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Mace is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Mace is a simple, yet effective, &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; that excels on &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;-oriented builds. Due to its nature as a hammer, it is capable of both &lt;a href=\"Guard%20Break\"&gt;breaking guards&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; with relative ease. However, its range is somewhat limited, and it is marginally &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;heavier&lt;/a&gt; than most other weapons in its class.\nAdditionally, it can make some limited use of poise, making it one of the lightest, and fastest, weapons that can reliably trade with &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt;. This, coupled with its &lt;a href=\"Perseverance%20%28skill%29\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, means the mace is an excellent choice both as a main weapon and as a backup for players with slower, more powerful weapons.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "52461", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52461", "title": "Mace of the Insolent", "text": "The Mace of the Insolent\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nLocated in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Crypt\"&gt;Undead Crypt&lt;/a&gt; in the pit, after encountering two &lt;a href=\"Imperious%20Knight\"&gt;Imperious Knight&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Mace of the Insolent is a powerful &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt;. It deals a total of three damage types, can cast any magic that a &lt;a href=\"Sacred%20Chimes\"&gt;Chime&lt;/a&gt; can\u00a0and has an average weight for a hammer.\nOnce upgraded, the weapon favors its &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt;-based damage over the other two, and for this reason it is advised to give it a Dark &lt;a href=\"infusion\"&gt;infusion&lt;/a&gt; as it will significantly increase its damage output. This can prove especially effective for &lt;a href=\"Hexes\"&gt;hexers&lt;/a&gt;, as it becomes a strong &lt;a href=\"Catalysts%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;catalyst&lt;/a&gt; while still being useful in melee combat.\nThis weapon should be viewed similarly to other weapons that double as catalysts, like the &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Flame\"&gt;Blue Flame&lt;/a&gt;, and their strategies also apply accordingly, for instance, using two Maces of the Insolent means that the player can buff them with either &lt;a href=\"Sunlight%20Blade%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Sunlight Blade&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Resonant%20Weapon\"&gt;Resonant Weapon&lt;/a&gt; and then &lt;a href=\"powerstance\"&gt;powerstance&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0them to get additional attack moves while still being able to cast spells."}
{"id": "150317", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150317", "title": "Mad King's Folly", "text": "Mad King's Folly is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThe wielder strikes the head of the pygmy king to the ground, awakening it with a scream. This attack consumes no &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt;, possesses 35 &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; health and inflicts 1.1 times the weapon's Attack Rating as damage. This attack cannot be &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parried&lt;/a&gt;.\nFollowing up with the the strong attack will plant the base of the crucifix into the ground and perform one of the pygmy king's three enchantments. This attack will also inflict 0.5 times the weapon's physical Attack Rating as damage as the enchantment takes effect."}
