{"id": "4628", "revid": "26269363", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4628", "title": "Magic Shield", "text": "Magic Shield (\u9b54\u6cd5\u306e\u76fe) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\n&lt;a href=\"Shield\"&gt;Shield&lt;/a&gt; buff that increases the &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; of the shield held in the left hand by 20% and cuts blocked &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; damage by 70%, stacking multiplicatively with the shield's unenchanted block ability. Magic Shield will dispel if the player unequips their shield in any way, including two handing. It is weaker than &lt;a href=\"Strong%20Magic%20Shield\"&gt;Strong Magic Shield&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally, it should be noted that Magic Shield may not be cast on a shield equipped in the right hand.\nOverview.\nAlthough extra &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; can be helpful, Magic Shield lasts only for a scant 15 seconds, making it difficult to use in prolonged fights or serial engagements.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "133913", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133913", "title": "Magic Shield (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Magic Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEffect.\nReinforces the player's left-hand &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;. Increases damage absorption while increasing &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; by 20%.\nPercentage of damage that chips through a raised shield is reduced by 30%, so weaker shields get larger absorption bonuses. For example, if a shield would normally block 50% of &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage, buffing it with Magic Shield would allow it to block 65%; if a shield blocks 80% of Fire damage, buffing it will cause it to block 86% of Fire damage. Therefore, chip damage can never be fully negated except in cases where absorption was already at 100% (e.g., &lt;a href=\"physical%20damage\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt;).\nEffect lasts for 60 seconds. Duration can be increased via equipping a &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;. Switching the &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; equipped in the off-hand away from the shield will remove the effect.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "134193", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134193", "title": "Magic Shield (Shield)", "text": ""}
{"id": "57115", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57115", "title": "Magic Shield (shield)", "text": "The Magic Shield\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;small shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDrops from the &lt;a href=\"Leydia%20Apostle\"&gt;Leydia Apostle&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Crypt\"&gt;Undead Crypt&lt;/a&gt;.\nOne could simply clear the large hall before the fight with &lt;a href=\"Velstadt\"&gt;Velstadt&lt;/a&gt;, and continuously ring the bell beneath the staircase to continuously farm for the shield, as it would not require the use of a Bonfire to respawn them. Simply ring the bell once more, whenever the Apostles are dead, to spawn additional ones.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Magic Shield, as the name of the shield may imply, boasts excellent &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; defenses, and the highest base &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; defense of any shield in the game, while weighing only 2.0 units and having an appreciable physical damage reduction. It can also deflect spells with a &lt;a href=\"Parry%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt;, though the window is marginally-longer due to the animation.\nWhile it may seem like an excellent shield for countering mages and the like, it also possesses a dangerously-low &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;, being much lower than most other small shields, save for the &lt;a href=\"Foot%20Soldier%20Shield\"&gt;Foot Soldier Shield&lt;/a&gt;. One should be cautious not to block one too many attacks with the shield, as their guard will certainly break easily if it is overworked.\n&lt;a href=\"Infusing\"&gt;Infusing&lt;/a&gt; this shield with a &lt;a href=\"faintstone\"&gt;faintstone&lt;/a&gt; will grant it a 100% damage reduction from magical attacks, though some damage \"will still bleed\" through due to the nature of &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;certain&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Soul%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "67252", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=67252", "title": "Magic Stone", "text": "Magic Stones are\u00a0 in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUse.\nUsed at &lt;a href=\"Steady%20Hand%20McDuff\"&gt;Steady Hand McDuff&lt;/a&gt; to grant weapons the Enchanted infusion.\nEffect.\nCauses weapon damage to &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;scale&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. This differs from &lt;a href=\"Faintstone\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; infused weapons in that Enchanted weapons deal purely &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Damage\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt;."}
