{"id": "5140", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5140", "title": "Mail Breaker", "text": "The Mail Breaker is a &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound on a corpse in the early part of lower &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Burg\"&gt;Undead Burg&lt;/a&gt;, in one of the rooms that the &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Thief\"&gt;Hollow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; ambush the player from.\nCharacteristics.\nBeing something of a hybrid between &lt;a href=\"daggers\"&gt;daggers&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords\"&gt;thrusting swords&lt;/a&gt;, the Mail Breaker has the disadvantage of having short reach and the weakest damage of the thrusting swords, but also the advantage of the highest critical rates of the thrusting swords. Though do not be fooled by critical modifiers as most other weapons will out perform Mail Breaker on crits even with on weapons with lower crit mods due to them possessing higher innate damage for the lower modifier to work off of. \nAlthough the in-game stat menus show Mail Breaker having a 120 critical rate, this weapon also benefits from a higher &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;motion value&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstabs&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte\"&gt;Ripostes&lt;/a&gt; making it deal higher damage that usual on these critical attacks like all of the other Thrusting Swords. \nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:\nTrivia.\nThe Mail Breaker has appeared in every game of the Souls series."}
{"id": "105652", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=105652", "title": "Mail Breaker (Dark Souls)", "text": ""}
{"id": "52407", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52407", "title": "Mail Breaker (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Mail Breaker is a &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nStrong attacks with this weapon completely bypass shield defenses.\nDue to its low base damage and mediocre scaling, it is wise to infuse with either bleed, poison, or mundane.\nThis is a niche weapon, as it works great against tanks and greatshield users, especially when infused with bleed or poison.\nAfter the developers patched the critical multipliers for daggers in general, they became much less used as their backstabs and ripostes dealt much less damage. However, the Mail Breaker always had a moderate critical modifier like the unpatched daggers, which means that is now superior to any other dagger, potentially being able to deal more damage than even the top tier daggers. This, added to the fact that its moveset is that of a rapier, with the exception that its one handed strong attack is exactly the same has its one handed weak attack, makes it so that the Mail Breaker, though a Rapier, is in essence quite possibly the best dagger in the game."}
{"id": "130265", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130265", "title": "Mail Breaker (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Mail Breaker is a &lt;a href=\"Daggers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
