{"id": "132099", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132099", "title": "Man-grub", "text": "Man-grubs are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nMan-grubs appear as disfigured humans whose lower bodies have been replaced with a maggot-like tail. Most Man-grubs will try to tackle and scratch the player in an attempt to kill them, but some also wield &lt;a href=\"Man-grub%27s%20Staff\"&gt;staves&lt;/a&gt; that they use to cast unique &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey can also vomit maggots at the player. If this attack connects, the player will be covered by countless maggots that cause gradual &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up for a long duration. The maggots can be removed by equipping and swapping to a &lt;a href=\"Torch%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;torch&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "132120", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132120", "title": "Man-grub's Staff", "text": "The Man-grub's Staff is a &lt;a href=\"Staves%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;staff&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nReward for reaching Rank 2 in the &lt;a href=\"Rosaria%27s%20Fingers\"&gt;Rosaria's Fingers&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Man-grub's Staff is a very unique staff, in that its &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; attribute is not &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;, but &lt;a href=\"Luck\"&gt;Luck&lt;/a&gt;. As such, it requires a similarly unique build in order to utilize, as players must skill Intelligence in order to meet the casting requirements of various &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sorceries&lt;/a&gt;, as well as Luck in order to boost the effectiveness of the catalyst itself.\nThe most effective way to use this staff is not to level Intelligence and Luck equally, but rather to level Intelligence and &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; as supplements to a primarily Luck-based build. This gives the player access to powerful utility spells that complement Luck-based weapons, particularly in invasions, without the need to invest massive amounts of Intelligence to boost the hitting power of their spells.\nAt 40 Luck, the Man-grub's Staff has a higher effective &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; than any other staff at 45 Intelligence, and only loses out to pure Intelligence-focused staves at 50 Intelligence and higher.\nAt the base wielding requirement of 18 Intelligence, players will have access to utility spells such as &lt;a href=\"Chameleon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Chameleon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Snap%20Freeze\"&gt;Snap Freeze&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Great%20Heavy%20Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Great Heavy Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spook\"&gt;Spook&lt;/a&gt;. However, increasing Intelligence to 23 (which can also be achieved by simply equipping a &lt;a href=\"Scholar%20Ring\"&gt;Scholar Ring&lt;/a&gt;) will give the player access to relatively powerful spells such as &lt;a href=\"Great%20Farron%20Dart\"&gt;Great Farron Dart&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Flashsword\"&gt;Farron Flashsword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Homing%20Soulmass%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Homing Soulmass&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Soul Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with &lt;a href=\"Upgrade%20Materials%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
