{"id": "138408", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=138408", "title": "Man Serpent", "text": "Man Serpents, or Serpent-Men, are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nDescendants of the ancient &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt;s, Man Serpents are a rapacious race of creatures with a human-like body and the head of a snake. They live high on the mountains, in &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;, where they are mostly isolated from the rest of the world and have erected large temples to worship their ancestors.\nThey wear badly worn and dirty clothes, with their long snake-like heads wrapped in rags, and come armed either with paired &lt;a href=\"Bandit%27s%20Knife%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;knives&lt;/a&gt;, or with a &lt;a href=\"Man%20Serpent%20Hatchet\"&gt;shotel&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Small%20Leather%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Dragon%20Greatshield\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt;. Certain variants also have the ability to spew fireballs.\nTheir offensive capabilities are not restricted just to the weapons they wield, and they can even lash out or bite with their long reptilian heads, draining large amounts of &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nMan Serpents usually attack in groups, given their bandit-like nature, and are experts in preparing ambushes, sometimes found hiding behind pillars or corners, or even clinging from the ceilings.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Bandit%27s%20Knife%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;knives&lt;/a&gt;-wielding variant is the quickest and most aggressive. Special care must be taken when they raise their secondary knife as a shield. Attacking them while in this stance will result in them &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parrying&lt;/a&gt; and then \"&lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;riposting&lt;/a&gt;\" by biting the head of their adversaries, lifting them from the ground and then lashing them back down for high damage.\nThe fireball spewing variants are also dangerous, as they have an extremely long aggro range and their projectiles have homing capabilities, serving mainly as distractions when the player is fending off other enemies, not to mention they do a considerable amount of &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. It is advisable to kill them with ranged attacks from very far away, before they become hostile, or, if the player is skilled enough, rush forward and slay them while evading the rest of the enemies."}
{"id": "132900", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132900", "title": "Man Serpent Hatchet", "text": "The Man Serpent Hatchet is an &lt;a href=\"Axes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Man%20Serpent\"&gt;Man Serpent&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Man Serpent Hatchet is a very good, if late axe. It has a quite long reach and its curved blade, as stated in the description, partially bypasses blocking, dealing 40% damage past it. \nUpgrades.\nReinforced with &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "132477", "revid": "1188343", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132477", "title": "Man Serpent Summoner", "text": "Man Serpent Summoners are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nOnly two summoners appear in the game. Their main method of attack consists in infinitely summoning enemies to deal with their foes, though they are also capable of using a whip at close range, as well as casting sorceries similar to &lt;a href=\"Deep%20Soul\"&gt;Deep Soul&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Affinity\"&gt;Affinity&lt;/a&gt; with their &lt;a href=\"Mendicant%27s%20Staff\"&gt;staves&lt;/a&gt;. They are usually positioned away from the player's immediate reach, allowing them to summon at least one enemy to contend with. They are very weak at close range, falling from a few hits of a melee weapon. While capable of moving, they are very slow and seem to avoid it.\nThe first one is encountered on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak%23Bonfires\"&gt;Dragon-Kin Mausoleum&lt;/a&gt; and summons &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Drakeblood Knights&lt;/a&gt; to fight for him. The first encounter with this foe will drop the &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Greatsword\"&gt;Drakeblood Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally, there is a rare chance it will summon &lt;a href=\"Havel%20the%20Rock%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Havel the Rock&lt;/a&gt; at this location. Defeating him here will yield the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Tooth%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dragon Tooth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Greatshield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Havel's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;. If Havel has been killed in his location adjacent to the Great Belfry, the summoner can no longer call him for aid, making the Drakeblood Knight the only summon available.\nThe second summoner can be found before reaching the &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak%23Bonfires\"&gt;Great Belfry&lt;/a&gt; bonfire. This one calls in the &lt;a href=\"Rapier%20Champion\"&gt;Rapier Champion&lt;/a&gt;, a very powerful enemy similar to the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Master\"&gt;Sword Master&lt;/a&gt;, although he wields a rapier instead, and is garbed in &lt;a href=\"Wolnir%27s%20Crown\"&gt;Wolnir's Crown&lt;/a&gt;, though he does not drop it. Defeating this enemy the first time yields &lt;a href=\"Ricard%27s%20Rapier%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Ricard's Rapier&lt;/a&gt;. This summoner can also call in Havel, though the same conditions apply to the first summoner should Havel be slain.\nLocation.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;. Only two are encountered in the game, the first one on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak%23Bonfires\"&gt;Dragon-Kin Mausoleum&lt;/a&gt; and the second one before reaching the Great Belfry.\nStrategy.\nThe summoners rely mostly on summoning enemies as their main form of attack, though they are capable of casting sorceries from a distance while you engage the enemies. Up close they are slow to attack with the whip, though they cast sorceries at a faster rate. However, they cannot summon when in melee combat, or casting ranged sorceries. Both summoners have only a modicum of health and are also vulnerable to headshots."}
{"id": "53014", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53014", "title": "Manchettes of Judgment", "text": "The\u00a0Manchettes of Judgment\u00a0are a\u00a0 piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".They are part of the &lt;a href=\"Judgment%20Set\"&gt;Judgment Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nThe Manchettes of Judgment, along with the rest of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Judgment%20Set\"&gt;Judgment Set&lt;/a&gt;, is found in a chest in the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0behind an &lt;a href=\"Illusory%20Wall%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;illusory wall&lt;/a&gt;, one floor above the &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, underneath the flight of stairs. There is a &lt;a href=\"Pharros%27%20Contraption\"&gt;Pharros' Contraption&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0nearby that will highlight the illusory wall."}
{"id": "2968", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2968", "title": "Maneater Mildred", "text": "Maneater Mildred (\u4eba\u98df\u3044\u30df\u30eb\u30c9\u30ec\u30c3\u30c8) is an &lt;a href=\"enemy\"&gt;enemy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"phantom\"&gt;phantom&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". She is a cannibalistic\u00a0woman wearing a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Sack\"&gt;Sack&lt;/a&gt; and wielding a &lt;a href=\"Butcher%20Knife\"&gt;Butcher Knife&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlot.\nManeater Mildred has no dialogue whatsoever, and her appearances are brief. As such, little is known about her. She was probably included in the game to give offline players a taste of invasions and &lt;a href=\"co-op%20play\"&gt;co-op play&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nManeater Mildred moves quickly,\u00a0but her\u00a0attacks are\u00a0slow, and don't do that much damage. She also\u00a0can't block attacks very well and can be stunlocked by any weapon. Mildred can be easily\u00a0&lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;bed or &lt;a href=\"parried\"&gt;parried&lt;/a&gt;. On the other hand, fighting her can be dangerous as she spawns inside a poisonous swamp with movement impediments. It is recommended to lure her into the bonfire\u00a0area before engaging her if caught unprepared."}
