{"id": "44409", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44409", "title": "Manslayer", "text": "The Manslayer is a &lt;a href=\"Katanas%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;katana&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nLocated near the fourth bonfire of &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Amana\"&gt;Shrine of Amana&lt;/a&gt; (Rise of the Dead). Start from the bonfire, and go through the door at the top of the nearby staircase (must be hollow for the door to open). After getting to the other tower, simply go down the stairs and out the door. From here the Manslayer is found inside a chest behind the columns in the water, to the left.\nCharacteristics.\nThis katana is interesting, due to the fact that it is exactly the same as the &lt;a href=\"Uchigatana%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Uchigatana&lt;/a&gt; when both are fully upgraded, with the added bonus of dealing &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; damage. Aside from that, its damage, its scaling and moveset are identical in every way.\nThe only real downsides to the Manslayer are that it must be upgraded through &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt;, its extra unit of weight when compared to the Uchigatana, and that it is the inferior choice if the player wants to go for an elemental infusion. It has also a very minute increase to its stats requirement, thus being the second easiest katana to wield, the first being the Uchigatana. It can also be noted that the Uchigatana is slightly longer than the Manslayer.\nTrivia.\nThe Manslayer's description is possibly a reference to the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four_Hitokiri_of_the_Bakumatsu\"&gt;Four Hitokiri of the Bakumatsu&lt;/a&gt;, four samurai who were considered unbeatable by normal men. Additionally, 'hitokiri' literally translates to 'manslayer.'"}
