{"id": "19287", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19287", "title": "Manus", "text": ""}
{"id": "8848", "revid": "356969", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8848", "title": "Manus, Father of the Abyss", "text": " is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" and a &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Artorias of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nManus is the final boss of the\u00a0\"Artorias of the Abyss\" DLC. He is encountered in the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Chasm%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Chasm of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is possible to summon the past version of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Great%20Gray%20Wolf%20Sif\"&gt;Great Gray Wolf Sif&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0to aid in the battle. Sif's summon sign is found in the arena where the player fights Manus, inside the fog door.\nAppearance.\nManus appears to be a massive beast-like humanoid with a long spiked tail and multiple chaotic horns sprouting from his head and neck, covered with red-glowing eyes. His right arm holds a staff he uses to attacks and cast dark sorceries and his left arm is bigger and covered in fur with his hand being covered with teeth underneath his palm, capable of extending when attacking.\nPlot.\nOnce the &lt;a href=\"Chosen%20Undead\"&gt;Chosen Undead&lt;/a&gt; has the &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Pendant\"&gt;Broken Pendant&lt;/a&gt; in their possession, Manus pulls them through a magical rift from &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Basin\"&gt;Darkroot Basin&lt;/a&gt; into the past land of &lt;a href=\"Oolacile\"&gt;Oolacile&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe has kidnapped &lt;a href=\"Dusk%20of%20Oolacile\"&gt;Princess Dusk&lt;/a&gt; and is eventually confronted in the &lt;a href=\"Chasm%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Chasm of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nManus was a primordial human who possessed an extraordinary soul consisting of a &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Manus\"&gt;viscous, lukewarm lump of gentle humanity&lt;/a&gt;, an immense &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Soul\"&gt;Dark Soul&lt;/a&gt;. He was also a sorcerer who used a &lt;a href=\"Manus%20Catalyst\"&gt;rough and old wooden catalyst&lt;/a&gt;, very crude but large enough to be used as a weapon. His &lt;a href=\"Pursuers\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt; in particular were dark and in fact manipulated the Dark Soul, even managing to give it a will and throw it at enemies to chase them. Manus also possessed &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Pendant\"&gt;one half of an ancient stone pendant&lt;/a&gt; infused with powerful dark magic that was infinitely precious to him and represented a source of wrenching nostalgia and lost joy of a passed loved one. At some point in the distant past, Manus died and his body was buried in the caves of the region upon which the civilization of &lt;a href=\"Oolacile\"&gt;Oolacile&lt;/a&gt; would later arise.\nAt some point after &lt;a href=\"Gwyn\"&gt;Gwyn&lt;/a&gt; sacrificed himself to link the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Primordial%20Serpent\"&gt;Primordial Serpent&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Kaathe\"&gt;Kaathe&lt;/a&gt; arrived in Oolacile and manipulated the country to upturn the grave of the primordial man buried beneath the &lt;a href=\"Oolacile%20Township%20Dungeon\"&gt;dungeons&lt;/a&gt; of their city and resurrect him. In fact, Kaathe was looking for a potential &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Lord\"&gt;Dark Lord&lt;/a&gt; and after the &lt;a href=\"Four%20Kings\"&gt;Four Kings&lt;/a&gt; and their &lt;a href=\"Darkwraith%20%28enemy%29\"&gt;Darkwraiths&lt;/a&gt;, to whom he had taught the powers of &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Hand\"&gt;Lifedrain&lt;/a&gt;, had been sealed together with &lt;a href=\"New%20Londo%20Ruins\"&gt;New Londo&lt;/a&gt;he decided to find another path to achieve his goal.\nHowever, the royal family of Oolacile took the precious broken pendant of Manus for themselves, giving it to &lt;a href=\"Dusk%20of%20Oolacile\"&gt;Princess Dusk&lt;/a&gt;. The wrenching nostalgia connected to his object of obsession and the sincere hope to reclaim it drove Manus mad and his Dark Soul went wild, transforming him into a dark beast eternally seeking his pendant. His immense mass of humanity out of control led to the manifestation of an &lt;a href=\"Chasm%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Abyss&lt;/a&gt; that spread, threatening to devour the entire land. The Dark emanating from Manus did not limit itself to generating countless &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20Phantom\"&gt;Humanity Phantom&lt;/a&gt;s with a will of their own but also influenced the &lt;a href=\"Bloathead\"&gt;residents of Oolacile&lt;/a&gt;, making their humanity go wild and horribly mutating their bodies, bloating their head and opening them with cracks lined with innumerable tiny red eyeballs and protuding brain parts. On the brink of madness, Oolacile sorcerers would also discover &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Orb\"&gt;abyssal sorceries&lt;/a&gt; that are more weighty and deal physical damage instead of magical as their Dark Soul, used instead of normal souls, were closer to their natural state and produced sorceries with a more tangible presence and closer to matter.\nAs the Abyss continued to spread across the land of Oolacile, &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Artorias\"&gt;Knight Artorias&lt;/a&gt; came to stop it and confront Manus, as the &lt;a href=\"Four%20Knights%20of%20Gwyn\"&gt;Knight of Gwyn&lt;/a&gt; already had experience with fighting the Abyss and its creatures after the events of New Londo and his hunt for the Darkwraiths, and possessed a &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Pendant\"&gt;Silver Pendant&lt;/a&gt; that protected him from the Dark. Artorias, together with his trusted companion &lt;a href=\"Great%20Grey%20Wolf%20Sif\"&gt;Sif&lt;/a&gt;, thus faced Manus but his strength proved insufficient to defeat the Father of the Abyss and he succumbed to the Abyss. Wounded by the battle, Artorias used his &lt;a href=\"Cleansing%20Greatshield\"&gt;Cleansing Greatshield&lt;/a&gt; to form a barrier to protect Sif leaving a magic barrier to repel the Dark. Artorias, now corrupted to the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Artorias\"&gt;Soul&lt;/a&gt; by the Abyss and with his &lt;a href=\"Set%20of%20Artorias\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; corroded, was left to fight alone and wounded the distorted creatures of Oolacile.\nAt one point Manus managed to take possession of his lost pendant, kidnapping Princess Dusk and taking her to his Abyss. However, due to a time distortion, Manus found himself chasing a further copy of his pendant, but this one was located in the future. Using his Dark power, Manus snatched the &lt;a href=\"Chosen%20Undead\"&gt;Chosen Undead&lt;/a&gt; that found it from the future bringing him to the Oolacile of the past. This Undead would be able to put the corrupted Artorias to rest and succeed his mission, facing Manus and defeating him, thus saving Oolacile from further corruption. After the Undead rescued Princess Dusk, however, she found herself in the future together with her pendant, thus creating the paradox that led to her salvation at the hands of that same Undead centuries later. Thanks to &lt;a href=\"Elizabeth\"&gt;Elizabeth&lt;/a&gt;'s confidentiality, the legend spread that Artorias had defeated Manus and his Abyss, omitting the role of the unsung hero to preserve the honor of the knight.\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough he was killed, the Dark Soul of Manus was so large and powerful that he was reborn in death, and his soul split into miniscule fragments that retained some will. These pieces began to coalesce once again absorbing the other humanities, becoming the incarnations of different emotions of Manus and then human in shape, with their own self-awareness: &lt;a href=\"Elana%2C%20the%20Squalid%20Queen\"&gt;Elana&lt;/a&gt; the embodiment of Manus' wrath, &lt;a href=\"Alsanna%2C%20Silent%20Oracle\"&gt;Alsanna&lt;/a&gt;, the embodiment of Manus' fear, &lt;a href=\"Nadalia%2C%20Bride%20of%20Ash\"&gt;Nadalia&lt;/a&gt; the embodiment of Manus' solitude and &lt;a href=\"Nashandra\"&gt;Nashandra&lt;/a&gt;, the tiniest fragment of Manus and the embodiment of his want. These new entities had some recollection of their father and his dark powers and when the Abyss that they called home was dissipated they scattered across the land. To sustain themselves and seek more and more power, they reached &lt;a href=\"Drangleic\"&gt;Drangleic&lt;/a&gt; where in one way or another they came into contact with the holders of magnificent souls, drawn to their awesome strength.\nStrategies.\nIt is possible for the player to kill Manus outside his fog gate:\nIf the player wishes to face Manus conventionally, it is advisable to equip &lt;a href=\"Stamina\"&gt;Stamina&lt;/a&gt;-boosting items that such as the &lt;a href=\"Cloranthy%20Ring\"&gt;Cloranthy Ring&lt;/a&gt;, as well as a high-&lt;a href=\"Stability\"&gt;Stability&lt;/a&gt; shield that blocks &lt;a href=\"Physical%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt;. Only attack Manus after he finishes his &lt;a href=\"%23High%20Jump%20Slam\"&gt;jumping smash&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"%23Berserk%20Combo\"&gt;frenzy combo&lt;/a&gt;, lest you be caught in the middle of his strikes.\nManus will start using his magic attacks at around 50% health. Use the Silver Pendant to deflect them, as they are difficult to dodge.\nNotes.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Pendant\"&gt;Silver Pendant&lt;/a&gt;, although not required, can be of great help as it blocks his magic attacks if used with correct timing.\n&lt;a href=\"Great%20Grey%20Wolf%20Sif\"&gt;Great Grey Wolf Sif&lt;/a&gt; can help in this battle. Whilst Sif's attacks are not very damaging, the extra summon can keep Manus distracted and give the player time to heal. It is wise to only summon Sif after Manus is below half health, to distract him in his harder phase, making it less likely the player will be targeted by the Dark Orb barrage attack.\nSif's summon sign is\u00a0\"inside\" the Manus's arena, directly to the left of where the player spawns. As a result, Sif can only be summoned\u00a0\"during\" the fight. Thankfully, Sif is summoned instantly after touching the sign, without the usual white phantom-summoning animation. Since it is summoned during the fight it does not increase Manus' Hp.\nBoss information.\nAttacks.\nLong Arm Slam.\nManus briefly holds up his shadowy limb then brings it down at the player. This attack can reach more than halfway across the boss arena and breaks the guard of most medium-stability shields, dealing moderate damage to the player. It can be dodged by rolling in any direction during its downswing. This attack is telegraphed by rapid movement along his shadowy limb.\nBack Swipe.\nIf the player is behind Manus, he can twist his arm all the way around to defend his back.\nCatalyst Smash.\nManus quickly strikes the ground with his catalyst, dealing moderate damage. Often followed by a Short Arm Slam.\nHigh Jump Slam.\nManus jumps high above the player, then slams down with his catalyst and hand. This causes the player to lose their target lock afterwards.\nBerserk Combo.\nManus lets out a quick scream which makes him mad, then performs four swipes and two downward smashes, potentially hitting the player six times. This deals high damage, and drains a lot of stamina if blocked.\nDark Orb Barrage.\nManus uses his &lt;a href=\"Manus%20Catalyst\"&gt;Catalyst&lt;/a&gt; to cast a barrage of Dark Orbs, similar to the sorcery Dark Bead. The Dark Orbs spread out in a fan shape, making it easier to evade by strafing/rolling at close range. The Dark Orbs also drop to the ground after a moment, limiting the range of this spell.\nManus telegraphs this attack by holding his Catalyst out to his left, charging it for a moment, then swinging it towards the player to release the Dark Orbs. This attack can break the guards of most shields, so try blocking it with the Silver Pendant.\nAbyss Rain.\nManus casts a dark sorcery where multiple Dark Orbs appear in the air above and rain down around him in a sizable area of effect. Each Dark Orb can home in on the player within a certain range. The player can use their invulnerability frames from &lt;a href=\"Rolling\"&gt;fast rolling&lt;/a&gt; (12 invulnerability frames, 14 with the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood%20Grain%20Ring\"&gt;Dark Wood Grain Ring&lt;/a&gt;). Alternatively, use the Silver Pendant \u2014 it does not stop the Dark Orbs, but holds them in place above the player if you remain still, letting you roll away before the Silver Pendant wears off.\nAbyss Cage.\nDark Orbs propagate from above Manus, surrounding the entire arena before homing back in on Manus. This attack covers the entire arena, except for the area right next to Manus, like an inverted AoE. Dodge it by getting as close as possible to Manus once he starts casting. The Silver Pendant can also block this attack.\nMusic.\n&lt;embedvideo service=\"youtube\" alignment=\"center\" description=\"Dark Souls \u2014 Manus, Father of the Abyss by \"&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w2BEeW5W-1A&lt;/embedvideo&gt;"}
{"id": "7998", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7998", "title": "Manus Catalyst", "text": "The Manus Catalyst (\u30de\u30cc\u30b9\u306e\u5927\u6756) is a &lt;a href=\"Catalysts\"&gt;catalyst&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" and is only available with the &lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Artorias of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt; DLC.\nAvailability.\nAscend any catalyst with the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Manus\"&gt;Soul of Manus&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nSimilarly to the &lt;a href=\"Tin%20Crystallization%20Catalyst\"&gt;Tin Crystallization Catalyst&lt;/a&gt;, the Manus Catalyst greatly boosts the power of spells at the cost of halving their casts (including &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Miracles&lt;/a&gt;), though this may be offset with use of the &lt;a href=\"Dusk%20Crown%20Ring\"&gt;Dusk Crown Ring&lt;/a&gt;. In addition, the Manus Catalyst also boosts the power of Dark sorceries, based on the player's strength stat. \nThe strong attack of the Manus Catalyst is quite powerful for a catalyst, but very slow, and uses the Greataxe moveset.\nMagic Adjust.\nThe Manus Catalyst's Magic Adjust scales very quickly with intelligence, at a rate of about 8 points per level. However, it reaches its limit at 30, where the scaling drops to about 2 points per level, until 50 intelligence.\nStarting 32 int, the Manus Catalyst's Magic Adjust is outclassed by the &lt;a href=\"Tin%20Crystallization%20Catalyst\"&gt;Tin Crystallization Catalyst&lt;/a&gt;, which is also lighter. As intelligence grows higher, the Tin Crystallization Catalyst will out perform the Manus Catalyst even more. While the Manus Catalyst's grants a boost to dark sorceries (provided high strength), it will still not outperform the Tin Crystallization Catalyst. However, if the &lt;a href=\"Bellowing%20Dragoncrest%20Ring\"&gt;Bellowing Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt; and Dusk Crown are equipped, it can still outperform the Tin Crystallization Catalyst, albeit only in Dark Sorceries.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "8402", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8402", "title": "Marvellous Chester", "text": ""}
{"id": "6220", "revid": "56216774", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6220", "title": "Marvelous Chester", "text": "Marvelous Chester (\u7d20\u6674\u3089\u3057\u3044\u30c1\u30a7\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc) is a &lt;a href=\"character\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"merchant\"&gt;merchant&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Artorias of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt; DLC of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". Like the player, he was dragged back into the past, into the realm of ancient &lt;a href=\"Oolacile\"&gt;Oolacile&lt;/a&gt;. He's voiced by .\nPlot.\nMarvelous Chester is an enigmatic entity who sells a variety of useful items such as &lt;a href=\"Green%20Blossom\"&gt;Green Blossom&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Purple%20Moss%20Clump\"&gt;various&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Blooming%20Purple%20Moss%20Clump\"&gt;moss&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bloodred%20Moss%20Clump\"&gt;clumps&lt;/a&gt;, albeit for a higher price than normal. This makes him a very convenient stop for stocking up on items for the nearby &lt;a href=\"Battle%20of%20Stoicism\"&gt;Battle of Stoicism&lt;/a&gt; arena.\nUnfortunately, he is also a dangerous and unscrupulous individual, invading the player in an attempt to kill them. Even after being defeated, Marvelous Chester will still sell items to the player, although with a more disgruntled tone as if the player interacting with him is mocking him after being defeated.\nLore.\nMarvelous Chester was dragged into the past by &lt;a href=\"Manus%2C%20Father%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Manus, Father of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;. Little else is known about him. Given that his preferred weapon of choice is the &lt;a href=\"Sniper%20Crossbow\"&gt;Sniper Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;, it is likely that Marvelous Chester is from &lt;a href=\"Carim\"&gt;Carim&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nMarvelous Chester is dangerous at mid-range, as his bolts and his throwing knives can quickly rack up damage. In particular, his special throwing knives, which he throws in threes, greatly build up &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt;. At long range, he is capable of firing multiple bolts at the player in quick succession, possibly dealing heavy consecutive damage. At close range, he performs sweeping low kicks that do a fair amount of damage and &lt;a href=\"stamina\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; drain. Marvelous Chester also has an unusually high amount of HP for an NPC."}
