{"id": "7104", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7104", "title": "Mask of the Child", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Mask of the Child is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"head%20armor\"&gt;head armor&lt;/a&gt; piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nCharacteristics.\nThe Mask of the Child has very poor defense and resistances, and cannot be upgraded. However, it provides a +10 boost (50% pre-&lt;a href=\"patch%201.06\"&gt;patch 1.06&lt;/a&gt;) to &lt;a href=\"stamina\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; recovery. It is also very &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;light&lt;/a&gt;. These characteristics make the Mask of the Child popular for both &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; and PvE.\nThe Mask of the Child's stamina regeneration effect stacks with those of other stamina-boosting effects, such as those of the &lt;a href=\"Cloranthy%20Ring\"&gt;Cloranthy Ring&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Power%20Within\"&gt;Power Within&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Green%20Blossom\"&gt;Green Blossom&lt;/a&gt;s, and &lt;a href=\"Grass%20Crest%20Shield\"&gt;Grass Crest Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nCannot be reinforced.\nGallery.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
{"id": "7149", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7149", "title": "Mask of the Father", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Mask of the Father is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; piece of &lt;a href=\"head%20armor\"&gt;head armor&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Mask of the Father increases the player's maximum &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;equipment burden&lt;/a&gt; by 5% (down from 15% pre-&lt;a href=\"patch%201.06\"&gt;patch 1.06&lt;/a&gt;). However, it offers negligible defense and cannot be upgraded. \nIn a majority of cases the weight of this helm cancels out its own effect. In order for the 5% bonus equip load to cancel out the weight added on by the mask, for light rolls (25% burden), the character needs 96+ (56 END without modifiers, 24 with Havel's ring, 40 with ring of FaP, 14 with both) maximum equip load. For medium roll+, 8 END is required, which is the minimum possible END. \nThe Mask of the Father's burden increase perk stacks with those of other items: &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Havel's Ring&lt;/a&gt; (+50% equip burden) and the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Favor%20and%20Protection\"&gt;Ring of Favor and Protection&lt;/a&gt; (+20%). These effects stack multiplicatively rather than additively, which can make for very potent armor combinations. This is often employed as a build strategy for characters with high &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt;, as they can obtain heavy defenses and immense\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0while retaining speed and mobility.\nUpgrades.\nCannot be reinforced.\nGallery.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
{"id": "7150", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7150", "title": "Mask of the Mother", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Mask of the Mother is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"head%20armor\"&gt;head armor&lt;/a&gt; piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nWhen worn, the Mask of the Mother increases maximum &lt;a href=\"HP\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; by 10% \"(15% prior to &lt;a href=\"patch%201.06\"&gt;patch 1.06&lt;/a&gt;)\". Compared to other head armor, the Mask of the Mother is very &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;light&lt;/a&gt;, has poor defense and resistances, and cannot be upgraded.\nThe Mask of the Mother's HP-boosting effect stacks and compounds with the &lt;a href=\"Tiny%20Being%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Tiny Being's Ring&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Favor%20and%20Protection\"&gt;Ring of Favor and Protection&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nCannot be reinforced.\nGallery.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
