{"id": "6704", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6704", "title": "Prism Stone (Dark Souls)", "text": "Prism Stones are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nDrops a brightly glowing stone in front of the player, with a short (but unskippable) animation. If there is a light twinkling sound upon the stone landing, then the player will survive the fall if they jump off the ledge with full &lt;a href=\"Health\"&gt;Health&lt;/a&gt;. If a scream is heard upon impact, then the fall is fatal. There are 8 colors of prism stone. The colors serve no purpose other than aesthetic. The colors are purple, red, yellow, green, white, light blue, blue, and pink.\nOverview.\nPrism Stones are a useful utility item in many ways. In addition to their usefulness in gauging falling safety, they can serve as path markers or reminders, and can help prevent new players from getting lost. They are also useful in making sure that the path ahead is safe. This is particularly useful in the darkness of the &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20the%20Giants\"&gt;Tomb of the Giants&lt;/a&gt;, and on the invisible walkways of the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Cave\"&gt;Crystal Cave&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "44392", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44392", "title": "Prism Stone (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Prism Stones are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral Information.\nPrism Stones can be used to mark paths or dropped to see whether or not a fall will be fatal. They can also be traded to &lt;a href=\"Dyna%20%26amp%3B%20Tillo\"&gt;Dyna &amp; Tillo&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Things%20Betwixt\"&gt;Things Betwixt&lt;/a&gt; for low grade items. Common items include:"}
{"id": "131379", "revid": "1188343", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131379", "title": "Prism Stone (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Prism Stones are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUsage.\nWhen used, the player will drop one of these pebbles on the ground; each stone dropped will begin to sparkle in one of a few various colors, serving as a sort of marker. Known colors include: blue, green, purple, yellow, white and orange. What color a dropped stone will become is random and cannot be chosen.\nThey can also be dropped from ledges or cliffs in order to judge whether the player will survive a fall or not. If the stone emits a scream, then the drop is fatal.\nIn online play, Prism Stones can be useful for White Phantoms to guide hosts through levels, by signaling areas and items of interest (such as treasure chests and levers) or to provide trace amounts of light without equipping a &lt;a href=\"Torch%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Torch&lt;/a&gt;."}
