{"id": "67362", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=67362", "title": "Prisoner's Set", "text": "The Prisoner's Set is a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;light armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nEach piece can be dropped by various enemies:\nCharacteristics.\nThe Prisoner's set is a greatly tattered and worn out set that offers nearly nothing in terms of defense and for the few shreds of old cloth that they are, the armor is surprisingly heavy. While the chest piece and head gear are no different defense-wise, they offer 5% additional item discovery when worn.\nBecause of this, it is a must have to any player, at least possessing the chest piece and the hood, as it will make farming rare items much more easy task. Combining this with the &lt;a href=\"Covetous%20Gold%20Serpent%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Covetous Gold Serpent Ring&lt;/a&gt; (+2 if possible) is a very smart choice as it will stack with the inherent buff of the clothes."}
{"id": "31208", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31208", "title": "Prisoner's Tatters", "text": "The Prisoner's Tatters is a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Prisoner%27s%20Set\"&gt;Prisoner's Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nEach piece can be dropped by various enemies:\nCharacteristics.\nThe Prisoner's Tatters provide minimal defense and despite its low weight is still an inefficient piece of armor, meaning it is outperformed by most chest pieces. However, it is the only chest piece in the game that raises item discovery. Due to this effect, it can be considered a high risk, high reward item that can be used to optimize item discovery for farming purposes at the cost of taking significantly more damage.\nDue to the significant loss of defence, farming difficult enemies may be faster in the long term to use a conventional chest piece instead of the Prisoner's Tatters, due to reduced risk of deaths wasting time and the ability to fight more recklessly for faster farming runs."}
