{"id": "130625", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130625", "title": "Profaned Capital", "text": "The Profaned Capital (\u7f6a\u306e\u90fd, Tsumi no Miyako, Capital of Sin) is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is a subsection of the &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThe Profaned Capital is a highly decimated ruin that has somehow sunken into a great chasm, the only natural light pouring from a crack in the cavernous walls. Very little of what was once a proud civilization remains, making this area quite small. The state of the Capital is in such disarray that the only things remaining are a few bridges and tunnels, a vestige of a great tower, a church sunken in a swamp, and the throne room of &lt;a href=\"Yhorm%20the%20Giant\"&gt;Yhorm the Giant&lt;/a&gt;. The rest of what was once a prosperous realm has long since corroded away. An overlook of the Capital is viewable from Irithyll Dungeon.\nOne of two bonfires is within the central tower, its interior hollowed out, but its heights traversable thanks to numerous ladders up and down its interior and exterior. The source of the ladders is no mystery, as the corpse of &lt;a href=\"Laddersmith%20Gilligan\"&gt;Laddersmith Gilligan&lt;/a&gt; can be seen splayed out right by the bonfire, where the player can learn a gesture.\nOff to the side is a network of tunnels with multiple holes in the floor, opening up to a caverous, filthy swamp that inflicts Toxic instead of Poison and is occupied by &lt;a href=\"Sewer%20Centipede\"&gt;Sewer Centipedes&lt;/a&gt;. An old church in visible disarray is half-sunken in the swamp, populated by &lt;a href=\"Monstrosity%20of%20Sin\"&gt;grotesque hand-headed creatures&lt;/a&gt;. A path by the church leads back to Irithyll Dungeon, where one can access otherwise-blocked cells.\nOn the other side of the chasm and across a half-decimated bridge is a great and ornate fa\u00e7ade, flanked by inactive gargoyles. Handmaids surround a golden brazier that perpetually burns, perhaps being the Profaned Flame itself. The entrance is flanked by two antechambers filled with more handmaids, the left one also accessible by the previously-mentioned bridge. Scattered across the whole floor are artifacts of gold and silver, as well as piles of charred, half-melted bodies. Straight ahead is the chamber of Yhorm himself.\nLore.\nThe Profaned Capital was ruled over by Yhorm the Giant, descendant of an ancient conqueror, who was nevertheless asked by the previously subjugated people to lead them. A sorcery school was established there, one of two leading schools claiming to be heir to the legacy of &lt;a href=\"Big%20Hat%20Logan\"&gt;Big Hat Logan&lt;/a&gt;. The court sorcerers from the Profaned Capital also served as oracles, as golden stitching of their robes suggest. Although they were undeniably intelligent and adept in their craft, it is possible that they did not follow Big Hat Logan as much as they claimed to.\nAs a result of a curse shared between &lt;a href=\"Monstrosity%20of%20Sin\"&gt;a group of women&lt;/a&gt;, the everlasting Profaned Flame was triggered. Despite their culpability, the women went on living carelessly, although they then turned into &lt;a href=\"Monstrosity%20of%20Sin\"&gt;malformed creatures&lt;/a&gt;.. After Yhorm became a Lord of Cinder in order to stop the Profaned Flame, the city was burned down by fire said to be coming from the sky. It consumed only humans.\nPart of the flame is preserved in icy skull, found in &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. It serves as a prison, in which guards are &lt;a href=\"Jailer\"&gt;Jailer&lt;/a&gt;s, survivors from the Profaned Capital. &lt;a href=\"Jailer%20Handmaid\"&gt;Handmaids&lt;/a&gt; serving in the Capital reportedly took pleasure in hurting others. Both Jailers and Handmaids are survivors of the Profaned Capitol, wield fiery attacks, and enjoy inflicting pain on others, signifying that the Profaned Flame not only has physical effect, but psychological ones. &lt;a href=\"Gargoyle\"&gt;Gargoyle&lt;/a&gt;s wielding either &lt;a href=\"Gargoyle%20Flame%20Spear\"&gt;spears&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Gargoyle%20Flame%20Hammer\"&gt;hammers&lt;/a&gt; (into which the Profaned Flame is imbued) are encountered throughout the Profaned Capital. It is not known if they appeared before or after the city was ruined.\nSometime after the Profaned Flame destroyed the Capital, &lt;a href=\"Pontiff%20Sulyvahn\"&gt;Pontiff Sulyvahn&lt;/a&gt; discovered the Profaned Flame and the Capital, \"a burning ambition took root within him\". He would later infuse the Profaned Flame within his own &lt;a href=\"Profaned%20Greatsword\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, and would perhaps introduce the Profaned Flame to the Fire Witches, leading to their hearts being consumed by it. They would learn to use its power and summon firestorms with their halberds., and would eventually take Irithyll for themselves. \nBonfires.\nThe Profaned Capital is a subsection of the &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt; and comprises the following &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfires&lt;/a&gt;:"}
{"id": "131528", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131528", "title": "Profaned Coal", "text": "The Profaned Coal is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;, in the lower cell block that precedes the route to the &lt;a href=\"Profaned%20Capital\"&gt;Profaned Capital&lt;/a&gt;. It is inside the cell containing several &lt;a href=\"Wretch\"&gt;Wretch&lt;/a&gt;es, just opposite of &lt;a href=\"Karla\"&gt;Karla&lt;/a&gt;'s cell.\nUsage.\nGive the coal to &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Andre\"&gt;Blacksmith Andre&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; to allow usage of the following gems for infusions:"}
{"id": "133549", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133549", "title": "Profaned Flame", "text": "Profaned Flame (\u7f6a\u306e\u708e) is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;, on the floor in the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Slave\"&gt;Giant Slave&lt;/a&gt;'s cell. It is guarded by the giant itself and numerous &lt;a href=\"Hound%20Rat\"&gt;Hound Rat&lt;/a&gt;s.\nEffect.\nThe caster waves the catalyst, conjuring a flame at the target's location. The flames concentrate and focus at the location for approximately 1 second before exploding, inficting 2.6 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst as &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. The explosion will also knock down any enemies in the area. \nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "140219", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140219", "title": "Profaned Flame (skill)", "text": "Profaned Flame is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nUpon activating the skill, the player gains almost instant &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; and 100 &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; health, and lunges down and forward while bringing the sword to their left. Inputting a strong attack while in this lunge animation will ignite the sword and bring it into an upward arc that ends behind the player, inflicting 1.85 times the weapon's Attack Rating as damage and 1.9 times the weapon's base Poise damage to any enemies in front of the player, while knocking them skyward. Igniting the sword will buff it with 80 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage for 45 seconds.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nThis skill can be useful for dealing strong focused damage to any enemies in front of the player, while simultaneously buffing the sword. As the Profaned Greatsword has no &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; requirements, the buff is a great way to add Fire damage to a weapon without the need to invest into caster stats. This Fire damage can be quite useful against enemies that are weak to the element, such as &lt;a href=\"Pus%20of%20Man\"&gt;Pus of Man&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Corpse%20Grub\"&gt;Corpse Grub&lt;/a&gt;s.\nOnline gameplay.\nThis skill works exactly the same as the &lt;a href=\"Stomp%20%28upward%29\"&gt;upward Stomp&lt;/a&gt;, only with the addition of buffing the weapon prior to performing the upward slash. As such, it can be used in the same way as Stomp, to trade with opponents and deal immense damage to them while disabling them. The increased Fire damage from the buff can then be used to further gain an advantage over opponents in combat."}
{"id": "131434", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131434", "title": "Profaned Greatsword", "text": "The Profaned Greatsword (\u7f6a\u306e\u5927\u5263) is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;soul-transposed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by transposing the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Pontiff%20Sulyvahn\"&gt;Soul of Pontiff Sulyvahn&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt; for 3,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nA true quality weapon, the Profaned Greatsword is a well-balanced ultra greatsword with a versatile moveset and devastating power attacks.\nWhile it tends slightly towards &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; in its &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, the Profaned Greatsword also scales very well with &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, granting it formidable damage output on builds that focus on leveling physical stats. It is also one of the lightest weapons in its class, only outweighing the &lt;a href=\"Astora%20Greatsword\"&gt;Astora Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Zweihander%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Zweihander&lt;/a&gt; of the ultra greatswords that can be two-handed. It also has the third-highest base damage of the ultra greatswords, after the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Knight Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Ringed%20Knight%20Paired%20Greatswords\"&gt;Ringed Knight Paired Greatswords&lt;/a&gt;, and on a full quality build is out-damaged only by the Black Knight Greatsword when two-handed.\nThe Profaned Greatsword has a very robust moveset, allowing the wielder to perform horizontal and vertical swings, along with various thrusting attacks as needed. Additionally, as it is imbued with the power of the Profaned Flame, fully charged strong attacks with this weapon will inflict additional &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage for that attack, making the strong attacks performed by this weapon unusually deadly. Its &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Profaned%20Flame%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Profaned Flame&lt;/a&gt;, can be used to give the weapon a longer-lived buff and inflict Fire damage with all attacks.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nVideos.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "58031", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=58031", "title": "Profound Still", "text": "Profound Still\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Hexes\"&gt;hex&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Darkdiver%20Grandahl\"&gt;Darkdiver Grandahl&lt;/a&gt; for 13,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral Information.\nSimilar to the effects of &lt;a href=\"Vow%20of%20Silence\"&gt;Vow of Silence&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", when cast, causes a wave of dark energy to emit from the player. Any enemy that comes into contact with the wave is unable to cast spells for 30 seconds. However, it does possess a somewhat slow &lt;a href=\"casting%20time\"&gt;casting time&lt;/a&gt; (though not the longest) and players will most likely avoid the caster mistaking it for other spells. Finding an opportune moment to cast is definitely recommended.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
