{"id": "137129", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=137129", "title": "Proof of a Concord Well Kept", "text": "The Proof of a Concord Well Kept is a &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nAs a &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Sentinels%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Blue Sentinel&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Darkmoon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Darkmoon Blade&lt;/a&gt; summoned into the world of a &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20Blue%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Way of Blue&lt;/a&gt; adherent, this item is obtained by defeating a red invader who has equipped the &lt;a href=\"Aldrich%20Faithful%20%28item%29\"&gt;Aldrich Faithful (item)&lt;/a&gt; covenant item.\nUsage.\nUse to acquire two &lt;a href=\"Proof%20of%20a%20Concord%20Kept\"&gt;Proofs of a Concord \nKept&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "52788", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52788", "title": "Protective Chime", "text": "The Protective Chime is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Sacred%20Chimes\"&gt;sacred chime&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;\"Dark Souls II\".&lt;/a&gt;\nAvailability.\nThe Protective Chime can be found in a chest behind an illusory wall in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Iron%20Keep\"&gt;Iron Keep&lt;/a&gt;. It is on the ledge after\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Belfry%20Sol\"&gt;Belfry Sol&lt;/a&gt;, where the player can drop down to return to the Belfry Sol\u00a0Approach. The &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Spirit%20Tree%20Shield\"&gt;Grand Spirit Tree Shield&lt;/a&gt; is found in the same chest. \nCharacteristics.\nFor Miracles, this chime is not very notable. It is as fast as the &lt;a href=\"Cleric%27s%20Sacred%20Chime\"&gt;Cleric's Sacred Chime&lt;/a&gt; and up until 40 &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; will be ever so slightly stronger than it, and compared to the &lt;a href=\"Priest%27s%20Chime\"&gt;Priest's Chime&lt;/a&gt; it is closer than the Cleric's in strength while still being faster but will be more and more outclassed as Faith is increased. Ultimately, it is not very useful due to being encountered much later than either Chime, which will also most likely already be upgraded a bit. \nFor Hexes however, there is a genuine niche. While it will in the end be outclassed in damage by the even faster &lt;a href=\"Caitha%27s%20Chime\"&gt;Caitha's Chime&lt;/a&gt;, up until that point it is somewhat comparable to the &lt;a href=\"Archdrake%20Chime\"&gt;Archdrake Chime&lt;/a&gt; due to still keeping somewhat close in power while having 20 more Casting Speed bonus. "}
{"id": "98000", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=98000", "title": "Prowlers", "text": "The\u00a0Prowlers are a group of &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;dark spirits&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nLocation.\nNext to the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Idol\"&gt;Ashen Idol&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and on the staircase that lead to &lt;a href=\"Brume%20Tower%23Bonfires\"&gt;The Smelter Throne&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThe Prowlers will invade once the player has approached the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Idol\"&gt;Ashen Idol&lt;/a&gt; before &lt;a href=\"Brume%20Tower%23Bonfires\"&gt;The Smelter Throne&lt;/a&gt;. Initially, one Prowler will invade the player, but once they proceed to the staircase, four more will spawn in and engage in combat. All five Prowlers must be defeated in order to banish the invader.\nStrategy.\nUpon stepping out of the lift, the first Prowler will spawn next to a nearby &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Idol\"&gt;Ashen Idol&lt;/a&gt; positioned in plain sight. This idol heals enemies in a similar fashion to &lt;a href=\"Warmth\"&gt;Warmth&lt;/a&gt;. The player may fight the Prowler in front of the idol, concentrating in dealing consecutive attacks to compensate for the constant healing it provides. Another method is to simply lure the Prowler back to where the lift is, out of the reach of the idol's healing powers, and confront him there. When the Prowler has sustained enough damage, however, he will retreat back to where the idol is to replenish his health. Once defeated, the player is advised to deactivate the idol with the use of a &lt;a href=\"Smelter%20Wedge\"&gt;Smelter Wedge&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs soon as the player steps on the nearby staircase, four more Prowlers will spawn. All of them will already be hostile and come rushing after the player, even they haven't seen them yet. It's not advisable to take on all of them at once, or they will pummel the player with arrows and melee attacks which cause &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up. A good strategy consists in simply running back to the lift (wearing the &lt;a href=\"Silvercat%20Ring\"&gt;Silvercat Ring&lt;/a&gt; is recommended to avoid falling damage if the lift is too far away) and simply stay on it until all of them lose interest. Then approach the staircase slowly and draw them in one by one by using a ranged attack. These four Prowlers have significantly less health and stamina than the first one, and their attacks frequently leave them open for &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;s or normal combos.\nEach of them uses an\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt;, so\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Lloyd%27s%20Talisman%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lloyd's Talismans&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0are very useful for fighting them.\u00a0"}
