{"id": "53023", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53023", "title": "Prowling Magus", "text": "The Prowling Magus is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nLocated past the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Amana%23Bonfires\"&gt;Rise of the Dead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Amana\"&gt;Shrine of Amana&lt;/a&gt;. The player must be &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;hollowed&lt;/a&gt; in order to open the door to proceed.\nIn\u00a0\"\", one can be found in &lt;a href=\"Aldia%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Aldia's Keep&lt;/a&gt;, in the room on the right of the main hallway (&lt;a href=\"Aldia%20Key\"&gt;Aldia Key&lt;/a&gt; required).\nStrategy.\nThe Prowling Magus near the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Amana%23Bonfires\"&gt;Rise of the Dead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; acts in the very same way as the &lt;a href=\"Prowling%20Magus%20and%20Congregation\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; encountered in &lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Cove%20Tseldora\"&gt;Brightstone Cove&lt;/a&gt;. The Magus has low &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; and is easily staggered, so attacking in quick succession will quickly take care of this foe.\nAttacks.\nUses the same attacks as its &lt;a href=\"Prowling%20Magus%20and%20Congregation\"&gt;counterpart&lt;/a&gt;, fires dark orbs at the player and performs an &lt;a href=\"Area%20of%20Effect\"&gt;area-of-effect&lt;/a&gt; dark blast. This version also equips a &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Bone%20Shield\"&gt;Cursed Bone Shield&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "52316", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52316", "title": "Prowling Magus and Congregation", "text": "The Prowling Magus and Congregation is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". \u00a0\nLocation.\nThis boss is found in &lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Cove%20Tseldora\"&gt;Brightstone Cove Tseldora&lt;/a&gt; in a ruined Chapel, before the &lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Cove%20Tseldora%23Bonfires\"&gt;Chapel Threshold&lt;/a&gt; bonfire. \nDescription.\nThis boss is actually a large collection of enemies comprised of:\nThe Magus is a hexer donning a dark tattered robe, a &lt;a href=\"Warlock%20Mask\"&gt;Warlock Mask&lt;/a&gt; and a unique catalyst. The Congregation is made up of diverse types of hollows. Upon traversing the fog wall, the hollows are initially seen prostrating before the Magus. The Magus has his own health bar, but the health bar of the Congregation counts for all of the\u00a0hollows.\nPlot.\nThe Magus was an evil warlock hailing from &lt;a href=\"Aldia%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Aldia's Keep&lt;/a&gt; who partook in forbidden rituals, infecting its body and mind with &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;dark magic&lt;/a&gt;. The Magus leads a small congregation of &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;s within a chapel, the remnants of Brightstone Cove Tseldora's ravaged population since the infestation of &lt;a href=\"Parasite%20Spider\"&gt;spiders&lt;/a&gt;. The hollows act as puppets to the Magus' will, and may be under the influence of the warlock's dark powers.\nSummoning.\n&lt;a href=\"Benhart%20of%20Jugo\"&gt;Benhart of Jugo&lt;/a&gt; can be summoned for this fight. His summon sign is at the &lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Cove%20Tseldora%23Bonfires\"&gt;Royal Army Campsite&lt;/a&gt; bonfire in Brightstone Cove, in the tent closest to the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Peasant\"&gt;Undead Peasant&lt;/a&gt; that is amongst four bodies with loot.\nStrategies.\nThe difficulty of this boss does not come from the boss itself, but rather the number of enemies. Killing the &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Priest\"&gt;priests&lt;/a&gt; first is advised, as they can\u00a0heal surrounding enemies and\u00a0cast very strong &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Miracles%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;miracles&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0By using &lt;a href=\"Profound%20Still\"&gt;Profound Still&lt;/a&gt;, one can make both the priests and the Magus unable to cast magic, which makes them considerably weaker for the duration of the battle.\nThere are two variants of hollows: &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Laborer\"&gt;Undead Laborer&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Supplicant\"&gt;Undead Supplicant&lt;/a&gt;s. The laborers are faster and can surround the player with ease, while the supplicants will often be hindered by the benches placed around the area and won't pose any serious threat other than the occasional attack or hindering the player's movement. Any large sweeping attacks or spells with an area-of-effect are effective; for example, the &lt;a href=\"Halberd%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt;'s running attack (be wary of its &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;, as hitting multiple enemies at once will degrade weapons quickly) or the &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Storm%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Chaos Storm&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0pyromancy.\u00a0A well-placed shot of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Soul%20Appease\"&gt;Soul Appease&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0can also deal with most of the Congregation in one attack.\nThe Prowling Magus himself uses hexes which can deal a lot of &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage if they connect. However, he doesn't have much health and most of his attacks are fairly easy to dodge.\nHiding behind the benches is a good way to block the priests' lightning spear attacks and provides time to heal. However, any attacks connecting with the benches will destroy them.\nDefenses.\n&lt;a href=\"Prowling%20Magus\"&gt;Prowling Magus&lt;/a&gt;.\n (Stats are from Param Studio and are not estimated)&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Priest\"&gt;Hollow Priest&lt;/a&gt;s x 2.\n (Stats are from Param Studio and are not estimated)&lt;br&gt;Strike/Slash/Thrust defense are applied on top of Physical Defense. -35% slash means taking 135% damage.\n&lt;a href=\"Undead%20Laborer\"&gt;Undead Laborer&lt;/a&gt;s x 5.\n (Stats are from Param Studio and are not estimated)&lt;br&gt;Strike/Slash/Thrust defense are applied on top of Physical Defense. -35% slash means taking 135% damage.\n&lt;a href=\"Undead%20Supplicant\"&gt;Undead Supplicant&lt;/a&gt;s x 3.\n (Stats are from Param Studio and are not estimated)"}
{"id": "143728", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143728", "title": "Prying Wedge", "text": "Prying Wedge is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nActivating the skill causes the player to charge forward and chain two powerful upward slashes, which deal high stamina damage against raised shields. Transitioning into the strong attack will result in a strong downward strike.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nThis skill is generally quite useful against shield-carrying enemies, as the initial chain has good forward momentum and can be initiated quite quickly. It also inflicts high &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; damage, and is capable of inflicting an impressive amount of stagger even on foes with standing poise such as &lt;a href=\"Darkwraith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Darkwraiths&lt;/a&gt;, so it can be useful even against foes without shields.\nDue to the high stamina damage, the first two slashes are very useful for breaking down shields, and can either inflict bonus &lt;a href=\"Instability\"&gt;Instability&lt;/a&gt; damage with the second attack of the chain, or result in a guard break and leave the foe open for a riposte.\nOnline gameplay.\nThis skill is particularly useful against players who rely on shields for defense, moreso due to the the attack's strong forward momentum, which allows the wielder to quickly close the distance to their target. While the effect is comparable to the guard break of &lt;a href=\"Stance%20%28Straight%20Sword%29\"&gt;Stance&lt;/a&gt;, it is considerably more powerful due to the double attack of the chain and the forward charge. In this regard, it is also much more useful than a kick, which is much shorter ranged and slower.\nHowever, what makes this skill truly shine is that the strong attack strike can be delayed for a considerable amount of time after the initial chain is complete, and possesses &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; frames which allows it to be used for trades against smaller weapons. As it comes down with a relatively short delay, the strong attack can be used to roll-catch players who attempt to dodge immediately after being hit by the chain. As well, the strong attack can be used as the final guard-breaking hit on particularly strong shields, if the shield manages to survive the first two strikes.\nThe strong guard-breaking ability of this skill means that it may behoove the player to equip the &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Slayer%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Knight Slayer's Ring&lt;/a&gt; in order to further augment its stamina damage to lethal levels."}
{"id": "140172", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140172", "title": "Puncture", "text": "Puncture is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nWhen held, the player enters a ready stance in preparation for firing an arrow. Pressing the strong or weak attack button takes out an &lt;a href=\"Ammunition%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;arrow&lt;/a&gt; of the selected variety, nocks it, draws it back and then releases it after a short delay. This skill cannot be cancelled once begun.\nAn arrow fired using this skill will inflict 25% more damage upon striking a target. If hitting a target with a raised shield, a percentage of the damage will pierce the shield, depending on the size of the arrow fired.\nConsumes 9 &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; per arrow fired, or 7 FP with the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Ring\"&gt;Farron Ring&lt;/a&gt; equipped.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nGiven the luxury of time and place of choosing, this skill allows players to maximize the damage inflicted with each individual arrow. Further augmenting the strength of each attack with equipment such as the &lt;a href=\"Hawk%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Hawk Ring&lt;/a&gt; and even &lt;a href=\"Lloyd%27s%20Sword%20Ring\"&gt;Lloyd's Sword Ring&lt;/a&gt; can amplify the damage of each attack to the point of making the bow a damage-dealer in its own right. The FP cost of this skill can be recouped via various methods, ranging from a &lt;a href=\"Simple%20Gem\"&gt;Simple&lt;/a&gt;-infused off-hand tool to an &lt;a href=\"Executioner%27s%20Greatsword\"&gt;Executioner's Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnline gameplay.\nWhile ideal for combining with the &lt;a href=\"Obscuring%20Ring\"&gt;Obscuring Ring&lt;/a&gt; to deliver high-damage harassment to an opponent from range, this skill can also find use in chipping down opponents who hide behind 100% physical block shields. The fraction of damage that chips through shields is greater than that of a &lt;a href=\"Greatbows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatbow&lt;/a&gt; firing greatarrows using the &lt;a href=\"Puncturing%20Arrow\"&gt;Puncturing Arrow&lt;/a&gt; skill, making it useful for inflicting actual meaningful damage against defensive foes, even those who wield titans like &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Greatshield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Havel's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "140212", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140212", "title": "Puncturing Arrow", "text": "Puncturing Arrow is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is exclusive to &lt;a href=\"Greatbows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatbows&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThe wielder readies the greatbow, entering a prepared firing stance and holding steady; moving will cancel this stance. The player can then nock the greatarrow of their choice and release it when ready. The arrow will gain increased travel distance (and with it damage fall-off) and inflict 12% more damage, and will penetrate any enemies it hits, allowing it to damage multiple foes with a single shot.\nIf used without the required &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt;, the arrows will deal less damage than regular shots and inflict reduced knockback but will still penetrate.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nAs the skill requires the player to stand still prior to even readying an arrow, it can be difficult to use against mobile targets. However, the increased damage and penetrating nature of the shot makes it extremely useful for dealing with crowds of enemies, particularly if they can be funneled through a single approach, such as down a narrow hallway.\nOnline.\nOther players will generally not stand around waiting to be shot with a greatbow, and can easily dodge the shots that they can see coming, so the primary use of this skill is through ambushes with the &lt;a href=\"Obscuring%20Ring\"&gt;Obscuring Ring&lt;/a&gt;. This skill allows invaders to get a powerful first strike in on unwary hosts and summoned phantoms, helping to narrow their Estus advantage before properly engaging them. Keep in mind that it is incapable of dealing significant damage through raised shields, so against wary parties it may be useful to try to strike them from the sides or behind."}
{"id": "140224", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140224", "title": "Punitive Flame", "text": "Punitive Flame is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "150982", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150982", "title": "Purging Monument", "text": "The Purging Monument (\u89e3\u546a\u306e\u7891, \"Kaishu no Ishibumi\", Monument of the Absolution of the Curse) is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt is a small, separated area in &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28location%29\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;, home to a rather unnerving \"sculpture\" conformed by what appears to be a mass of flesh and bones, perhaps the remains of innumerable &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;s which apparently have filled up and poured out from an old well.\nIts access is linked to the \"show your humanity\" riddle and consists of an area with a few, albeit powerful enemies, a bridge, and the monument itself.\nAccess.\nFinding access to the Purging Monument is not so obvious at first and requires the player to solve the \"show your humanity\" riddle. The riddle itself is located near the &lt;a href=\"The_Ringed_City_%28location%29%23Bonfires\"&gt;Ringed City Streets bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, in the section unlocked as a shortcut. The solution consists in transforming oneself into a &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20Phantom\"&gt;Humanity Phantom&lt;/a&gt; (through the use of the &lt;a href=\"Chameleon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Chameleon&lt;/a&gt; sorcery or a &lt;a href=\"Young%20White%20Branch\"&gt;Young White Branch&lt;/a&gt;) (can only be done while standing in the water) and approach the entrance to this area. Doing so will trigger a ladder to descend, granting access.\nInside, two &lt;a href=\"Ringed%20Knight\"&gt;Ringed Knight&lt;/a&gt;s and one &lt;a href=\"Judicator%20Giant\"&gt;Judicator Giant&lt;/a&gt; can be encountered. Near the giant are stairs going down. Once at the bottom of the stairs, fall on the right and cross the bridge to get to the monument.\nServices.\nThe Purging Monument provides a number of services to the player depending on their current status in a similar way as &lt;a href=\"Velka%2C%20the%20Goddess%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Velka&lt;/a&gt;'s statue does in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;:\nQuestline.\n&lt;a href=\"Amnesiac%20Lapp\"&gt;Amnesiac Lapp&lt;/a&gt; makes the first mention of this monument's existence and tells the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;Ashen One&lt;/a&gt; how he has been running in circles searching for it throughout the swamp without success, his intentions being to cure himself from his &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt;ing in the hopes of regaining his memory, who he was, and what was his real name in his past life.\nThe player can then embark on a mission of finding the monument and return to Lapp to inform him of its location, progressing with this through his questline."}
{"id": "4570", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4570", "title": "Purging Stone", "text": "Purging Stones are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nA Purging Stone reduces &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28auxiliary%20effect%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"buildup\"&gt;buildup&lt;/a&gt; and cures the &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%23Curse\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt;."}
