{"id": "2082", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2082", "title": "Pyromancer", "text": "The Pyromancer is one of the &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nPyromancers combine early access to &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; with decent &lt;a href=\"Physical%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt;. Pyromancers are also unique in that they start at Level 1, so they possess the advantage of being able to invade any person at the start, as well as keeping at the lowest level possible. These factors make the Pyromancer a good choice for PvP builds.\nThe Pyromancer has quite a few advantages early in the game, including the ability to combine reasonably strong melee attacks from the &lt;a href=\"Hand%20Axe\"&gt;Hand Axe&lt;/a&gt; with very potent &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; pyromancy. Their starting armor, while decrepit looking, actually has strong resistance to both Poison and Fire, which are common hazards in the early areas of the game.\nPyromancers do, however, start with the worst shield in the game, although it is still reasonably effective up until the point where a player can obtain a better one.\nThe basic pyromancy trainer, &lt;a href=\"Laurentius%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Laurentius of the Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt;, is one of the last trainers available to the player. Therefore, pyromancers have access to no pyromancies other than Fireball until this point, that is; without the &lt;a href=\"Master%20Key\"&gt;Master Key&lt;/a&gt; which allows anyone access to &lt;a href=\"Quelana%20of%20Izalith\"&gt;Quelana of Izalith&lt;/a&gt; who teaches expert level pyromancies, and &lt;a href=\"Eingyi\"&gt;Eingyi&lt;/a&gt; who has a secret &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flame\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20Mist%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;toxic spells&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "143032", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143032", "title": "Pyromancer's Parting Flame", "text": "The Pyromancer's Parting Flame is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flames%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy flame&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound on a corpse in the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Painted World of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;, in the tower where &lt;a href=\"Livid%20Pyromancer%20Dunnel\"&gt;Livid Pyromancer Dunnel&lt;/a&gt; invades (&lt;a href=\"Crossbreed%20Priscilla\"&gt;Crossbreed Priscilla&lt;/a&gt;'s boss arena). The path to the tower is hidden behind an &lt;a href=\"Illusory%20Wall%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;illusory wall&lt;/a&gt; in the lower level of Ariandel Chapel basement.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Pyromancer's Parting Flame has slightly inferior &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; compared to the standard &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flame%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt;; however, it has a unique feature in that most offensive spells will be preluded by a variant of &lt;a href=\"Combustion%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Combustion&lt;/a&gt;, inflicting 0.8 times the catalyst's Attack Rating as &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage to targets that are at very close range. This means that should an offensive spell be cast at melee range, the target will be hit by the flame prior to taking damage from the spell itself, increasing the total damage dealt. As such, the Pyromancer's Parting Flame is optimal for close-range &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; such as &lt;a href=\"Black%20Flame%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Flame&lt;/a&gt;. However, due to the inferior &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; compared to the standard flame, it cannot deal as much damage with medium or long range pyromancies.\nSpells cast with the Parting Flame also have 15% increased stamina cost, regardless of whether or not they utilize the aforementioned feature. Naturally, this does not affect &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Surge%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire Surge&lt;/a&gt; due to the spell not having any stamina cost to begin with.\nIts primary defining feature is its &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Parting%20Flame\"&gt;Parting Flame&lt;/a&gt;, which allows for the replenishment of the player's &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt; by killing enemies, greatly increasing long-term survival, though its long cast time makes it far less effective when in the midst of combat.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;a href=\"Cornyx%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Cornyx of the Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt; can upgrade the Pyromancer's Parting Flame up to +10. This requires a total of 12 of each standard titanite (&lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Shard%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Shards&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Large%20Titanite%20Shard%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Large Shards&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Chunk%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Chunks&lt;/a&gt;) as well as a single &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Slab%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Slab&lt;/a&gt;. Fully upgrading the flame will also cost a total of 10,944 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nGallery.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "173161", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=173161", "title": "Pyromancer (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Pyromancer is one of the &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%203\"&gt;Dark Souls 3&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt is a class with high &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;, making it suitable for builds based on &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; or Dark Spells. It has the lowest &lt;a href=\"Luck\"&gt;Luck&lt;/a&gt; of all classes, a trait shared with the &lt;a href=\"Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Knight&lt;/a&gt;. \n&lt;a href=\"Fireball%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; is a strong spell and benefits from the fact that many early enemies are vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;, if a bit expensive and hard to aim due to it being thrown in an arc. The Pyromancer effectively still has two Pyromancies due to its casting tool, the &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flame%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt;, having the classic pyromancy &lt;a href=\"Combustion%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Combustion&lt;/a&gt; as its &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Weapon Art&lt;/a&gt; for a melee range alternative. The &lt;a href=\"Great%20Swamp%20Ring\"&gt;Great Swamp Ring&lt;/a&gt; will boost the damage of Fireball by 12% but since Combustion is a Weapon Art it won't be boosted. \nSpeaking of, the &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flame%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt; will be the only casting tool for Pyromancy for a while and while it scales with both Intelligence and Faith it still works relatively well with more investment in one stat over the other. There is however one complicating factor for the scaling: unless Intelligence is at least 22 (goes down to a minimum of 18 as the Pyromancy Flame is upgraded), certain spells (Fireball, &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Orb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire Orb&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Great%20Chaos%20Fire%20Orb\"&gt;Great Chaos Fire Orb&lt;/a&gt;) won't scale with the Faith part of the Flame and therefore end up doing greatly decreased damage on a Faith build with insufficient investment in Intelligence. When wielded in the right hand it has the peculiar function of working as a free, short range punch that deals fire damage, helping against enemies weak to fire like the ooze-like &lt;a href=\"Writhing%20Rotten%20Flesh\"&gt;Writhing Rotten Flesh&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Hand%20Axe%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Hand Axe&lt;/a&gt; is a surprisingly useful weapon. While it is pretty short, really only outranging &lt;a href=\"Daggers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Daggers&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Thrall%20Axe\"&gt;Thrall Axe&lt;/a&gt;, it is quick and deals decent damage for its size. Its &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Weapon Art&lt;/a&gt; is &lt;a href=\"Warcry\"&gt;Warcry&lt;/a&gt;, boosting weapon damage by 10% for 30 seconds and changing the heavy attack into a charge. While the charge is rather difficult to use for a Pyromancer in its default armor due to low &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; and the small size of the weapon itself, the damage boost is easy to use for foes resistant to Fire. \nA mediocre &lt;a href=\"Caduceus%20Round%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Caduceus Round Shield&lt;/a&gt; rounds out the equipment setup. While it is unsuitable for blocking anything but the occasional Magic attack, it is still a light &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Parry&lt;/a&gt; tool. Actually blocking attacks should be left to the physically sturdy shields such as the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Eagle%20Kite%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Silver Eagle Kite Shield&lt;/a&gt;. \nIts &lt;a href=\"Pyromancer%20Set\"&gt;Pyromancer Set&lt;/a&gt; has good elemental defences and &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; resistances but bad physical defences. \nThe primary Pyromancy trainer is found early on, in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;."}
