{"id": "161054", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=161054", "title": "Pyromancy", "text": ""}
{"id": "3051", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3051", "title": "Pyromancy (Dark Souls)", "text": "Pyromancy is a type of in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nAll pyromancies, even those not directly related to fire, are cast with a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flame\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt;.\nTo obtain one, one can choose the &lt;a href=\"Pyromancer\"&gt;Pyromancer&lt;/a&gt; as their &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;starting class&lt;/a&gt;, or talk to the pyromancy trainers: &lt;a href=\"Laurentius%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Laurentius of the Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0after he is rescued and if the player does not already have a Pyromancy Flame, or\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Eingyi\"&gt;Eingyi&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0if the player has 11 &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; or higher. Upgrading a Pyromancy Flame can only be done through one of the formerly mentioned pyromancers, as well as\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Quelana%20of%20Izalith\"&gt;Quelana of Izalith&lt;/a&gt;, who can ascend the flame further than Laurentius or Eingyi.\nUnlike &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Miracles&lt;/a&gt;, Pyromancies are unique in that they do not require a specific &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; level, or scale with any stat. Rather, players may upgrade their Pyromancy Flame 15 times at any pyromancy teacher, then ascend once and upgrade their Ascended Pyromancy flame another 5 times to increase their damage output. This means that players can use a high level Pyromancy Flame to deal high damage at low soul levels \u2013 making it useful for PvP. (Note, the Ascended Pyromancy Flame does not scale with intelligence, despite the item indicating such)\nUnfortunately, many pyromancies share the deficiency of having limited range and having a slow casting time. This means that in order to use pyromancies properly, players must plan ahead and predict enemy movements. It also makes pyromancies dangerous to use in close combat, especially against other players. However, the speed of casting pyromancies can be increased through investing in the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0attribute, the limit being 45 points in Dexterity before no further casting speed increases are given to the player, making pyromancies a far more viable choice for close range combat.\nLore.\nBefore the creation of Pyromancy, flame sorceries were used by the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Witch%20of%20Izalith\"&gt;Witch of Izalith&lt;/a&gt;, her Daughters of Chaos, and later by the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Demon%20Firesage\"&gt;Demon Firesage&lt;/a&gt;. The Witch and her daughters used flame sorcery to challenge the &lt;a href=\"Everlasting%20Dragons\"&gt;ancient dragons&lt;/a&gt;, casting it from &lt;a href=\"catalysts\"&gt;catalysts&lt;/a&gt; just as &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;soul sorceries&lt;/a&gt; were. In the wake of her failed attempt to recreate the First Flame, the Witch of Izalith and some of her daughters were engulfed in the newly formed\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bed%20of%20Chaos\"&gt;Bed of Chaos&lt;/a&gt;. This also resulted in the birth of Pyromancy and all knowledge of flame sorcery has since vanished.\n&lt;a href=\"Quelana%20of%20Izalith\"&gt;Quelana of Izalith&lt;/a&gt;, a Daughter of Chaos, managed to flee the catastrophe created by her mother. Quelana is credited as the \"mother of pyromancy\" and is likely the originator of the primal pyromancies. Quelana teaches her art to a select few students and now resides in &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Salaman%20the%20Master%20Pyromancer\"&gt;Salaman the Master Pyromancer&lt;/a&gt;, a student of Quelana over two-hundred years before the events surrounding the &lt;a href=\"Chosen%20Undead\"&gt;Chosen Undead&lt;/a&gt;, was the inventor of &lt;a href=\"Great%20Fireball\"&gt;Great Fireball&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 his namesake. &lt;a href=\"Carmina\"&gt;Carmina&lt;/a&gt;, the most accomplished pupil of Salaman, is credited with having taken the art in new directions. Carmina's pyromancies focus on actualizing the inner-self, and &lt;a href=\"Power%20Within\"&gt;Power Within&lt;/a&gt; was kept secret for eons due to its dangerous nature.\n&lt;a href=\"Eingyi\"&gt;Eingyi&lt;/a&gt;, an &lt;a href=\"Egg%20Burdened\"&gt;egg-burdened&lt;/a&gt; servant of &lt;a href=\"Quelaag%27s%20Sister\"&gt;The Fair Lady&lt;/a&gt;, was banished from the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt; as a heretic for his perversions of pyromancy. Eingyi's pyromancies are a diversion from the art, illustrating that Pyromancy can be made into something beyond the mere manipulation of fire.\nMost &lt;a href=\"pyromancer\"&gt;pyromancer&lt;/a&gt;s, and many of the rudimentary spells that they wield, seem to originate from the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt;, a remote region where they were driven. Due to its primitive nature, Pyromancy is often shunned by advanced cultures and many sorcerers mock its simplicity."}
{"id": "57209", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57209", "title": "Pyromancy (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Pyromancy\u00a0is a class of &lt;a href=\"Spell%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nPyromancies typically deal &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage and are cast with a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flame%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Pyromancy%20Flame\"&gt;Dark Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0\nThis particular school of magic is unique in that its spells have no requirements to be used, provided the player has at least 3 (4 including the DLC) Attunement Slots (a single attunement slot is also fine as the majority of spells only require one), and a Pyromancy Flame, then every single Pyromancy spell in-game can be used. Due to this, it tends to be used by most players who favor physical damage builds, but who still want to possess some magical spells to either surprise opponents or to merely fill the gap between short and long range combat without having the need to pull out a bow mid combat, thus allowing for a shield to be used in the other hand to block strikes or spells. It is important to note that most of these spells have severe range penalties to compensate for its ease of use, as well as a very small number of uses.\u00a0\nRegardless of it being used primarily by those who don't cast regular spells, leveling up Faith and Intelligence is still a good idea as both will raise the damage of all fire based forms of damage caused by the player, Pyromancies included. As such, a player who focuses on magical attributes will still deal more damage than those who do not. \u00a0\nPlayers may also upgrade their Pyromancy Flame up to a total of ten times by using a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Fire%20Seed\"&gt;Fire Seed&lt;/a&gt; at each stage along with souls to increase their damage output.\nThis school suffers from the same problems that other sources of fire damage suffer from; most armors tend to have higher fire resistances and enemies can also become &lt;a href=\"Waterlogged\"&gt;Waterlogged&lt;/a&gt; due to water present in the terrain or rain. As such this gives them +300 Fire Defense, which greatly reduces the efficacy of pyromancies. Enemies entirely submerged in water, such as the &lt;a href=\"Lizardman\"&gt;Lizardman&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Amana\"&gt;Shrine of Amana&lt;/a&gt;, can be entirely unaffected by most pyromancies for as long as they stay underwater. Finally, most DLC enemies boast greater elemental resistances than enemies in the core game, and enemies within the &lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20the%20Old%20Iron%20King\"&gt;Crown of the Old Iron King&lt;/a&gt; have an even greater resistance to fire damage, with the &lt;a href=\"Fume%20Knight\"&gt;Fume Knight&lt;/a&gt; in particular being especially resistant and also immune to poison/toxic. "}
{"id": "133528", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133528", "title": "Pyromancy (Dark Souls III)", "text": " are a class of &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\", pyromancies are aligned with both &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. To cast a pyromancy, the player requires a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flames%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt; as a catalyst. The player can only attune pyromancies by resting at a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;.\nPyromancies can be purchased from &lt;a href=\"Cornyx%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Cornyx of the Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Karla\"&gt;Karla&lt;/a&gt; with the discovery of Pyromancy Tomes found in the game. Other pyromancies can be found as lootable items on corpses, inside of chests, by &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;soul transposing&lt;/a&gt; various souls with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt;, or as rewards for ranking up in certain &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenants&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "161095", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=161095", "title": "Pyromancy (disambiguation)", "text": ""}
{"id": "3101", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3101", "title": "Pyromancy Flame", "text": "The Pyromancy Flame is a &lt;a href=\"casting%20tool\"&gt;casting tool&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" used for casting &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt;. It is analogous to &lt;a href=\"catalysts\"&gt;catalysts&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"talismans\"&gt;talismans&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt;s.\nUpgrades.\nTo increase the damage output of cast pyromancies, the flame needs to be upgraded through certain NPCs.\nThere are two levels of upgrades for the flame, the regular Pyromancy Flame and the &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flame%20%28ascended%29\"&gt;ascended Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt;. The first one can be upgraded a total of 15 times by &lt;a href=\"Laurentius%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Laurentius&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Quelana%20of%20Izalith\"&gt;Quelana&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Eingyi\"&gt;Eingyi&lt;/a&gt;. After this, players must travel to &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt; to ascend and further upgrade the flame with Quelana. This can be done another five times.\nUpgrading the regular Pyromancy Flame to +15 costs 149,500 &lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;. Upgrading the ascended Pyromancy Flame to +5 costs another 191,000 souls, for a combined total of 340,500 souls to fully upgrade the Pyromancy Flame."}
{"id": "53997", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53997", "title": "Pyromancy Flame (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Pyromancy Flame is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flames\"&gt;pyromancy flame&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound inside a chest after defeating the &lt;a href=\"Flexile%20Sentry\"&gt;Flexile Sentry&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"No-man%27s%20Wharf\"&gt;No-man's Wharf&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Pyromancy Flame is one of only two catalysts in the game that can cast &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; (the other being the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Pyromancy%20Flame\"&gt;Dark Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt;). Initially, it is weaker than the Dark Pyromancy Flame, but when fully upgraded it attains a similar (if not slightly stronger) strength level.\nUnlike the Dark Pyromancy Flame, the Pyromancy Flame does not suffer a damage penalty when in human form, making it more useful for online play. Unlike all other catalysts, the Pyromancy Flame cannot be &lt;a href=\"Infusion\"&gt;infused&lt;/a&gt; with its own element (in this case, &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;).\nThe Pyromancy Flame can also be used as a &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; weapon, though it will deal little damage."}
{"id": "133950", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133950", "title": "Pyromancy Flame (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Pyromancy Flame is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flames%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy flame&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is a magical tool analogous to &lt;a href=\"Staves%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;staves&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt;, the only difference being that it is used to cast &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe standard &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; catalyst, the Pyromancy Flame is the most ideal tool for casting spells to their fullest potential. While it lacks the close-ranged power bonus of the &lt;a href=\"Pyromancer%27s%20Parting%20Flame\"&gt;Pyromancer's Parting Flame&lt;/a&gt; or the ability to reliably attack enemies like the &lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Scar\"&gt;Demon's Scar&lt;/a&gt;, it has no wielding requirements whatsoever and possesses the highest &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of all Pyromancy tools in the game.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced through &lt;a href=\"Cornyx%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Cornyx of the Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "177619", "revid": "27795815", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=177619", "title": "Pyromancy Flame (ascended)", "text": "The ascended Pyromancy Flame is a &lt;a href=\"casting%20tool\"&gt;casting tool&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" used for casting &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt;. It is an upgrade of the regular &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flame\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nThe ascended Pyromancy Flame can be obtained by having &lt;a href=\"Quelana%20of%20Izalith\"&gt;Quelana of Izalith&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification%23Ascension\"&gt;ascend&lt;/a&gt; a regular Pyromancy Flame that was reinforced to +15.\nCharacteristics.\nThe ascended Pyromancy Flame has a greater &lt;a href=\"magic%20adjustment\"&gt;magic adjustment&lt;/a&gt; compared to the regular Pyromancy Flame, effectively increased the damage of all offensive &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; cast with it.\nAlthough the ascended Pyromancy Flame has an &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus\"&gt;intelligence bonus&lt;/a&gt;, its magic adjustment is not affected by the wielder's &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;intelligence&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "52302", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52302", "title": "Pyromancy Flames", "text": "Flames are &lt;a href=\"Casting%20Tools%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;casting tools&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\", and are the only casting tools in the game which are able to cast them. They are unique amongst casting tools for the cheapness of upgrading them, in that only the cost of &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Souls&lt;/a&gt; needed to upgrade them increases; the player will only ever need one &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Seed\"&gt;Fire Seed&lt;/a&gt; per upgrade. However, this is counterbalanced by the fact that Fire Seeds are found sporadically throughout the game."}
{"id": "132072", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132072", "title": "Pyromancy Flames (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Pyromancy Flames are &lt;a href=\"Casting%20Tools%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;casting tools&lt;/a&gt; needed to perform &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pyromancies&lt;/a&gt;, one of the three main &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; types, in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nPyromancy Flames can be upgraded with &lt;a href=\"Upgrade%20Materials%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;titanite&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in the same fashion as\u00a0regular weapons. However, unlike other weapon upgrade methods, Pyromancy Flames can only be upgraded by speaking to &lt;a href=\"Cornyx%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Cornyx of the Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt;, rather than with &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Andre\"&gt;Blacksmith Andre&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs with the Pyromancy Flames of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\", the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the casting tool &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scales&lt;/a&gt; with both &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;. However, unlike the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; Attack Bonus of the previous game, which scaled based on \"total combined\" Intelligence and Faith, the Pyromancy Flames of \"Dark Souls III\" scale based on leveling both &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stats&lt;/a&gt; \"equally\", and lose effectiveness if one stat is favored over the other."}
