{"id": "129207", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=129207", "title": "Quelana", "text": ""}
{"id": "132659", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132659", "title": "Quelana Pyromancy Tome", "text": "The Quelana Pyromancy Tome is a &lt;a href=\"Key%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;key item&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt;.\nFrom the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Ruins%20%28bonfire%29\"&gt;Demon Ruins&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, follow a nearby corridor that leads to a room with two &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Cleric\"&gt;Demon Cleric&lt;/a&gt;s. Drop down and follow a passageway nearby containing several &lt;a href=\"Hound%20Rat\"&gt;Hound Rat&lt;/a&gt;s. Hitting the wall directly opposite to this corridor reveals an &lt;a href=\"Illusory%20Wall%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;illusory wall&lt;/a&gt; (the wall can be identified by a blue glow). The corpse of a giant spider-humanoid lies behind it, along with the tome.\nUsage.\nGiving the tome to &lt;a href=\"Karla\"&gt;Karla&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; unlocks the following &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; for purchase:"}
{"id": "3040", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3040", "title": "Quelana of Izalith", "text": "Quelana of Izalith (\u30af\u30e9\u30fc\u30ca) is a &lt;a href=\"character\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; trainer in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". She is voiced by , who\u00a0also voiced the &lt;a href=\"Darkmoon%20Knightess\"&gt;Darkmoon Knightess&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\nQuelana sits on an island in &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt; directly in front of the entrance to &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Witch%20Quelaag\"&gt;Chaos Witch Quelaag's&lt;/a&gt; lair. The most guaranteed way to encounter her is to level up a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flame\"&gt;Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt; to +10. Being invaded by or summoning someone with a +10 or above flame reportedly spawns her as well.\nPlot.\nUpon meeting Quelana, she offers to teach the player &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt;. After a while, she asks the player to defeat what is left\u00a0of her corrupted sisters, &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Witch%20Quelaag\"&gt;Quelaag&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Daughter%20of%20Chaos\"&gt;Daughter of Chaos&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Bed%20of%20Chaos\"&gt;Bed of Chaos&lt;/a&gt; to free the consumed souls of her mother and sisters. Upon completing her requests, she gifts the player her final pyromancy: &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Tempest\"&gt;Fire Tempest&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nQuelana was originally a \"flame witch\" who used fire sorcery. When Izalith was consumed and the demons infested the city, she fled and became the creator of pyromancy.\u00a0It is unknown whether the knowledge of fire sorcery was forgotten by her or whether she created pyromancy as a safer version of it. Quelana passed on her knowledge to &lt;a href=\"Salaman%20the%20Master%20Pyromancer\"&gt;Salaman&lt;/a&gt;, who in turn passed on his knowledge of pyromancy to the people of the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt;.\nAccording to a developer interview, Quelana and the other &lt;a href=\"Daughters%20of%20Chaos\"&gt;Daughters of Chaos&lt;/a&gt; are a different species, despite appearing similar to humans. Her in-game model may not reflect her \"canon\" appearance, with pale, ash-colored skin, as seen in the opening cutscene and achievement art.\nStrategy.\nQuelana has an unlimited amount of pyromancies at her disposal. She seems to prefer &lt;a href=\"Great%20Fireball\"&gt;Great Fireball&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Tempest\"&gt;Fire Tempest&lt;/a&gt; the most. Both are very powerful if they connect, but have slow start-ups, allowing players to go for the backstab if they are close enough. Quelana may deal high damage but is physically very weak. Quelana is also just as susceptible to poison as the player is; one can choose to attack her and have her wade into the swamp surrounding her, leading to a slow death. Finally, the &lt;a href=\"Infested%20Barbarian\"&gt;Infested Barbarian&lt;/a&gt;s can also damage her heavily should they chase the player to that point."}
{"id": "130935", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130935", "title": "Quella", "text": ""}
{"id": "89613", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=89613", "title": "Quella, God of Dream", "text": " is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nQuella is the god of dreams and her fables talk about a great divine tree that is capable of talking and can access the \"dreamworld\"."}
{"id": "140174", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140174", "title": "Quickstep", "text": "Quickstep is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nSkill commonly found in &lt;a href=\"Daggers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Daggers&lt;/a&gt; and other small weapons. The player performs a quick leap in the direction of movement, facilitating easily getting into enemies' blind spots. It is effective against enemies hiding behind &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Shields&lt;/a&gt; or simply to have better mobility while in combat. Quicksteps have less recovery than rolls, however players will suffer from &lt;a href=\"Instability\"&gt;Instability&lt;/a&gt; immediately after dodge frames.\nOnly consumes 5 &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; (4 &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Manikin%20Claws%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Manikin Claws&lt;/a&gt;' case), which allows its frequent use throughout an encounter to keep adversaries off-balance.\nCertain enemies can be seen to make frequent use of this skill, like &lt;a href=\"Thrall\"&gt;Thrall&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Assassin\"&gt;Hollow Assassin&lt;/a&gt;s, in an attempt to surround the player and allow other foes to enter the battle to attack them from all sides.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nGenerally Quickstep is not overly useful against non-human enemies, as normal rolls will suffice much of the time; as well, rolls do not cost FP, which is a much more limited resource outside of invasions and duels. However, when traversing deep water that forces the player to walk and fat-roll (&lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;), Quickstep can be useful for negating the negative impact on movement, allowing for easier exploration.\nOnline gameplay.\nQuickstep can be useful when facing opponents wielding ultra weapons, as an &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Ultra Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt; will have a very hard time hitting anybody with quick reactions. However, be wary that faster weapons like &lt;a href=\"Curved%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Curved Swords&lt;/a&gt; have wide horizontal swings that can catch players to the side and inflict bonus damage due to &lt;a href=\"Instability\"&gt;Instability&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "98444", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=98444", "title": "Quicksword Rachel", "text": "Quicksword Rachel is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;dark spirit&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0.\nLocation.\n&lt;a href=\"Brume%20Tower\"&gt;Brume Tower&lt;/a&gt;. Invades after beginning to descend the first ladder in the tower full of &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Crawler\"&gt;Ashen Crawler&lt;/a&gt;s.\nGeneral Information.\nShe wears an &lt;a href=\"Alonne%20Knight%20Helm\"&gt;Alonne Knight Helm&lt;/a&gt; with the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Old%20Knight%20Set\"&gt;Old Knight Set&lt;/a&gt; and wields the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Soldier%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Hollow Soldier Shield&lt;/a&gt;. She can also use a lot of different weapon buffs, including &lt;a href=\"Aromatic%20Ooze\"&gt;Aromatic Ooze&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Pine%20Resin%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Gold&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Pine%20Resin\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Charcoal%20Pine%20Resin%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Charcoal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rotten%20Pine%20Resin%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Rotten&lt;/a&gt; resins.\nStrategy.\nWhile her combat tactics are nothing out of the ordinary, she has a considerable amount of HP. Additionally, she'll constantly buff her sword with a random element and she can't be lured into climbing up the ladder used by the player to reach the area where she spawns.\nIt is possible to defeat Rachel by igniting one of the oil-filled containers and then kiting her around it, causing her to constantly take &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage until she dies."}
{"id": "143730", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143730", "title": "Quill Dart", "text": "Quill Dart is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nWhen performed, the wielder leaps into the air and throws the four blades in the left hand in a fan-shaped pattern. Each dart will inflict damage equal to 30% of the weapon's physical attack rating, and 35% of any elemental damage in the case of an elemental &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infusion&lt;/a&gt;. The direction of the leap can be controlled by the wielder.\nUpon landing, performing a strong attack will cause the wielder to charge forth with the sword, inflicting 120% of the weapon's attack rating to any target it hits.\nThe dart attack costs 7 &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt;, or 6 FP with the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Ring\"&gt;Farron Ring&lt;/a&gt; equipped. The follow-up strong thrust costs 8 FP, or 6 FP with the Farron Ring equipped.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nThe individual darts do not inflict a meaningful amount of damage, so this skill is not a very efficient use of FP for damage purposes. However, the darts can be used to draw aggro from faraway enemies without expending throwables like &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Knife%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Throwing Knives&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnline gameplay.\nBecause of the wide spread of the dart attack, one should not expect to hit a target with more than one dart while performing this skill. However, due to its low cost, this skill can be handy for harassing an opponent if a &lt;a href=\"Simple%20Gem\"&gt;Simple&lt;/a&gt; infusion is utilized for FP recovery.\nThe strong follow-up is very handy for punishing foes that attempt to dodge the darts and then close the distance on what they presume is a vulnerable target, particularly as the weapon's thrust damage can inflict &lt;a href=\"Counter%20Attack\"&gt;counter damage&lt;/a&gt;. It has strong forward momentum, and can be used to turn the tables on an overconfident opponent. However, beware that it possesses no &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; and thus can be punished in return if not used wisely.\nIt is worthwhile to note that &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; buildup can be inflicted with the darts should the weapon be buffed. This means that by using a &lt;a href=\"Rotten%20Pine%20Resin%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Rotten Pine Resin&lt;/a&gt;, it is possible to safely inflict &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; safely from long range."}
