{"id": "98818", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=98818", "title": "Rampart Golem Set", "text": "The Rampart Golem Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in .\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Rampart%20Golem\"&gt;Rampart Golem&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Eleum%20Loyce\"&gt;Frozen Eleum Loyce&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Rampart Golem Set offers remarkable &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; and defenses for its &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, as well as moderate resistances. It is one of the few heavy armor sets to offer a resistance to &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;curses&lt;/a&gt;, but no &lt;a href=\"Petrification%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;petrification&lt;/a&gt; resistance. \nLike most heavy armor sets, it has a weakness against &lt;a href=\"strike\"&gt;strike&lt;/a&gt; attacks, but possesses a significant resistance to &lt;a href=\"slash\"&gt;slash&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"thrust\"&gt;thrust&lt;/a&gt; attacks.\nIt is interesting to note that it has a very marginal weakness to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt;, but is also marginally-more robust against &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt;. It has rather high defenses against &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage, making it a balanced set overall.\nUpgrades.\nUpgrades with &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt;, up to +5."}
{"id": "99994", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=99994", "title": "Rampart Golem Shield", "text": "The Rampart Golem Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nA medium-&lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; that has stats comparable to that of the &lt;a href=\"Rebel%27s%20Greatshield\"&gt;Rebel's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, while weighing far less, and even besting some of its &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; defenses (&lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;dark&lt;/a&gt;).\nWhile this shield has excellent all-around defences, it is quite heavy, and has the lowest &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; and one of the lowest physical defence of all shields in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\", making it a very bad choice for PvE.\nThis shield is far more useful in short &lt;a href=\"PvP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; engagement, being able to protect against any &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; effectively. Caution should be used though, as a &lt;a href=\"Corrosive%20Urn\"&gt;Corrosive Urn&lt;/a&gt; will break it in one hit, even when using the &lt;a href=\"Bracing%20Knuckle%20Ring\"&gt;Bracing Knuckle Ring&lt;/a&gt;+2, and it will become useless.\nLike the Rebel's Greatshield's saving grace, infusing this with any elemental type (&lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt;, lightning, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;, or dark) once the shield is at maximum &lt;a href=\"reinforcement\"&gt;reinforcement&lt;/a&gt; (+10) will grant the shield a 100% reduction to the element chosen."}
