{"id": "140171", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140171", "title": "Rapid Fire", "text": "Rapid Fire is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nUpon holding down the Left Strong Attack button ( / ) button, the player enters a stance, readying the bow. Firing a type of &lt;a href=\"Ammunition%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;arrow&lt;/a&gt; will allow them to unleash them at an extremely fast rate, albeit dealing 40% less damage per arrow.\nConsumes 4 &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; for each arrow fired, or 3 with the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Ring\"&gt;Farron Ring&lt;/a&gt; equipped.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nNot very useful skill overall as each arrow only deals about one third of normal damage. Since enemies tend to start moving once the first arrow connects, subsequent shots can potentially miss if locking-on to them. Still, some players may find it useful to keep certain enemies at bay.\nOnline gameplay.\nThis skill can be tricky to use in battle, however it shines in invasions in areas with ladders such as the &lt;a href=\"Profaned%20Capital\"&gt;Profaned Capital&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Archives\"&gt;Grand Archives&lt;/a&gt;, as the arrows will still do tremendous stamina damage to players attempting to climb the ladder. If one can catch an opponent attempting to climb up or down a ladder, Rapid Fire can very quickly knock them off, causing them to lose their grip and take fall damage, and leaving them vulnerable to bonus &lt;a href=\"Instability\"&gt;Instability&lt;/a&gt; damage while getting up."}
{"id": "4546", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4546", "title": "Rapier", "text": "The Rapier is a &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Rapier, like other thrusting swords, can attack from behind a &lt;a href=\"Shields\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, giving an advantage for defensive players, it's also a fast weapon that uses little &lt;a href=\"stamina\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; from the player, allowing longer combos.\nIt's made exclusively of &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28Damage%20Type%29\"&gt;thrusting&lt;/a&gt; attacks, being perfect for fights in small corridors, and has a higher critical rate than most swords, resulting in more powerful &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte\"&gt;ripostes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;s. The thrust attacks have a very small vertical hitbox, which may result in having a hard time with hitting smaller enemies like &lt;a href=\"Slime\"&gt;Slime&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Leech\"&gt;Giant Leech&lt;/a&gt;es.\nAlthough the in-game stat menus show Rapier having a 110 critical rate, the Rapier benefits from a higher &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;motion value&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstabs&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte\"&gt;Ripostes&lt;/a&gt; making it deal higher damage on these critical attacks like all of the other Thrusting Swords. \nDue to its &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt; attack type, it is the perfect weapon to pair with &lt;a href=\"Leo%20Ring\"&gt;Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt; for a boost to counter damage. \nIts most notable weakness is its relatively low damage with its normal attacks, most notably against &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;es, as they usually cannot be riposted or backstabbed, making the Rapier's true advantage more specific for &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; battles.\nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
