{"id": "130286", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130286", "title": "Red Eye Orb (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Red Eye Orb is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe player must defeat a &lt;a href=\"Darkwraith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Darkwraith&lt;/a&gt; located at the bottom of a tower in the &lt;a href=\"High%20Wall%20of%20Lothric\"&gt;High Wall of Lothric&lt;/a&gt; after receiving the &lt;a href=\"Lift%20Chamber%20Key\"&gt;Lift Chamber Key&lt;/a&gt; provided by &lt;a href=\"Ringfinger%20Leonhard\"&gt;Ringfinger Leonhard&lt;/a&gt; once they have obtained a &lt;a href=\"Pale%20Tongue\"&gt;Pale Tongue&lt;/a&gt;.\nFrom the &lt;a href=\"High%20Wall%20of%20Lothric%23Bonfires\"&gt;Tower on the Wall&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, make way to the bottom of the tower and unlock the barred door with the key given by Leonhard. Ride the lift down and fight the Darkwraith there. The item will be automatically added to the player's inventory once he dies.\nUsage.\nUsing this infinite consumable will allow a player to invade another player's world as a dark spirit. A Host of Embers can only be invaded in this manner if the boss for the area is still alive. Unlike in the first \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", usage of this item is not restricted to any specific &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;, and victory requirements will vary depending on the covenant that the player has pledged themselves to.\nInvasion ranges can also vary depending on covenant status. In all cases, invasion range is based on the player's Soul Level."}
{"id": "134096", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134096", "title": "Red Hilted Halberd", "text": "The Red Hilted Halberd is a &lt;a href=\"Halberds%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;'s sewers. The &lt;a href=\"Grave%20Key\"&gt;Grave Key&lt;/a&gt; is required to unlock the gate in the sewage system that gives access to this area. It is found at the center of the room where the player is attacked by &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Skeletons&lt;/a&gt; for the first time.\nCharacteristics.\nA favorite in &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, the Red Hilted Halberd can be a very strong polearm in the right hands.\nUtilizing the thrusting halberd moveset, the Red Hilted Halberd is generally incapable of taking advantage of &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; except when performing a two-handed strong attack, which has a long wind-up and leaves the wielder wide open if it misses. Compared to the normal &lt;a href=\"Halberd%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt;, it performs better with physical &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infusions&lt;/a&gt; but is weaker than its cousin when it comes to elemental infusions.\nWhat makes this weapon useful, however, is that it is the only halberd in the game with &lt;a href=\"Perseverance%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Perseverance&lt;/a&gt;, which grants the wielder passive &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; while also reducing any incoming damage. This means that unlike most other halberds, the Red Hilted Halberd has an option to stand its ground and fight enemies head-on if they manage to get inside of the weapon's reach.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
