{"id": "58740", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=58740", "title": "Red Rust Shield", "text": "The Red Rust Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Vengarl%20of%20Forossa\"&gt;Vengarl of Forossa&lt;/a&gt; for 4,500 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Shaded%20Woods\"&gt;Shaded Woods&lt;/a&gt; along with the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Rust%20Sword\"&gt;Red Rust Sword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Red%20Rust%20Scimitar\"&gt;Red Rust Scimitar&lt;/a&gt; after his body has been defeated.\nCharacteristics.\nWhen looking at the stats of the Red Rust Shield, one might think this is a rather worthless shield, and to a certain point it is, as it provides little to no elemental, &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Petrification%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Petrification&lt;/a&gt; defenses and its &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; is average at best. It also doesn't help that this shield can only be upgraded with &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever, this shield draws a comparison to the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Knight%20Greatshield\"&gt;Old Knight Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, as it has very high &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; resistances for less than half its &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; and with much more &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;. As such, it can be used effectively in areas where poison and bleed damage are a recurring hazards, such as &lt;a href=\"Huntsman%27s%20Copse\"&gt;Huntsman's Copse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Earthen%20Peak\"&gt;Earthen Peak&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "57193", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57193", "title": "Red Rust Sword", "text": "The\u00a0Red Rust Sword\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThis weapon can be obtained from &lt;a href=\"Vengarl%20of%20Forossa\"&gt;Vengarl of Forossa&lt;/a&gt; after defeating his body at the &lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Cove%20Tseldora\"&gt;Brightstone Cove Tseldora&lt;/a&gt; primal bonfire for 7,000 souls.\nCharacteristics.\nWhat makes the Red Rust Sword unique is that its entire moveset is that of an &lt;a href=\"Axes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt;, (apparently due to its weight as mentioned in its description)."}
{"id": "6737", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6737", "title": "Red Sign Soapstone", "text": "The Red Sign Soapstone is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound at the very top of the stairs in the central tower in the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;, guarded by some &lt;a href=\"Crow%20Demon\"&gt;Crow Demon&lt;/a&gt;s.\nGeneral information.\nUsing the Red Sign Soapstone causes the player to place a red summon sign on the ground. Players that see the sign will be able to summon the user to their world as a &lt;a href=\"Phantom%23Red%20Phantoms\"&gt;red phantom&lt;/a&gt; to duel for &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20Mechanic\"&gt;humanity&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;. As with red phantom invasions, the winner is rewarded with one humanity, as well as a number of souls dependent on the defeated player's soul level.\nPlayers must be unhollowed in order to place the Red Sign Soapstone or to summon a player that has placed the soapstone. Player placing soapstone may be summoned by players that are within range and (- (10 +10% of the placing player's level), or any level higher (for example, a level 100 player can be summoned by any player that is level 80 or higher); in addition, the host does not need the area boss to be alive to summon. People who share similar soul levels have a higher priority in match-making.\nThose wishing to summon a red sign soapstone user must not have placed their own red sign soapstone. Placing of your own sign prevents you from seeing other's signs. You may summon a player (- (10 -10% of the placing player's level), or any level lower (for example, a level 100 player can summon any player level 1 - 122).\nRed phantoms summoned through Red Sign Soapstones cannot be &lt;a href=\"indicted\"&gt;indicted&lt;/a&gt; if they kill the host."}
