{"id": "62033", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=62033", "title": "Reeve's Greatshield", "text": "Reeve's Greatshield\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nNotes.\nAlong with the &lt;a href=\"Orma%27s%20Greatshield\"&gt;Orma's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, and parts of the &lt;a href=\"Imperious%20Set\"&gt;Imperious Set&lt;/a&gt;, Reeve's Greatshield is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Imperious%20Knight\"&gt;Imperious Knight&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Crypt\"&gt;Undead Crypt&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn par with &lt;a href=\"Orma%27s%20Greatshield\"&gt;Orma's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, Reeve's Greatshield has the second highest damage output among all &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt; in the game at 200 (300 when maxed), behind &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Greatshield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Havel's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, at 253 (380 when maxed?).\nAs a pair with &lt;a href=\"Orma%27s%20Greatshield\"&gt;Orma's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, Orma's and Reeve's Greatshields are the only shields in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\" that can be &lt;a href=\"power-stance\"&gt;power-stance&lt;/a&gt;d. You can Power Stance with this and &lt;a href=\"Orma%27s%20Greatshield\"&gt;Orma's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt; provided you have 50 &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;. Reeve's must be in the right-hand and Orma's must be in the left-hand.\nWhen power-stanced with &lt;a href=\"Orma%27s%20Greatshield\"&gt;Orma's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, pressing LB will initiate a unique attack that the player character will clench the two interlocking greatshields to the front like a pair of pincers to crush enemies in between, dealing &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;strike&lt;/a&gt; damage from both shields with very heavy &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; damage. This move shares the same animation as the &lt;a href=\"Imperious%20Knight\"&gt;Imperious Knight&lt;/a&gt;'s shield pincer attacks. Pressing LT will result in the same pincer attack, with higher stamina usage and damage rating. The LB pincer attacks have very high stamina usage at about 70 per use, and the LT variant about 90.\nSome players reported that the LB pincer attack has a yet undetermined time frame by which enemy strikes from an angle to both sides will be deflected, but attacks from the center front are not affected.\nUnlike the &lt;a href=\"Imperious%20Knight\"&gt;Imperious Knight&lt;/a&gt;s, the \"clenched shields\" state at the end of the pincer attack cannot be prolonged, and does not count as blocking.\nOwing to high inherent damage rating and unique Power Stance attack that delivers damage from both shields at once, the Orma's &amp; Reeve's Greatshield pairing might be the only shields in \"Dark Souls II\" that can be counted as a legit weapon.\nWhen upgraded and with the right build, this shield pairing can make short work of most bosses and lightly armored players while providing solid defense; its main drawback lies in the initial long windup of its first pincer attack (same windup time as a shield bash), and its almost non-existent range means players will have a hard time following up on an attack after knocking back an enemy due to sheer poise damage."}
