{"id": "4619", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4619", "title": "Repair", "text": "Repair (\u4fee\u5fa9) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nRepairs only equipped &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; by 150 &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; points. Exception: It won't repair &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;crystal&lt;/a&gt; weapons, but it will repair the equipment parts of &lt;a href=\"Crystalline%20Set\"&gt;Crystalline Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nWhile it is possible to use Repair simply to save cost of regular &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; repairs, it is more useful when used to extend the life of fragile weapons (such as the &lt;a href=\"Washing%20Pole\"&gt;Washing Pole&lt;/a&gt;) or weapons that use durability for special abilities (such as the &lt;a href=\"Drake%20Sword\"&gt;Drake Sword&lt;/a&gt;). Due to its single use, it is possible to have the spell equipped in the &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;attunement&lt;/a&gt; slot granted by a &lt;a href=\"Darkmoon%20Seance%20Ring\"&gt;Darkmoon Seance Ring&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"White%20Seance%20Ring\"&gt;White Seance Ring&lt;/a&gt;, casting the spell and removing the ring (and instead, equipping another desired ring) effectively gives the player a free repair at no expense.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "73940", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=73940", "title": "Repair (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Repair is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nSimilarly to its \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"Repair\"&gt;counterpart&lt;/a&gt;, this sorcery will restore &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; to damaged &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;. Casting this will cause all gear to gain 20 durability points back. Gear will not be repaired if it is completely broken.\nIt will repair equipped armor, &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;rings&lt;/a&gt;, and currently active weapons, but has no effect on weapons in inactive slots. This makes this spell less effective for players looking to maintain large quantities of weapons and &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt;, as a &lt;a href=\"Casting%20Tools%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;casting tool&lt;/a&gt; always has to be active while casting. This can be counteracted by using items like &lt;a href=\"Amber%20Herb\"&gt;Amber Herb&lt;/a&gt;s or &lt;a href=\"Rouge%20Water\"&gt;Rouge Water&lt;/a&gt; to restore casts. Wearing a &lt;a href=\"Bracing%20Knuckle%20Ring\"&gt;Bracing Knuckle Ring&lt;/a&gt; can make Repair restore up to 40 effective durability, further improving its usefulness.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "133909", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133909", "title": "Repair (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Repair (\u4fee\u7406) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Orbeck%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Orbeck of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; for 2,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once he has been given the &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Scroll\"&gt;Golden Scroll&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nRestores 50 &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; to all currently equipped &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;, including weapons not currently being wielded. This applies to equipment that has been completely broken as well (e.g., has 0 durability).\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "6707", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6707", "title": "Repair Powder", "text": "Repair Powder is a &lt;a href=\"restorative%20item\"&gt;restorative item&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nRestores up to 100 points of &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; for right hand &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;. Weapons cannot be &lt;a href=\"repair\"&gt;repair&lt;/a&gt;ed past their maximum durability.\nRepair Powder cannot be used on &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Crystal&lt;/a&gt; weapons.\nOverview.\nRepairing through &lt;a href=\"blacksmiths\"&gt;blacksmiths&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Repairbox\"&gt;Repairbox&lt;/a&gt; is generally more cost-efficient for most weapons, so Repair Powder is mainly useful when using an extremely brittle weapon like the &lt;a href=\"Washing%20Pole\"&gt;Washing Pole&lt;/a&gt; or weapons that sacrifice durability for special attacks, such as &lt;a href=\"Grant\"&gt;Grant&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20King%20Greataxe\"&gt;Dragon King Greataxe&lt;/a&gt;, allowing them to be used multiple times without having to travel to a blacksmith or rest at a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;."}
