{"id": "10411", "revid": "341640", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10411", "title": "Resonance Ring", "text": "Resonance Rings are a gameplay mechanic in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nGeneral information.\nResonance Rings appear in an area where another player has recently used a miracle. It is possible to find multiple Resonance Rings at once. Resonance rings appear as small white rings fixed slightly above the ground. When the player is close to one, the power of certain &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Miracles&lt;/a&gt; are boosted. When the player is close enough so that their miracles can receive a boost, a white circle will appear over the selected miracle.\nThe effect of resonance rings does stack and is divided in four levels; standing next to three up to five resonance rings results in Double Synergy, to six up to nine rings results in Triple Synergy and to ten or more results in Quadruple Synergy. Each level generally multiplies the effect of ordinary Synergy; a Double Synergy doubles the effect, a Triple Synergy triples it and a Quadruple Synergy quadruples it. Wearing the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20the%20Sun%20Princess\"&gt;Ring of the Sun Princess&lt;/a&gt; grants a boost to miracles equivalent to that of being close to a resonance ring. The effects of the Ring of the Sun Princess stack with resonance rings, so standing next to one Resonance Ring with the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20the%20Sun%20Princess\"&gt;Ring of the Sun Princess&lt;/a&gt; equipped results in a Double Synergy, to three up to five resonance rings results in a Triple Synergy and to six or more results in a Quadruple Synergy.\nSee &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20Synergy\"&gt;Miracle Synergy&lt;/a&gt; for more information."}
{"id": "171867", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=171867", "title": "Resonance ring", "text": ""}
{"id": "58029", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=58029", "title": "Resonant Flesh", "text": "Resonant Flesh is a &lt;a href=\"Hexes\"&gt;hex&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Felkin%20the%20Outcast\"&gt;Felkin the Outcast&lt;/a&gt; for 3,400 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral Information.\nWhen cast, Resonant Flesh boosts the player's maximum &lt;a href=\"HP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; in exchange for up to 2,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;. The HP gained depends on the souls held by the caster at the time of casting. Casting the spell with little to no souls results in a small gain to HP alternatively, casting it with 2,000 souls or more results in a gain of about 20% of the player's total HP. This spell will last 54 seconds when spiced down to 10 Faith all the way up to 180 seconds at 30 Faith where the duration scaling is capped.\nThe high HP increase, long duration and relatively low requirements of Resonant Flesh makes it a very useful spell for all players, regardless of their &lt;a href=\"vigor\"&gt;vigor&lt;/a&gt;. Players with low HP can counteract this weakness with Resonant Flesh while players with high HP can use it to become considerably more durable than they were before. Resonant Flesh only increases the HP cap, and does not add to the player's current HP. This means that any healing should be done after casting Resonant Flesh to conserve healing items.\nThe effects of the spell will stack multiplicatively with other items or equipment that boost the player's HP, such as the &lt;a href=\"Life%20Ring\"&gt;Life Ring&lt;/a&gt; variants.\nAttunement Milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:\nDuration Scaling Information.\nDuration values are listed in seconds. Base duration of this spell only depends on Faith. Base duration shown as well as values with the &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest&lt;/a&gt; variants applied and pieces of &lt;a href=\"Northwarder%20Set\"&gt;Northwarder Set&lt;/a&gt; applied. "}
