{"id": "68903", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=68903", "title": "Rhoy the Explorer", "text": "Rhoy the Explorer is a &lt;a href=\"dark%20spirit\"&gt;dark spirit&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nRhoy will invade offline players in the &lt;a href=\"Grave%20of%20Saints\"&gt;Grave of Saints&lt;/a&gt;, when the player approaches the ladder leading to the top levels of the area.\nIt is important to note that Rhoy will not spawn unless the player is offline and not part of the &lt;a href=\"Rat%20King%20%28covenant%29\"&gt;Rat King covenant&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nRhoy wears a full &lt;a href=\"Aurous%27%20Set%20%28transparent%29\"&gt;Aurous' Set (transparent)&lt;/a&gt;, as well as the &lt;a href=\"Illusory%20Ring%20of%20a%20Conqueror\"&gt;Illusory Ring of a Conqueror&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Illusory%20Ring%20of%20the%20Exalted\"&gt;Illusory Ring of the Exalted&lt;/a&gt; pair. He wields an invisible &lt;a href=\"Shotel%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Shotel&lt;/a&gt; +5 and &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Crossbow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Heavy Crossbow&lt;/a&gt; +5. The final result is that Rhoy looks naked, when he is in fact fully equipped.\nRhoy is actually a very average Phantom, and poses no threat in and of himself. Nonetheless beware of the shield-ignoring ability of his weapon. The real danger of the battle are the rats that will ambush the player: these will drop from the ceiling behind the player, and attack them from behind unexpectedly. They can be turned against Rhoy if a &lt;a href=\"Seed%20of%20a%20Giant%20Tree\"&gt;Seed of a Giant Tree&lt;/a&gt; is used.\nFarming.\nRhoy is notable for being very easily farmed. He will spawn up to 15 times per game/&lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20Ascetic\"&gt;Bonfire Ascetic&lt;/a&gt;. This can be useful for players trying to max out their &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20Blue\"&gt;Way of Blue&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Company%20of%20Champions\"&gt;Company of Champions&lt;/a&gt; covenants. Rhoy also has a 100% chance of dropping an &lt;a href=\"Awestone\"&gt;Awestone&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0if the player is a member of the Company of Champions. Players should start to the &lt;a href=\"Grave%20Entrance\"&gt;Grave Entrance&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. From there, it is \"recommended\" to stay at the top level until all 5 rats have dropped and been killed, especially after &lt;a href=\"NG%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;NG&lt;/a&gt;. Once done, players should jump down the ladder, and immediately climb it. This will trigger Rhoy's invasion.\nAfter about 15 cycles, Rhoy will stop spawning, and will require a Bonfire Ascetic. The bonfire this should be used is \"not\" the current Grave Entrance bonfire, but rather the first bonfire of the area: &lt;a href=\"Harval%27s%20Resting%20Place\"&gt;Harval's Resting Place&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn , Rhoy will invade only once in NG, but he will invade infinitely if the Bonfire Intensity is 2 or higher and the player is in the Company of Champions covenant. He also has a chance to drop Awestones as normal drops, effectively rewarding 2 Awestones for a lucky kill.\nA safe way to kill him is to activate the drawbridge on the second floor and lure him there to then push him down to the bottomless pit below: this will make his drop unavailable drop (the &lt;a href=\"Awestone\"&gt;Awestone&lt;/a&gt; that is always dropped will be added to the player's inventory regardless).\nA comfortable and quick farm method rather than to run around the top floor until all the rats are dead and then kill him by the bon fire to reset (average lap 2:30) is starting from the grave entrance bonfire to drop down the ladder with out climbing it, stand hugging the base of the ladder for about one second, use this time to enchant if needed, you will get the message he has invaded, turn the corner and kill the three rats, two in the lower hole and the one above quickly. you should still have about 2 seconds to spare and you will see him climbing down the ladder. you can now fight him in that area with out the worry of rats."}
{"id": "129526", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=129526", "title": "Ricard", "text": ""}
{"id": "140230", "revid": "28000958", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140230", "title": "Ricard's Lunge and Press", "text": "Ricard's Lunge and Press is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThe player makes a sudden stop and quickly starts performing three-stabbing attacks one after another, culminating with a strong lunge.\nThe strong attack button will add another set of stabs before the final lunge.\nUsage.\nCampaign.\nVery useful skill in most situations against individual enemies, although it may also have its uses against crowds.\nOnline gameplay.\nVery useful against human opponents as this skill allows the player to stun-lock them, &lt;a href=\"Guard%20Break\"&gt;break their guards&lt;/a&gt; and deal huge amounts of damage in one swift attack, as long as the player is able to connect the initial stab."}
{"id": "4666", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4666", "title": "Ricard's Rapier", "text": "Ricard's Rapier is a &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Prince%20Ricard\"&gt;Undead Prince Ricard&lt;/a&gt; on the high roof area of &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nRicard's Rapier's\u00a0strong attack\u00a0deals several weak hits in very quick succession. This makes Ricard's Rapier one of the better weapons to use with a &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;weapon buff&lt;/a&gt; build (in PvE), as enchantments such as &lt;a href=\"Darkmoon%20Blade\"&gt;Darkmoon Blade&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Magic%20Weapon\"&gt;Crystal Magic Weapon&lt;/a&gt; add a fixed amount of damage to every hit.\nAlthough the in-game stat menus show the Ricard's Rapier having a 100 critical rate, this weapon benefits from a higher &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;motion value&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstabs&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte\"&gt;Ripostes&lt;/a&gt; making it deal higher damage on these critical attacks like all of the other Thrusting Swords.\nRicard's Rapier deals slightly inferior damage compared to the other thrusting swords.\nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "52408", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52408", "title": "Ricard's Rapier (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Ricard's Rapier is a &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nRicard's Rapier is one of the best &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;thrusting swords&lt;/a&gt; available, due to having great &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Scaling%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"critical\"&gt;critical&lt;/a&gt; damage, and low &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;.\nBecause of its low &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement, one can &lt;a href=\"power%20stance\"&gt;power stance&lt;/a&gt; Ricard's Rapier with as little as 12 Strength and still retain an immense damage output, provided the player has a high amount of Dexterity.\nThe rapier's strong attack ( / ) delivers three quick blows followed by a fourth delayed thrust that deals mild damage and does heavy &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; damage. This is very hard to land properly on players, as it is delayed and somewhat easily telegraphed.\nDue to its low poise damage and low reach for a thrusting weapon, this weapon may be considered undesirable for &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;. However, it is exceptional\u00a0for PvE when power stanced.\nWhen fully upgraded, it will require\u00a0at least 38 Dexterity before\u00a0it will out-damage the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Rapier%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Rapier&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0It is wise to stock up on &lt;a href=\"Repair%20Powder%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Repair Powder&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0before using this weapon,\u00a0as the heavy attack will consume a great deal of the weapon's &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;.\nDue to its high attack rate, Ricard's Rapier is very effective at &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"buildup\"&gt;buildup&lt;/a&gt;s such as &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "133958", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133958", "title": "Ricard's Rapier (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Ricard's Rapier is a &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by the &lt;a href=\"Rapier%20Champion\"&gt;Rapier Champion&lt;/a&gt; the first time he is summoned and defeated by the player in &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;, before reaching the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Belfry\"&gt;Great Belfry&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nRicard's Rapier has the same &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; as the standard &lt;a href=\"Rapier%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Rapier&lt;/a&gt;, but what makes this weapon unique is its &lt;a href=\"weapon%20art\"&gt;weapon art&lt;/a&gt;. The weapon art starts off with a stance, then the player executes several pokes before ending it with a stronger thrust. Before the finishing attack, performing a strong attack will follow up the weapon art with a few more pokes before ending it with the thrust. Due to it being a thrusting weapon, Ricard's Rapier can benefit from the &lt;a href=\"Leo%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
