{"id": "44682", "revid": "56088513", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44682", "title": "Ring of Blades", "text": "The Ring of Blades is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEffect.\nIncreases physical damage by 20/35/50 points for the base, +1, and +2 versions respectively. \nIf a weapon has an elemental infusion, the damage bonus is reduced by 50%. It is instead reduced by 20% if the elemental infusion matches the weapon's natural element. Uninfused elemental weapons gain the full benefit, but the ring will not add physical damage to weapons that deal no physical damage at all (such as the &lt;a href=\"Moonlight%20Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Moonlight Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;)."}
{"id": "24075", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24075", "title": "Ring of Blind Ghosts", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; which was &lt;a href=\"Removed%20Content\"&gt;removed&lt;/a&gt; from the final release of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nAs the description states, the Ring of Blind Ghosts was intended to prevent the wearer from being attacked by &lt;a href=\"Ghost\"&gt;Ghost&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Banshee\"&gt;Banshee&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"New%20Londo%20Ruins\"&gt;New Londo Ruins&lt;/a&gt;. It was also connected to &lt;a href=\"Ingward\"&gt;Ingward&lt;/a&gt;, however, as it was removed from the game before release, it is unknown how the player would have obtained it normally."}
{"id": "24077", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24077", "title": "Ring of Condemnation", "text": "The Ring of Condemnation is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; which was &lt;a href=\"Removed%20Content\"&gt;removed&lt;/a&gt; from the final release of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nAs the description states, the Ring of Condemnation was intended to act like the &lt;a href=\"Karmic%20Justice\"&gt;Karmic Justice&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt;, in that it would automatically perform a &lt;a href=\"counter-attack\"&gt;counter-attack&lt;/a&gt; on an assailant after the wearer sustained constant damage.\nIt was also intended to be an item which was obtained from a &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; devoted to &lt;a href=\"Velka%2C%20Goddess%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Velka, Goddess of Sin&lt;/a&gt;. However, both the ring and the covenant were removed from the game before release."}
{"id": "24073", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24073", "title": "Ring of Displacement", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; which was &lt;a href=\"Removed%20Content\"&gt;removed&lt;/a&gt; from the final release of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nAs the description states, the Ring of Displacement was intended to prevent the wearer from taking damage. However, in order to balance this, it had a fixed chance of breaking whilst it was worn. As it was removed from the game before release, it is unknown how the player would have obtained it normally."}
{"id": "132775", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132775", "title": "Ring of Favor", "text": "The Ring of Favor is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "2735", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2735", "title": "Ring of Favor and Protection", "text": "The Ring of Favor and Protection is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nWhen worn, the Ring of Favor and Protection increases the player's maximum &lt;a href=\"Health\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%29%23Stamina\"&gt;Stamina&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Equip%20Load\"&gt;equipment load&lt;/a&gt; by 20%. The item is destroyed, however, if it is ever removed.\nAfter the player reaches 40 &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt;, wearing the Ring of Favor and Protection is the only way to further increase maximum Stamina.\nOverview.\nThis ring is useful for players that are absolutely sure that they would never require another ring slot, or if they temporarily require a boost in vitality and stamina. However, removing the ring (and thus breaking it) is ill-advised since only two of them can be obtained per playthrough.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, many builds rely on the Ring of Favor and Protection to don heavier armor without sacrificing the fast roll, and the extra HP\u2014essentially granting players the equivalent of extra soul levels without actually leveling up. Players are conversely limiting the diversity of rings they can use, however. The &lt;a href=\"Hornet%20Ring\"&gt;Hornet Ring&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Havel's Ring&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Bellowing%20Dragoncrest%20Ring\"&gt;Bellowing Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt; are all examples of rings that players could otherwise use had they not equipped the Ring of Favor and Protection with the intent of not breaking it."}
{"id": "3050", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3050", "title": "Ring of Fog", "text": "The Ring of Fog is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral Information.\nWearers of this ring become transparent, although they are still visible. aggro from a shorter range, and lose interest after chasing players for a shorter distance. In terms of &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, players can use the ring in certain environments to remain hidden from their opponent. However, as they can still be locked on to, the usefulness of the ring diminishes severely if discovered by the enemy. \nIn PvE this ring can be used to run quickly through areas and can even trivialize some boss fights when used in conjunction with &lt;a href=\"Slumbering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring\"&gt;Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;. When using this ring combo the dogs in &lt;a href=\"Capra%20Demon\"&gt;Capra Demon's&lt;/a&gt; fight will never agro if the player does not go beyond a certain point in the boss area. This is also true of &lt;a href=\"Gravelord%20Nito\"&gt;Gravelord Nito's&lt;/a&gt; skeletons if the player stays near the entrance of the area and allows Nito to walk to them. \nHistory.\nPrior to &lt;a href=\"Patch%20Information%231.04\"&gt;Patch 1.04&lt;/a&gt;, the Ring of Fog also prevented players from locking onto users in PvP. This was considered overpowered by many and From Software took this ability out of the game for balancing."}
{"id": "45812", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45812", "title": "Ring of Giants", "text": "The\u00a0Ring of Giants\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "64312", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=64312", "title": "Ring of Knowledge", "text": "The Ring of Knowledge is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt; for 28,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nThe Ring of Knowledge grants +5 points to the &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; stat. Note that this does\u00a0not\u00a0work to obtain level requirements to talk to other characters."}
