{"id": "4581", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4581", "title": "Ring of Sacrifice", "text": "The Ring of Sacrifice is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", it allows &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; to be retained upon &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral information.\nUpon death the wearer will retain any &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20%28gameplay%20mechanic%29\"&gt;humanity&lt;/a&gt; that they were carrying with them (as well as retaining unhollowed form), but the ring itself will break. Dying with a Ring of Sacrifice equipped will show the message \"Ring Revival\" after the usual \"You Died\" message and will not result in the player leaving a &lt;a href=\"bloodstain\"&gt;bloodstain&lt;/a&gt;. Should a player with an uncollected bloodstain die while having a Ring of Sacrifice equipped, their bloodstain will not be lost.\nThe only death that this ring cannot nullify is from &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt;. Equipping this ring while dying from Curse will count as a normal death. The ring, however, will not break in this process. An upgraded version of this ring called the &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Ring%20of%20Sacrifice\"&gt;Rare Ring of Sacrifice&lt;/a&gt;, can save you from Curse, as well as curing the status.\nOverview.\nThe Ring of Sacrifice acts as an extra life, of sorts. It can be useful to the player if they are taking on a tough enemy for the first time or if there is a high risk that the player may die before they are able to retrieve a very valuable bloodstain. Because the player will not leave a bloodstain upon death with this ring, it can make traversing a difficult area less risky."}
{"id": "130363", "revid": "1188343", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130363", "title": "Ring of Sacrifice (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Ring of Sacrifice is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEffect.\nThe player will lose no &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; upon &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;, but the ring itself will break and be removed from their inventory afterward. If the player dies by being &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;cursed&lt;/a&gt;, the ring will fail to activate, causing all the usual effects of death and keeping the ring intact."}
{"id": "48262", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48262", "title": "Ring of Soul Protection", "text": "The Ring of Soul Protection\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nWhile worn, the player will lose nothing if they die and will survive a single &lt;a href=\"Petrification%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;petrification&lt;/a&gt;. However, the ring itself breaks upon taking effect. It is similar to the &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Ring%20of%20Sacrifice\"&gt;Rare Ring of Sacrifice&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" in this regard, but unlike the latter, it can be repaired after it breaks for 6,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn\u00a0\"\", the ring costs 14,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; to repair."}
{"id": "5582", "revid": "37406887", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5582", "title": "Ring of Steel Protection", "text": "The Ring of Steel Protection is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;, in the room under the path of the boulder, guarded by a &lt;a href=\"Serpent%20Mage\"&gt;Serpent Mage&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral Information.\nThe Ring of Steel Protection boosts physical, strike, slash, and thrust defense by 50 points each."}
{"id": "45603", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45603", "title": "Ring of Steel Protection (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Ring of Steel Protection is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEffect.\nThe increased defense granted by this ring makes it one of the most handy rings in the game boasting one of the best defense to weight ratios of any item. The drawback however would be that it only increases defense against physical blows and does thus not decrease damage taken from any kind of magic."}
