{"id": "54375", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54375", "title": "Ring of the Dead", "text": "The Ring of the Dead is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Ring of the Dead is found in &lt;a href=\"Drangleic%20Castle\"&gt;Drangleic Castle&lt;/a&gt;, in a room accessed by using the elevator before the &lt;a href=\"Looking%20Glass%20Knight\"&gt;Looking Glass Knight&lt;/a&gt; boss fight. In order to get the ring, the &lt;a href=\"Milfanito\"&gt;Milfanito&lt;/a&gt; in the cage must be freed by using the &lt;a href=\"Key%20to%20the%20Embedded\"&gt;Key to the Embedded&lt;/a&gt; on the door. When talked to, she will scream and then disappear, leaving the Ring of the Dead as a drop.\nGeneral Information.\nThe ring makes its wearer appear human regardless of hollowing. The effect is purely cosmetic however, meaning that the ring has no practical use."}
{"id": "99018", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=99018", "title": "Ring of the Embedded", "text": "The Ring of the Embedded is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in .\nAvailability.\n&lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Eleum%20Loyce\"&gt;Frozen Eleum Loyce&lt;/a&gt; - From the Abandoned Dwelling bonfire, proceed as normal until there is a tree and a narrow alleyway between two buildings. Walk to the edge and then left to reach a corpse holding the ring.\nCharacteristics.\nIncreases VGR, END and VIT depending on how low level these stats are while increasing damage taken. Niche ring for low level runs."}
{"id": "5607", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5607", "title": "Ring of the Evil Eye", "text": "The Ring of the Evil Eye is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Depths\"&gt;Depths&lt;/a&gt;, on a corpse in the area inhabited by several &lt;a href=\"Basilisk\"&gt;Basilisk&lt;/a&gt;s.\nEffect.\nThe Ring of the Evil Eye absorbs 30 &lt;a href=\"Health\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; from each killed.\nGroups of enemies killed together grant only 30 &lt;a href=\"Health\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; in total. To get the full benefit of the Ring of the Evil Eye, kills must be spaced out.\nOverview.\nThis ring is excellent for countering damage-over-time effects such as those of the &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Blade\"&gt;Chaos Blade&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Power%20Within\"&gt;Power Within&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;. It also improves the durability of players as they travel. It is, however, less useful against tough enemies, such as &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;es.\nThis ring is an especially large boon to players &lt;a href=\"Cooperative%20Gameplay\"&gt;playing cooperatively&lt;/a&gt;. The healing effect of the ring will cut down on the need for the host to heal the summoned phantom from minor hits and fall damage."}
{"id": "44584", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44584", "title": "Ring of the Evil Eye (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Ring of the Evil Eye is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nThe Ring of the Evil Eye acts very similarly to its \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20the%20Evil%20Eye\"&gt;counterpart&lt;/a&gt;, regenerating a small amount of &lt;a href=\"Health%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt; for every enemy killed. The healing effect is a static number and is not affected by what enemy is killed. The effect of the standard ring is as strong as the \"Dark Souls\" version, but the +1 and +2 rings having substantially stronger effect (66% and 166% stronger respectively). This is to contrast with most other rings carried over from \"Dark Souls\", whose effects have been tuned down. The Ring of the Evil Eye is a somewhat viable means of maintaining health depending on the foes being faced and the amount of damage one takes before dispatching them as well as the version of the ring itself needless to say the +1 and 2 rings are better than the standard at this.\nOverview.\nThis ring serves as a great way to mitigate self-damaging effects, such as those caused by the &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Blade%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Chaos Blade&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and &lt;a href=\"Immolation\"&gt;Immolation&lt;/a&gt;, or damage-over-time effects like &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;, provided there are enemies around to kill. However, it is best to replace it with a different ring for boss fights that don't consist of multiple enemies (like &lt;a href=\"Prowling%20Magus%20and%20Congregation\"&gt;Prowling Magus and Congregation&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Lord\"&gt;Skeleton Lord&lt;/a&gt;s), as it is effectively useless when fighting only one or two tough enemies."}
{"id": "134149", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134149", "title": "Ring of the Evil Eye (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Ring of the Evil Eye is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nMechanics.\nAny enemy dying will proc the health restore effect, including ones that die due to other players or the environment. However, other players dying will not activate the effect, even if the wearer dealt the killing blow. Additionally, the heal doesn't account for multiple enemies being killed within a short period of time or by a single attack.\nThe effect can be stacked with &lt;a href=\"Arstor%27s%20Spear\"&gt;Arstor's Spear&lt;/a&gt; to heal an additional 30 HP per kill.\nUse.\nSingle player.\nThe Ring of the Evil Eye is an excellent way of conserving healing items or spells, and excels when used against groups of weak enemies due to healing the same amount regardless of how powerful the enemy is. Because of the way it procs against multiple kills, it is best to kill enemies one at a time if the goal is to recover health.\nOnline gameplay.\nThis ring can be very potent depending on the area. Because the effect procs no matter who gets the kill, a phantom can gain the benefit from the host or an allied phantom killing an enemy, and an invader can profit from the host's party killing enemies to get to the invader. In either case, it can be a very helpful way to maintain health due to possessing less health and half the Estus of a &lt;a href=\"Host%20of%20Embers\"&gt;Host of Embers&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "99335", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=99335", "title": "Ring of the Living", "text": "The Ring of the Living is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in .\nAvailability.\n&lt;a href=\"Frigid%20Outskirts\"&gt;Frigid Outskirts&lt;/a&gt;. Found on a corpse near the crates on the outer rim of the pit leading to &lt;a href=\"Lud%20and%20Zallen\"&gt;Lud and Zallen&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nRemoves the colored glow around your character when in the world of another player."}
{"id": "133068", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133068", "title": "Ring of the Sun's First Born", "text": "The Ring of the Sun's First Born is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound at\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;.\nFrom the &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley%23Bonfires\"&gt;Pontiff Sulyvahn&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, head back out toward the railing and fall straight onto the altar below.\nEffect.\nBoosts the power of offensive &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;miracles&lt;/a&gt; by 20%."}
{"id": "5592", "revid": "357165", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5592", "title": "Ring of the Sun's Firstborn", "text": "The Ring of the Sun's Firstborn (\u592a\u967d\u306e\u9577\u5b50\u306e\u6307\u8f2a) is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nNear &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Sun%20Gwyndolin\"&gt;Gwyndolin&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, accessible in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; by taking the bottom stairs after the elevator has been lowered.\nEffect.\nIncreases the attack power of offensive &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;miracles&lt;/a&gt; by 20%. This effect stacks with other miracle boosting bonuses, such as that of the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20the%20Sun%20Princess\"&gt;Ring of the Sun Princess&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20the%20Dark%20Sun\"&gt;Crown of the Dark Sun&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20Dusk\"&gt;Crown of Dusk&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "6173", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6173", "title": "Ring of the Sun Princess", "text": "The Ring of the Sun Princess (\u592a\u967d\u306e\u738b\u5973\u306e\u6307\u8f2a) is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nJoin the &lt;a href=\"Princess%27s%20Guard\"&gt;Princess's Guard&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; by talking to &lt;a href=\"Gwynevere%2C%20Princess%20of%20Sunlight\"&gt;Gwynevere, Princess of Sunlight&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral information.\nThe Ring of the Sun Princess increases &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20Synergy\"&gt;Miracle Synergy&lt;/a&gt; by one level. Wearing the Ring of the Sun Princess while standing next to a resonance ring results in a double synergy boost (although it does not necessarily make the synergy twice as powerful; see chart on Miracle Synergy page for details). Without the Ring of the Sun Princess, it is possible to have the benefits of a higher levels of synergy boost, but only when casting miracles near larger numbers of resonance rings.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
