{"id": "150117", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150117", "title": "Ringed Knight Paired Greatswords", "text": "The Ringed Knight Paired Greatswords are &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Paired%20Weapons\"&gt;paired&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ultra greatswords&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28location%29\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;. Guaranteed drop from the paired greatswords-wielding &lt;a href=\"Ringed%20Knight\"&gt;Ringed Knight&lt;/a&gt; in front of the &lt;a href=\"Church%20of%20Filianore\"&gt;Church of Filianore&lt;/a&gt; when killing him for the first time.\nCharacteristics.\nThe second-heaviest ultra greatsword in the game, the Ringed Knight Paired Greatswords are deadly powerhouses that are capable of devastating lone and multiple foes alike.\nRequiring the wielder to hit the soft-cap for &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to even consider wielding, the paired greatswords are capable of performing wide horizontal sweeps, vertical smashes as well as thrusting attacks, giving it a respectably varied moveset. It also possesses the &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; health of a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt;, similar to the &lt;a href=\"Fume%20Ultra%20Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fume Ultra Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, making it very strong at trading against other &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; weapons of equal size.\nThe defining characteristic of this weapon is that it is &lt;a href=\"Paired%20Weapons\"&gt;paired&lt;/a&gt;, allowing the wielder to perform devastating combos that bring both greatswords to bear on one or multiple targets. Each individual attack has extremely strong stun potential, locking down foes and rendering them helpless to be eviscerated by the blades' high damage output. While the one-handed attacks can be &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parried&lt;/a&gt;, the paired attacks cannot. This can be useful for mixing up attacks against opponents who attempt to parry this weapon due to the one-handed moveset. Additionally, its &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; can bring even more damage output to the table, as well as greatly extend the wielder's reach via launched projectiles and strong forward-momentum rush attacks.\nHowever, all of the paired greatswords' attacks are very slow to bring to bear, making it easy to reaction-dodge by experienced players. Like other ultra weapons, care must be exercised to prevent the foe from exploiting openings and punishing extended attack combos, particularly with &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;backstabs&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "150161", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150161", "title": "Ringed Knight Set", "text": "The Ringed Knight Set is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;medium armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Ringed%20Knights\"&gt;Ringed Knights&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Ringed Knight Set is a very high-end set of armor that provides strong protection. It has good defense against most forms of physical damage, being somewhat weak to &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage but resisting &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; very well. Its elemental defenses are also very strong, possessing across-the-board resistance to all elements except &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt;; unlike other plate armor sets, its &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; absorption is its second-strongest resistance, after &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile it has rather mediocre resistance to status effect buildup, its &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; resistance is unusually high. It also has a very good &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;-to-weight ratio to go with its high weight, making it a reliable set to wear for wielding ultra weapons."}
{"id": "150490", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150490", "title": "Ringed Knight Spear", "text": "The Ringed Knight Spear is a &lt;a href=\"Pikes\"&gt;pike&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28location%29\"&gt;the Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;. On the great stairway leading from the Inner Wall to the Streets, there is a small side path close to the bottom of the stairs where the second trio of &lt;a href=\"Harald%20Legion%20Knight\"&gt;Harald Legion Knight&lt;/a&gt;s is encountered. After traversing the hallway filled with &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt;-inflicting &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Cleric\"&gt;Undead Cleric&lt;/a&gt;s, the spear can be found on a corpse to the right, guarded by a spear-wielding &lt;a href=\"Ringed%20Knight\"&gt;Ringed Knight&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Ringed Knight Spear is both a versatile and great weapon for its category as it is one of only three spears in the game with the &lt;a href=\"Partizan%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Partizan&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt;, the others being the Partizan and &lt;a href=\"Yorshka%27s%20Spear\"&gt;Yorshka's Spear&lt;/a&gt;. As such, the weapon boasts powerful long-ranged thrusts that can keep individual foes at bay as well as wide sweep attacks that are adept at dealing with crowds.\nLike other Ringed Knight weapons, the Ringed Knight Spear's &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; ignites the blade of the weapon, dealing extra &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage and boosting the range of the weapon itself. Upon activation, the player leaps forward at great speed for a strong thrust, buffing the weapon with increased damage for a short amount of time and greatly augmenting the power of its strong attacks, though this comes at the cost of increased stamina usage.\nWhen the buff is active, the Ringed Knight Spear's jumping and rolling attacks transform into those normally performed by &lt;a href=\"Halberds%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;halberds&lt;/a&gt;.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "150118", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150118", "title": "Ringed Knight Straight Sword", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28location%29\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;. From the &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28location%29%23Bonfires\"&gt;Ringed City Streets&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, go towards the &lt;a href=\"Judicator%20Giant\"&gt;Judicator Giant&lt;/a&gt;, turning right before reaching the sunken church guarded by &lt;a href=\"Ringed%20Knight\"&gt;Ringed Knight&lt;/a&gt;s. At the top of a hill to the right, there will be a sunken building with a non-aggressive &lt;a href=\"White-faced%20Locust\"&gt;White-faced Locust&lt;/a&gt; atop, the sword can be found near him.\nCharacteristics.\nThough it may seem plain due to possessing the &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword\"&gt;Long Sword&lt;/a&gt; moveset, the Ringed Knight Straight Sword can be very powerful in the right hands. Unlike most straight swords it is largely &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;-oriented in terms of &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, and is tied with the &lt;a href=\"Gotthard%20Twinswords\"&gt;Gotthard Twinswords&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lothric%27s%20Holy%20Sword\"&gt;Lothric's Holy Sword&lt;/a&gt; for the longest straight sword in the game. However, it is also tied with the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Sword\"&gt;Dark Sword&lt;/a&gt; for the heaviest straight sword in the game (excluding paired weapons like the Gotthard Twinswords and &lt;a href=\"Valorheart\"&gt;Valorheart&lt;/a&gt;), and cannot benefit from &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infusions&lt;/a&gt;, making it less flexible as a weapon and ideal largely for quality builds.\nWhat sets the Ringed Knight Straight Sword apart from its peers is its &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ember%20%28Ringed%20Knight%20Straight%20Sword%29\"&gt;Ember&lt;/a&gt;. This ability greatly extends its already potent reach, and allows the wielder to perform devastating combos and chase down foes with abandon. The attacks from the Ember stance also possess &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt;, a rarity on weapons of this class size, and make it a force to be reckoned with.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "150203", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150203", "title": "Ringed Knights", "text": ""}
{"id": "131664", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131664", "title": "Ringfinger Leonhard", "text": "Ringfinger Leonhard is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;enemy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". He is voiced by .\nDescription.\nRingfinger Leonhard is a loyal knight and servant of &lt;a href=\"Rosaria%2C%20Mother%20of%20Rebirth\"&gt;Rosaria, Mother of Rebirth&lt;/a&gt;. He is a member of the covenant &lt;a href=\"Rosaria%27s%20Fingers\"&gt;Rosaria's Fingers&lt;/a&gt;, along with &lt;a href=\"Yellowfinger%20Heysel\"&gt;Heysel&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Creighton%20the%20Wanderer%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Creighton&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Longfinger%20Kirk\"&gt;Kirk&lt;/a&gt; (as well as the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;Ashen One&lt;/a&gt; should they choose to follow his questline). He introduces the player to &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; and the invasion mechanic by gifting them several &lt;a href=\"Cracked%20Red%20Eye%20Orb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Cracked Red Eye Orbs&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nBorn into royalty, where he learned the arts of sorcery and swordsmanship, Leonhard received horrid burns across his entire body through unmentioned circumstances. His face in particular was scalded terribly, and he wore a &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Mask\"&gt;Silver Mask&lt;/a&gt; to conceal this.\nSome unknown while later, he traveled to the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;, seeking out a way to heal his scarred body by rebirth. When he finally met &lt;a href=\"Rosaria%2C%20Mother%20of%20Rebirth\"&gt;Rosaria, Mother of Rebirth&lt;/a&gt;, he abstained from healing his burns for unknown reasons, instead taking vows to serve Rosaria and inheriting a &lt;a href=\"Crescent%20Moon%20Sword\"&gt;crescent sword&lt;/a&gt; imbued with the power of the moon.\nQuestline.\nLeonhard first appears in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; after either lighting the &lt;a href=\"Tower%20on%20the%20Wall\"&gt;Tower on the Wall&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"High%20Wall%20of%20Lothric\"&gt;High Wall of Lothric&lt;/a&gt; or defeating &lt;a href=\"Vordt%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Vordt of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;. He will give the player five &lt;a href=\"Cracked%20Red%20Eye%20Orb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Cracked Red Eye Orbs&lt;/a&gt; and encourage them to invade other players to collect &lt;a href=\"Ember\"&gt;Ember&lt;/a&gt;s. He will then leave Firelink Shrine the next time it is reloaded.\nAfter defeating the &lt;a href=\"Curse-rotted%20Greatwood\"&gt;Curse-rotted Greatwood&lt;/a&gt; or lighting the &lt;a href=\"Cliff%20Underside\"&gt;Cliff Underside&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;, Leonhard will return to his place next to Lothric's throne should the player be in possession of a &lt;a href=\"Pale%20Tongue\"&gt;Pale Tongue&lt;/a&gt;. Speaking to him will cause him to give the player the &lt;a href=\"Lift%20Chamber%20Key\"&gt;Lift Chamber Key&lt;/a&gt;, encouraging them to kill the &lt;a href=\"Darkwraith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Darkwraith&lt;/a&gt; locked up in Lothric's dungeon.\nThe key is used to open a locked door in the High Wall of Lothric underneath the Tower on the Wall bonfire. Killing the Darkwraith at the bottom of the elevator will reward the player with a full &lt;a href=\"Red%20Eye%20Orb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Red Eye Orb&lt;/a&gt;. When spoken to afterward, Leonhard will congratulate the player and teach them the &lt;a href=\"Gestures%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;\"Applause\" gesture&lt;/a&gt;, before he encourages them to join &lt;a href=\"Rosaria%27s%20Fingers\"&gt;Rosaria's Fingers&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce the player deepens devotion to Rosaria's Fingers by offering a Pale Tongue to &lt;a href=\"Rosaria%2C%20Mother%20of%20Rebirth\"&gt;Rosaria, Mother of Rebirth&lt;/a&gt; (as opposed to using the attribute reallocation or appearance change services), Leonhard will appear near the entrance to her chamber, where he briefly greets the player.\nWhen the player reaches the &lt;a href=\"Profaned%20Capital\"&gt;Profaned Capital&lt;/a&gt; past &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;, Leonhard becomes paranoid that they will try and steal &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Rosaria\"&gt;Rosaria's soul&lt;/a&gt;, and murders her before fleeing to &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;. The player can find a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Eye%20Orb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Eye Orb&lt;/a&gt; on Rosaria's corpse, which can be used to invade Leonhard's world in the chamber once containing the illusion of &lt;a href=\"Gwynevere%2C%20Princess%20of%20Sunlight\"&gt;Gwynevere, Princess of Sunlight&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce defeated, Leonhard will drop the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Rosaria\"&gt;Soul of Rosaria&lt;/a&gt;, his &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Mask\"&gt;Silver Mask&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Crescent%20Moon%20Sword\"&gt;Crescent Moon Sword&lt;/a&gt;; as well, the remainder of &lt;a href=\"Leonhard%27s%20Set\"&gt;his set&lt;/a&gt; can be purchased from the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt;. The questline ends at this point, as the player can choose to either return Rosaria's Soul to her corpse, consume it for &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;transpose&lt;/a&gt; it with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nLike the other members of Rosaria's Fingers, Leonhard has the &lt;a href=\"Obscuring%20Ring\"&gt;Obscuring Ring&lt;/a&gt; equipped by default, so retreating outside of lock-on range can allow him to approach the player stealthily. He will alternate between attacking with his curved sword and casting &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt; with his staff, using either &lt;a href=\"Homing%20Soulmass%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Homing Soulmass&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Soul Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;. If given the chance he will even cast &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic Shield&lt;/a&gt;. He is a very aggressive foe and his shotel can deal damage past shields, so good dodging skills are required to prevail against him. At range, he tends to cast Homing Soulmass and then combine it with &lt;a href=\"Crescent%20Blade\"&gt;Crescent Blade&lt;/a&gt; for an extremely powerful projectile attack. \nLike most other NPC invaders, Leonhard can drink from his &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt; up to twice before running out.\nEven with his melee prowess in mind, it is advised to keep close to him to avoid his repeated casting of ranged attacks and bait him into being parried. Conserving stamina to rush him down when he attempts to consume his Estus Flask. The second swing on his combo is the best chance to parry him, as it possesses a longer wind up animation."}
{"id": "137735", "revid": "27035229", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=137735", "title": "Rings", "text": ""}
{"id": "3847", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3847", "title": "Rings (Dark Souls)", "text": "Rings\u00a0are a type of &lt;a href=\"equipment\"&gt;equipment&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThe player character has two ring slots on their equipment screen, and at any time may have any two \"different\" rings on simultaneously; the player \"may not\" wear two copies of the same ring.\nCut content rings.\nThese rings were &lt;a href=\"Removed%20Content\"&gt;removed&lt;/a&gt; from the final release of \"Dark Souls\", however, they are still present in the game's data files. It is possible to add these rings to the player's inventory through the use of a save file editor."}
{"id": "59498", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=59498", "title": "Rings (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Rings are equipment &lt;a href=\"Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; that grant either &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; bonuses, self-augments to the wielder, as well as &lt;a href=\"Covenants%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; bonuses. Up to four rings can be equipped in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\", unlike the original \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", which only allowed two rings to be equipped at once. \nRings.\nNumbers separated by a \" / \" mark are in correspondence with its regular, +1, and +2 forms. Locations for upgraded rings are listed in ascending order. One thing to note is one can not equip 2 rings of the same type like a life ring and a life ring+2 the game will say, \"Cannot equip. this ring conflicts with another equipped ring.\""}
{"id": "130340", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130340", "title": "Rings (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Rings are a type of equipment in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". They grant either &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; bonuses, self-augmentations to the wielder, or various other bonuses. Up to four rings can be equipped at once.\nRings.\nLocations for upgraded rings are listed in ascending order."}
