{"id": "2704", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2704", "title": "Engorged Hollow", "text": "Engorged Hollows, also known as Engorged Zombies, are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nThey are only found in the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;.\nA passive Engorged Hollow can be found standing in the corner of a room, up a ladder, past the &lt;a href=\"Bonewheel%20Skeleton\"&gt;Bonewheel Skeleton&lt;/a&gt; tunnels. It drops the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Surge\"&gt;Fire Surge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0upon death.\nDescription.\nEngorged Hollows come in two varieties, unarmed and torch-wielding. The torch-wielders attack short ranged, while the unarmed cast Fire Surge, as well as large, fireball projectiles.\nThey release a cloud of\u00a0blood upon death which can inflict a great deal of Toxic buildup to the player if not avoided, causing 8 damage per second over 10 minutes once contracted.\u00a0They can also cast\u00a0a small cloud similar to\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Toxic%20Mist%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Toxic Mist&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategies.\nThere will be no visible cloud of blood if the engorged hollow is killed with &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Damage%20Type%29%23Utilization\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; and toxic discharge range will be extremely short in this case. However, if the player is pressed in very close for the killing blow, they can still be hit with toxic.\nSince the Toxic discharge has a very short range, the use of a ranged or long handled weapon, like a &lt;a href=\"Spear\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Halberd\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt;, is very effective.\n&lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt;bing will delay the Toxin's release; however, the blood must still be avoided for a few seconds. Parrying and riposting will not work for avoiding the toxin.\nAttacking with a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Spear\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0or &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords\"&gt;Thrusting Sword&lt;/a&gt; while\u00a0simultaneously\u00a0blocking with the &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Shield\"&gt;Spider Shield&lt;/a&gt; will block the toxic discharge.\nA lethal attack with significant knockback, such as the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20Greatsword\"&gt;Black Knight Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;'s power attacks, will in general keep the toxic cloud away from the player."}
{"id": "122019", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=122019", "title": "Engorged Zombie", "text": ""}
{"id": "71483", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=71483", "title": "Engraved Gauntlets", "text": "The\u00a0Engraved Gauntlets\u00a0are\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Cove%20Tseldora\"&gt;Brightstone Cove Tseldora&lt;/a&gt;; one must have the &lt;a href=\"Tseldora%20Den%20Key\"&gt;Tseldora Den Key&lt;/a&gt; to access the chest where it is located. The key itself is only obtained by completing the &lt;a href=\"Mild-Mannered%20Pate\"&gt;Pate&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Creighton%20the%20Wanderer\"&gt;Creighton&lt;/a&gt; questline.\nCharacteristics.\nAt first glance, the Engraved Gauntlets seem to be very poor stat-wise, as they offer little &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; resistances; however, they makes up for it by having the highest &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Petrification%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Petrification&lt;/a&gt; resistances in the game for hand armor, and by having a unique effect of a 5% chance for normal hits to deal damage equal to a &lt;a href=\"critical%20attack\"&gt;critical attack&lt;/a&gt;. When this effect is triggered, the gauntlets cause an explosion, releasing what seems to be ash around the player.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
{"id": "68637", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=68637", "title": "Enhanced Undead", "text": "The Enhanced Undead is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nEnhanced Undead are seemingly genetic experiments created by &lt;a href=\"Aldia%2C%20Scholar%20of%20the%20First%20Sin\"&gt;Lord Aldia&lt;/a&gt;, in his attempts to achieve immortality and recreate &lt;a href=\"dragons\"&gt;dragons&lt;/a&gt;. The former undead has undergone a hideous mutation which made it almost half-dragon, granting them increased strength but grotesquely altering their appearance into inhuman beasts that now prowl the darkest places of &lt;a href=\"Drangleic\"&gt;Drangleic&lt;/a&gt;. They resemble horrid amalgamations of twisted humans, being bulky in nature, having a large hunch-backed form, thick arms, and having to crawl around. Their hairless bodies are adorned in horned growths, protruding along their body; accompanied by a scaly tail.\nStrategy.\nThe Undead's attacks drain a lot of stamina so it is advisable to evade their attacks, rather than trying to block them. They move very slowly but caution is advised, they can perform a powerful lunge attack from a distance. Ranged attacks and spells are the safest way to eliminate them but it is possible to backstab them as long as the player steers clear of their tail swipes. Using &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison Arrows&lt;/a&gt; is also a very good idea as they have no ranged protection: this may trigger a jump attack from them though.\nLightning damage.\nIn the Sinner's Rise, since these creatures are immersed in &lt;a href=\"Water%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;water&lt;/a&gt;, they have lower &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; defense than usual and players who can deal high Lightning damage can take advantage of this. On the other hand, players who rely mainly on &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage will have a hard time against them, as the water increases their Fire defense to 95%.\nBackstab and run.\nThe Enhanced Undead can be &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;bed. In particular, when approaching the player, it will almost always close the gap with a lunge attack. The player can very easily evade this attack with a sideways roll (preferably to the left) even in deep water. This will leave the Enhanced Undead's back wide open. While the backstab itself might not be enough to kill the Undead, it can easily be finished off while it is recovering (and vulnerable).\nIn Sinner's Rise, the Enhanced Undead to the right will be \"partially\" unaware to the player's presence. It will face back and forth between the two opening. Wait until it looks the other way to close in and land a backstab.\nBaiting.\nThe Enhanced Undead can also be killed by repeatedly baiting its left handed swipe attack and landing a single blow while it recovers. While in close quarters the Enhanced Undead will use this move frequently so the player should be able to kill it fairly quickly. It is strongly advised to completely avoid its tail swipe attack however, it deals a lot of damage and has a deceptively short recovery time.\nElevator trickery.\nIt's possible to use the elevator to reach the underground section to the player's advantage in two way: one can either lure the enemy on the elevator itself and activate the pressure plate to send the mob away (even if they fall, they'll be stuck on the wooden platform above the area) or send the elevator back up first and bait the beast to attack close enough to the chasm to fall to their death."}
{"id": "46990", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46990", "title": "Enslaved Pig", "text": "Enslaved Pigs, also known as Undead Devourers, are &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nStrategy.\nThey have a weak attack but a high defense, as well as a decent &lt;a href=\"HP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; value. They can take a particularly long time to kill due to being too short, which causes the player to miss their attacks constantly. Using a weapon that strikes downward helps actually in hitting these foes. Using &lt;a href=\"lances\"&gt;lances&lt;/a&gt; also help as they thrust in the direction of the target lock.\u00a0"}
