{"id": "149470", "revid": "1429792", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=149470", "title": "Environmental Hazards", "text": "Besides enemies and bosses, the \"Dark Souls\" series is known for putting the player against a series of environmental hazards in an attempt to hinder their path and test their skills. Depending on what kind of obstacle the player comes across, they are expected to devise new strategies with which to traverse certain areas. These hindrances vary from mechanisms that trigger traps, bodies of deep water where movement is reduced, poisonous swamps, urns filled with noxious liquids, bottomless pits, and many others.\nIt is not uncommon for these kinds of obstacles to also inflict a certain type of elemental damage, such as fire, poison, bleed, frost, corrosion, etc., usually filling that element's build-up meter by a considerable amount.\nGame specific information.\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nBoulder machine\nDart-shooting traps\nDeep water\nLava\nPendulums\nPoison swamp\nSpike statues\nTar pit\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;.\nAcid pools\nAcid urns\nAcid-spitting dragon statues\nBraziers\nCoal tar puddles\nCorrosive egg sacks\nCrumbling floors\nCurse jars\nDart-shooting traps\nDeep water\nDropping platforms\nFlamethrowers\nGuillotines\nLava\nLift\nPetrifying statues\nOil casks\nPoison fog pits\nPoison pools\nPoison pots and urns\nPoison-spitting statues\nSnowstorms\nSharp crystal shards\nSpiked walls\nTrapped chests\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;.\nBallista\nClawed Curses\nFrost urns\nPoison swamp\nSkeleton Boulder\nToxic fog\nToxic swamp"}
