{"id": "18910", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18910", "title": "Escape Death", "text": "Escape Death is a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe only way to obtain this miracle is by modifying the game.\nCharacteristics.\nEscape Death acts exactly like a &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Ring%20of%20Sacrifice\"&gt;Rare Ring of Sacrifice&lt;/a&gt;. Upon its usage the character will become surrounded by a tearstone-like aura which lasts until death. Upon death, or becoming &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Cursed&lt;/a&gt; the message \"Magic Revived\" will appear and no loss of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0or &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20Mechanic\"&gt;humanity&lt;/a&gt; will be incurred.\nNotes.\nThe removal of this miracle was most likely due to developers noting that it would remove the penalty that death carries, therefore making the game unbalanced."}
{"id": "57190", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57190", "title": "Espada Ropera", "text": "The\u00a0Espada Ropera\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGiven to the player by\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Chancellor%20Wellager\"&gt;Chancellor Wellager&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0after vanquishing the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Giant%20Lord\"&gt;Giant Lord&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Espada Ropera is in essence an upgraded version of the &lt;a href=\"Rapier%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Rapier&lt;/a&gt;, it has borderline the same stats, same length, same moveset and same Counter-Strength and Poise Damage, although with 0.5 more weight and higher requirements which focus more on DEX builds, which is supported by its higher scaling in DEX, and lower scaling in STR. If playing as a DEX build and the Rapier is a go to weapon of choice, then perhaps the Espada Ropera should be swapped since it has higher potential for that build in particular and it has almost double the durability of the Rapier, making it a more attractive choice for regular PVE.\nIt also has 5 more points of damage than the Rapier when fully upgraded.\nAdditionally, the Espada Ropera (along with the Rapier) is also very good for use in &lt;a href=\"Power%20Stance\"&gt;power stance&lt;/a&gt; when it is wielded in the right hand as one will be able to use the strong attack to parry, which can't normally be done while in a power stance."}
{"id": "5142", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5142", "title": "Estoc", "text": "The Estoc is a &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound early in the &lt;a href=\"New%20Londo%20Ruins\"&gt;New Londo Ruins&lt;/a&gt;, on a corpse between the &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; elevator and the first bridge leading to the rest of the ruins.\nCharacteristics.\nAs with other thrusting swords, the Estoc can attack from behind a &lt;a href=\"Shields\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, making it useful defensively. The Estoc has the longest reach of all the thrusting swords; in addition, it has a slashing-like attack that deals &lt;a href=\"Regular%20%28Damage%20Type%29\"&gt;Regular Damage&lt;/a&gt;. The Estoc's good reach makes it a flexible weapon. While the Estoc's\u00a0weak attack is slightly slower than those of the other rapiers, it still has a relatively good attack speed.\nAlthough the in-game stat menus show the Estoc having a 100 critical rate, the Estoc benefits from a higher &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;motion value&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstabs&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte\"&gt;Ripostes&lt;/a&gt; making it deal higher damage on these critical attacks like all of the other Thrusting Swords. \nThe Estoc's greatest weakness lies in its relatively sluggish\u00a0weak attack\u00a0combos, making it harder to really rack up damage against nimble opponents. It can chain from weak attacks to a strong attack, but not vice versa.\nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "34024", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34024", "title": "Estoc (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Estoc is a &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Lenigrast\"&gt;Blacksmith Lenigrast&lt;/a&gt; for 1,500 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Estoc features &lt;a href=\"thrust\"&gt;thrust&lt;/a&gt; attacks with moderate range and slashes to the side that bypass shields. It has a fair base damage and moderate &lt;a href=\"Scaling%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, and has better range than the &lt;a href=\"Rapier%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Rapier&lt;/a&gt;. As with most thrusting swords, the Estoc can be used from behind the &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Estoc synergizes well with the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Stone%20Ring\"&gt;Stone Ring&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and weapon buffs. As this weapon hits very quickly, Estoc users can easily &lt;a href=\"stunlock\"&gt;stunlock&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"poise%20break\"&gt;poise break&lt;/a&gt; their opponents. This makes it one of the best thrusting swords for &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is notable for being the only &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;-oriented rapier in the game, attaining a B-scaling in Strength when fully &lt;a href=\"Upgrade%20Materials%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;reinforced&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "130264", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130264", "title": "Estoc (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Estoc is a &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;thrusting sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nAs the longest reaching thrusting sword, the Estoc can easily hit and punish opponents who aren't positioned properly. Unlike most thrusting swords in its class, it can perform a unique horizontal sweep attack that has great range and can catch people off guard. Its skill, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20Splitter\"&gt;Shield Splitter&lt;/a&gt;, can bypass &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt;, making it an effective counter against defensive opponents. This, coupled with the fact that it is the longest thrusting sword, definitely makes it an invaluable tool in anyone's arsenal.\nHowever, it does suffer some drawbacks. It cannot be used as a &lt;a href=\"Parry%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; tool, removing an extra layer of utility that a normal Rapier could normally have, and doesn't have an increased &lt;a href=\"critical%20attack\"&gt;critical attack&lt;/a&gt; modifier, making it a poor choice for &lt;a href=\"riposte\"&gt;riposte&lt;/a&gt;s.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with &lt;a href=\"Upgrade%20Materials%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "172408", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=172408", "title": "Estus", "text": ""}
{"id": "44668", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44668", "title": "Estus Flask", "text": ""}
{"id": "2994", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2994", "title": "Estus Flask (Dark Souls)", "text": "Estus Flasks are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nAn Estus flask is first granted to the player by &lt;a href=\"Oscar%2C%20Knight%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Oscar&lt;/a&gt; before he succumbs to death. Alternately, the player automatically receives the Estus Flask if they kill Oscar. Thereafter, players receive up to 5 Estus charges by resting at an unkindled bonfire. A kindled bonfire yields 10 charges; further kindling bonfires through &lt;a href=\"Rite%20of%20Kindling\"&gt;Rite of Kindling&lt;/a&gt; rewards an additional 5 charges per kindle to up to 20 in total. Additionally, if the bonfire last rested at is kindled by another player, the player receives an extra Estus charge, unless the player is at 20 Estus, which is the maximum amount possible. \nEffect.\nEstus Flasks are the basic healing items in \"Dark Souls\". They are replenished via resting at &lt;a href=\"bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfires&lt;/a&gt;. The amount they heal can be upgraded by offering &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper%20Soul\"&gt;Fire Keeper Soul&lt;/a&gt;s to other &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper\"&gt;Fire Keeper&lt;/a&gt;s. The maximum amount of times an Estus flask can be upgraded is seven times. Only seven fire keeper souls can be obtained in one game. Four of these can be found scattered throughout the world, but the other three must be obtained by killing the firekeepers to claim their souls (or in the case of &lt;a href=\"Anastacia%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Anastacia of Astora&lt;/a&gt;, obtaining her soul from &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Lautrec%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Lautrec&lt;/a&gt; after he kills her).\nNotes.\nFirekeeper souls are very rare (only 7 can be found per playthrough, and three are held by NPCs that the player may not want to kill or let die) and, though they can be consumed for &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20Mechanic\"&gt;humanity&lt;/a&gt;, they are usually better spent upgrading estus flasks. Upgrading estus flasks dramatically improves the player's ability to heal him or herself. For example, a player with twenty +7 Estus Flasks can heal up to 10,000 more &lt;a href=\"Health\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; in total than a player with twenty non-upgraded Flasks.\n&lt;a href=\"Phantom\"&gt;Phantom&lt;/a&gt;s of all types cannot rely on estus flasks for healing. However, they can still rely on all other healing items and spells, such as the Heal miracle, consuming solid humanity, etc. Friendly phantoms (not including NPC) are healed by estus whenever their host player uses one.\nPlayers hit by a &lt;a href=\"Lloyd%27s%20Talisman\"&gt;Lloyd's Talisman&lt;/a&gt; will not be able to drink estus for a limited duration.\nSome enemies, such as &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Soldier\"&gt;Hollow Soldier&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Balder%20Knight\"&gt;Balder Knight&lt;/a&gt;s, can also use Estus flasks for healing.\nBackstory.\nEstus are fondly treasured by the undead. Oscar names it \"an undead favorite\". On the other hand, the living are not cordial about Estus. The undead hunter &lt;a href=\"Lloyd\"&gt;Lloyd&lt;/a&gt; created &lt;a href=\"Lloyd%27s%20Talisman\"&gt;Lloyd's Talisman&lt;/a&gt;s to aid in his extermination of the undead, which block the healing ability of estus."}
{"id": "41933", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41933", "title": "Estus Flask (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Estus Flasks are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "130223", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130223", "title": "Estus Flask (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Estus Flask is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGiven to the player at the start of the game.\nOverview.\nThe player starts with three Estus Flask charges at the beginning of the game. In addition, the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Estus%20Flask\"&gt;Ashen Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt; can be picked up a short distance into the tutorial area, granting an overall total of four charges. Drinking from the flask restores &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Points%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; (the Ashen Estus Flask restores &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt;). Resting at a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; will refill all Estus Flasks to maximum charges.\nTo increase the number of Estus Flask charges, the player must first find an &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Shard\"&gt;Estus Shard&lt;/a&gt; and bring it to &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Andre\"&gt;Blacksmith Andre&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, where they will also be able to allot the total number of uses between the standard and the ashen Estus Flasks. The combined total between both Estus Flasks can reach a maximum of 15 charges. Any additional Estus Shards obtained &lt;a href=\"New%20Game%20Plus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;afterward&lt;/a&gt; will have no practical use, since they cannot be sold.\nThe potency of each charge can be increased by burning an &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Bone%20Shard\"&gt;Undead Bone Shard&lt;/a&gt; at the Firelink Shrine bonfire, for up to a maximum level of +10. As with Estus Shards, any additional Undead Bone Shards obtained will have no practical use.\nEquipping the &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Ring\"&gt;Estus Ring&lt;/a&gt; will increase the amount of HP recovered by consuming Estus by 20%.\nUpgrades.\nThe Estus Flask can be reinforced by burning an &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Bone%20Shard\"&gt;Undead Bone Shard&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29%23Bonfires\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, for up to a maximum level of +10.\nEstus Soup.\nThroughout the game, the player may come across a few pots and cauldrons cooking estus soup. Consuming the soup will restore 535 &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Points%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt;, and is subject to modification by equipping the &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Ring\"&gt;Estus Ring&lt;/a&gt; or being debuffed by the &lt;a href=\"Soldering%20Iron\"&gt;Soldering Iron&lt;/a&gt;.\nThese containers will refill each time an area is loaded, so if the player has already depleted one and does not want to rest at a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; in order to avoid repopulating the area, all they have to do is exit and continue the game, and the pot will be replenished with a new dose. Sitting at a bonfire will not refill the pot.\nEstus soup containers can be found in the following areas:"}
{"id": "44113", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44113", "title": "Estus Flask Shard", "text": "Estus Flask Shards are &lt;a href=\"Miscellaneous%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nEstus Flask Shards are given to the &lt;a href=\"Emerald%20Herald\"&gt;Emerald Herald&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Majula\"&gt;Majula&lt;/a&gt; to increase the total amount of &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt; uses that the player can hold. The flask can be upgraded with 11 shards to a maximum of 12 uses.\nThe shards can still be obtained after the flask uses are increased up to 12, but other than selling them to &lt;a href=\"Lonesome%20Gavlan\"&gt;Lonesome Gavlan&lt;/a&gt; for 1,200 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; each, they will be useless."}
{"id": "130373", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130373", "title": "Estus Ring", "text": "The Estus Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound at the bottom of the decrepit bell tower behind &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=\"Tower%20Key%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Tower Key&lt;/a&gt; required).\nClimb up the spiraling staircase inside the first tower and enter the second one at the other end of the bridge. While facing the lift inside, drop down onto the various caskets protruding from the walls (preferably on the right side as it is safer, although on the left side the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper%20Set\"&gt;Fire Keeper Set&lt;/a&gt; can be obtained) and make way to the bottom of the tower, where the ring can be looted from the lifeless body of an old &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper\"&gt;fire keeper&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nIncreases &lt;a href=\"HP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; restored by drinking from the &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt; by 20%."}
{"id": "130324", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130324", "title": "Estus Shard", "text": "Estus Shards are &lt;a href=\"Miscellaneous%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;miscellaneous items&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nA total of eleven Estus Shards can be collected in a single &lt;a href=\"NG%2B%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;game cycle&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nGive to &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Andre\"&gt;Blacksmith Andre&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; to increase usages of the &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt;. The shards can be allotted in either fashion regarding the &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Estus&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Estus%20Flask\"&gt;Ashen Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt;s."}
