{"id": "143023", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143023", "title": "Ethereal Oak Shield", "text": "The Ethereal Oak Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Painted World of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;, on a corpse found in a tower of the Millwood ruins. The corpse is located at the bottom half of the tower after going up a ladder and then going down the stairs.\nCharacteristics.\nA strong medium shield, the Ethereal Oak Shield possesses several beneficial characteristics that makes it a very popular tool.\nWith high elemental resistances save &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; and 100% physical absorption, it is capable of warding off most types of damage very effectively. Additionally, when wielded it regenerates &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Points%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; at a rate of 2 points per second, the equivalent to what a fully upgraded &lt;a href=\"Blessed%20Gem\"&gt;Blessed&lt;/a&gt; infusion is capable of. It also allows the wielder to perform the skill of the main-hand weapon, allowing for high moveset flexibility.\nThe only real drawback to this shield is its comparatively low stability, which does not increase meaningfully with upgrades, making it unsuitable for blocking multiple successive attacks.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "133933", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133933", "title": "Evangelist", "text": "Evangelists (\u8056\u5802\u306e\u6559\u5c0e\u5e2b \"Seid\u014d no Ky\u014dd\u014dshi\", Instructors of the Faith of the Cathedral), or Cathedral Evangelists, are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nAgents of the Church of the Deep, these women were sent to the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt; in order to spread religion and enlightenment among the citizens. However, their true goal was to collect potential victims to be sacrificed to &lt;a href=\"Aldrich%2C%20Devourer%20of%20Gods\"&gt;Aldrich&lt;/a&gt;. Sadistic and cruel, they enjoy taunting their victims before cleansing them of their sins with fire.\nTheir presence is announced by the distinctive tapping sound their &lt;a href=\"Spiked%20Mace\"&gt;maces&lt;/a&gt; make when they hit the ground as they walk.\nLocations.\n&lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;\nStrategy.\nEvangelists are very dangerous opponents that differ in tactics depending on their distance from the player. At long range, they will cast &lt;a href=\"Gnaw\"&gt;Gnaw&lt;/a&gt;, a swarm of insects that slowly homes in and will pursue the player for several seconds. If the attack connects, it will inflict some &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage and heavy &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up. At close range, they will use their &lt;a href=\"Spiked%20Mace\"&gt;maces&lt;/a&gt; and will attempt to \"cleanse\" the player by grabbing them and setting them &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;alight&lt;/a&gt;.\nEvangelists move slowly and are very vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;backstabs&lt;/a&gt;, but their maces have a wide radius and can strike the player if they move behind them. If they start casting a spell, it is possible to prevent them from firing it by staggering them."}
{"id": "135834", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135834", "title": "Evangelist Gloves", "text": "The Evangelist Gloves is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". They are part of the &lt;a href=\"Evangelist%20Set\"&gt;Evangelist Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nDrops from the &lt;a href=\"Evangelist\"&gt;Evangelist&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;."}
