{"id": "133471", "revid": "357034", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133471", "title": "Excrement-covered Ashes", "text": "The Excrement-covered Ashes are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". They are one of several &lt;a href=\"Umbral%20Ash\"&gt;umbral ashes&lt;/a&gt; that can be found throughout the course of the game.\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;.\nHead to the lake in Irithyll and look for the entrance to the sewers. Be careful of the &lt;a href=\"Sewer%20Centipede\"&gt;Sewer Centipede&lt;/a&gt;s in this area and keep a lookout for a small alcove directly across from the stairs that lead to the kitchen. The ashes are on a corpse resting in shin-high water.\nUsage.\nExtends the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt;'s inventory to include the following items:"}
{"id": "56639", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56639", "title": "Executioner", "text": ""}
{"id": "18133", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18133", "title": "Executioner's Chariot", "text": "The Executioner's Chariot is a\u00a0 in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nLocated in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Purgatory\"&gt;Undead Purgatory&lt;/a&gt;, the Executioner's Chariot attempts to run over the player when encountered. It barrels through whatever is in its path, whether friend or foe. Upon killing the charioteer, the chariot's horse acts much like a &lt;a href=\"Fang%20Boar\"&gt;Fang Boar&lt;/a&gt; from the original \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn \"Scholar of the First Sin\", a chariot horse can be found in &lt;a href=\"Drangleic%20Castle\"&gt;Drangleic Castle&lt;/a&gt;, in the hall previously filled with &lt;a href=\"Alonne%20Knight%20Captain\"&gt;Alonne Knight Captain&lt;/a&gt;s.\nSummoning.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Scholar%20of%20the%20First%20Sin\"&gt;Scholar of the First Sin&lt;/a&gt; only, &lt;a href=\"Creighton%20the%20Wanderer\"&gt;Creighton the Wanderer&lt;/a&gt; can be recruited as a &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;phantom&lt;/a&gt; for this fight, once freed, and, if the player moves fast enough, the shade &lt;a href=\"Bashful%20Ray\"&gt;Bashful Ray&lt;/a&gt; may also join, which can help in keeping the skeletons at bay for a while.\nLore.\nThe Executioner's Chariot was created with the sole purpose of tormenting and punishing the &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; during the hunts organized by the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Iron%20King\"&gt;Old Iron King&lt;/a&gt;. Although the Executioner appears to be the master of the chariot, it's actually the horse that controls the machine and carries out its creator's will to torture the undead.\nFight overview.\nThere are two phases to this fight: the \"chariot\" phase and the \"horse\" phase.\nAs you enter the fog door, phase one begins. The chariot will circle around the arena and attempt to ram into you. This can be avoided by hiding in the openings along the walls, or with a well-timed roll. The corridor is littered with &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Skeletons&lt;/a&gt; that will continue to revive until the &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Necromancers&lt;/a&gt;, which are hiding in the gaps along the walls, are killed. The chariot progressively loses speed the more damage it is dealt, giving you more time between its laps to deal with the skeletons and necromancers.\nThere are two methods of approaching the first phase. The first is to make your way around the corridor to the other side of the pit and pull the lever, which will lower a gate the chariot will crash into. The second method is to continually hit it with ranged attacks until it reaches 25% of its health. At this point, the chariot will be unable to clear the gap and fall. It will dangle off the ledge helplessly until it is hit one final time, which will cause it to lose its grip and tumble into the pit. This method skips phase two entirely.\nPhase two begins when the chariot bashes into the gate. The horse will be free as the chariot is completely destroyed and the charioteer is killed. The horse is very easy to fight and behaves similarly as the &lt;a href=\"Fang%20Boar\"&gt;Fang Boar&lt;/a&gt; from the first \"Dark Souls\". The horse has a charge attack where it bashes you with its head, this move is unblockable and does damage through your shield. If you linger behind the horse for too long, it will kick at you with its hind legs. If you are in front of it for too long, it will stand up on its hind legs and bash downwards on you. If you are at a medium distance away, the horse will spew a &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; fog that is unblockable and does heavy damage through your shield.\nStrategy.\nPhase 1: The key here is to rush towards each of the two Necromancers and take them out before the Skeletons can catch up, avoiding the Chariot by hiding in alcoves as you go along. Bring a high stability shield if you can't run directly from one Necromancer to the other. Once the second Necromancer is killed, take out the Skeletons. Let the Chariot kill them if you wish. After the Necromancers and the Skeletons have been taken out, run to the lever and pull it.\nPhase 2: At the start of phase two, the horse will fall over. This is the perfect time to use magic or pyromancy that has a long cast time for big damage. You don't want the horse to hit you as it does heavy damage and can deal damage through shields.\nCircle around the horse and don't get too far away from it or it might use its breath attack which deals a lot of damage (but is easily dodged). Do not stay in front of the horse. Instead, stay behind it and try to bait it into kicking with its hind legs. Once it kicks and you successfully avoid it, move in quickly and hit the horse one or two times. The horse will then turn towards you and you should circle around it once again. You may also try to bait it into doing its front stomp attack or dodging its breath attack and then getting a few blows in. You don't want it to charge you as it is more difficult to dodge and can deal serious damage.\nAlternate strategy (ranged or magic users).\nAfter entering the arena, the player can choose to rush the first Necromancer and clean up the Skeletons, allowing the player to take cover in an alcove. Each time the chariot comes around, a well cast spell or a well timed arrow can deal damage to the chariot (a good spell to use is &lt;a href=\"Homing%20Crystal%20Soulmass%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Homing Crystal Soulmass&lt;/a&gt; or just a simple &lt;a href=\"Homing%20Soulmass%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Homing Soulmass&lt;/a&gt;. After casting, stand in one of the alcoves and wait). When the boss gets down to about 1/3 to 1/5 of its health, the chariot will stop circling the arena, most likely surprising the player.\nContinuing around the arena, clearing out the remaining Necromancer and Skeletons, the player will notice that the chariot is being held above the pit by the two horses, while the charioteer dangles helplessly underneath. The player can now freely kill the boss without any resistance. A single attack will send the chariot tumbling into the abyss, finishing the boss fight.\nIf you are having trouble catching the Chariot as it goes by, try using a spell that shoots straight (like &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lightning Spear&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Soul Spear&lt;/a&gt;). Stand by one of the alcoves near the entrance to the boss fight and shoot it down the hall when you see the Chariot come around the corner. After you shoot it, you have plenty of time to dodge into the alcove. You can also use the binoculars if you like.\nAlternate strategy (melee).\nA version of the above strategy is also available for melee builds. Proceed as normal, working your way up the arena, and killing the two Necromancers, letting the chariot take care of the Skeletons (&lt;a href=\"Alluring%20Skull%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Alluring Skulls&lt;/a&gt; work well here). Once you kill the last Necromancer, instead of pulling the lever, wait for the chariot to pass and run to the edge of the pit. Stand with your back against the right hand wall, facing the opposite wall, and as close to the edge of the pit as you can safely be. Since the chariot is jumping, it cannot hit you here. Each time it lands you can take a swing at it, and whittle down its health bar. This works with most weapons, but a weapon with a wide swing is better as locking on is a very bad idea. The timings will vary, so some experimentation will be necessary. As an example, a &lt;a href=\"Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; R1, triggered the instant the boss jumps will always connect and do decent damage.\nThis strategy will end the same way as the caster version. Once the bosses health is low enough, it will miss the jump and end up hanging off the pit. Walk up and hit it once to finish the fight.\nAttacks.\nDefenses(Stats are from Param Studio and are not estimated)&lt;br&gt;Strike/Slash/Thrust defense are applied on top of Physical Defense.\nMusic.\n&lt;embedvideo service=\"youtube\" alignment=\"center\" description=\"Dark Souls 2 \u2014 Executioner's Chariot by \"&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WFujXVMAahU&lt;/embedvideo&gt;"}
{"id": "46126", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46126", "title": "Executioner's Chariot Soul", "text": "The\u00a0Executioner's Chariot Soul is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;boss soul&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nAvailability.\nObtained after defeating the &lt;a href=\"Executioner%20Chariot\"&gt;Executioner Chariot&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Purgatory\"&gt;Undead Purgatory&lt;/a&gt;.\nUse.\nConsume for 8,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;trade&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0to acquire either the &lt;a href=\"Shield%20Crossbow\"&gt;Shield Crossbow&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Chariot%20Lance\"&gt;Chariot Lance&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "131433", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131433", "title": "Executioner's Greatsword", "text": "The Executioner's Greatsword is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound at the graveyard in the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;.\nFrom the &lt;a href=\"Cleansing%20Chapel\"&gt;Cleansing Chapel&lt;/a&gt;, make way into the graveyard and proceed in the general straightforward direction until reaching the other end. A small enclosed area with several corpses and some loot can be found, one of which is the sword. Upon picking it up, however, the &lt;a href=\"Reanimated%20Corpse\"&gt;corpses&lt;/a&gt;, some of which are &lt;a href=\"Infested%20Corpse\"&gt;infested&lt;/a&gt;, will come to life and ambush the player.\nCharacteristics.\nDespite its relatively mundane appearance, the Executioner's Greatsword possesses several quirks that can make it a strong asset in one's arsenal.\nPossessing the same moveset as the &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt;, the Executioner's Greatsword also has the advantage of inflicting purely strike damage with its attacks, which is typically resisted very poorly by the vast majority of all armor sets in the game. As well, it &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scales&lt;/a&gt; very well with &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, further augmenting its ability to deal tremendous amounts of damage against opponents. It is also only one of two greatsword-class weapons that possess the &lt;a href=\"Stomp%20%28disambiguation%29\"&gt;Stomp (disambiguation)&lt;/a&gt; weapon art, the other being the Bastard Sword, which gives it some very useful &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; options.\nPerhaps its most unique characteristic is that for every enemy that dies, the wielder gains 6 &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt;. This can be useful for fueling the use of the weapon's &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, or even for casting spells on specialized builds. It is particularly useful in &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, as there is no requirement that the wielder use the weapon to kill enemies in order to replenish FP, or that the wielder even has to be the one to obtain the kill. This is very useful since non-&lt;a href=\"Host%20of%20Embers\"&gt;host&lt;/a&gt; players can recover FP without having to allot &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Estus%20Flask\"&gt;Ashen Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt;s, allowing them to utilize more standard Estus, and invaders can recover FP by profiting off of the work of a host's party.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;\nVideos.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
