{"id": "135187", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135187", "title": "Executioner Set (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Executioner Set (\u51e6\u5211\u4eba\u30b7\u30ea\u30fc\u30ba) is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nPurchased from the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt; for a total of 18,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; after &lt;a href=\"Horace%20the%20Hushed\"&gt;Horace the Hushed&lt;/a&gt; is killed.\nCharacteristics.\nWeighing in at the upper end of heavy armor sets, the Executioner Set provides good defenses as a cost of its weight.\nIt is extremely resilient against most forms of physical damage, only being weak to &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage like most other plate metal sets. It has very good elemental resistances as well, being weak only to &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage, and having higher than usual resistance to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. It also resists &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;status effects&lt;/a&gt; very effectively, only truly being \"weak\" to &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; buildup.\nWith a heavy weight and good &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;-to-weight ratio, the Executioner Set can reliably wield heavy weapons to trade against enemies, provided that the proper amount of &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; is invested.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "2597", "revid": "38876010", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2597", "title": "Executioner Smough", "text": "Executioner Smough (\u51e6\u5211\u8005\u30b9\u30e2\u30a6) is a and &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" and a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nSmough was the royal executioner of &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; in service of the &lt;a href=\"Gods\"&gt;Gods&lt;/a&gt;, wielding a &lt;a href=\"Smough%27s%20Hammer\"&gt;massive hammer&lt;/a&gt; and wearing &lt;a href=\"Smough%27s%20Set\"&gt;grotesque armor&lt;/a&gt;. He desired to be a part of &lt;a href=\"Four%20Knights%20of%20Gwyn\"&gt;Gwyn's Knights&lt;/a&gt; but he was rejected despite his immense power. This was not only because he took pleasure in his brutal work, making him eerily gleeful, but because he also ground the bones of his victims into his own feed to absorb them, while his hammer became capable of restoring health with attacks thanks to its continued use in his work.\nAt some point after Gwyn linked the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"The%20Nameless%20King\"&gt;Gwyn's firstborn son&lt;/a&gt; was dethroned and exiled, nearly all of the deities abandoned Anor Londo together and moved to an unknown location but Smough remained in the forsaken city alongside &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Slayer%20Ornstein\"&gt;Dragon Slayer Ornstein&lt;/a&gt; to guard the cathedral where &lt;a href=\"Gwynevere%2C%20Princess%20of%20Sunlight\"&gt;Gwynevere&lt;/a&gt; resided.\nTogether, these two powerful warriors would become the last ritual challenge for the potential &lt;a href=\"Chosen%20Undead\"&gt;Chosen Undead&lt;/a&gt;. In fact, the Undead who tried to follow in Gwyn's footsteps to sacrifice themselves to the Flame would have to be tested even before obtaining the &lt;a href=\"Lordvessel\"&gt;Lordvessel&lt;/a&gt; and seeking powerful souls. Ringing the &lt;a href=\"Bells%20of%20Awakening\"&gt;Bells of Awakening&lt;/a&gt; represents only the first of these challenges, and success means gaining access to &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt; to be tested further. The Undead who manage to overcome the tests and dangers of the fortress and defeat the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Golem\"&gt;Iron Golem&lt;/a&gt; would manage to access the city of the gods. Once they managed to enter the cathedral of Anor Londo to try to obtain the Lordvessel they would still be challenged by Smough and Ornstein, to ensure that only the strongest of the strongest Undead could have an audience with Gwynevere.\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter centuries of waiting for the Chosen Undead without success, Ornstein grew tired of his duty and left the cathedral in search of the &lt;a href=\"The%20Nameless%20King\"&gt;Nameless King&lt;/a&gt;. Consequently, the last remaining guard was Smough, who continued to hold his post and protect \"Gwynevere\". As a reward for his loyalty, Gwyndolin finally granted him the title of \"knight,\" even if he was the last one left in Anor Londo after all others had abandoned it. As the cathedral's sole guardian, Smough met his end when a worthy Undead reached Anor Londo and defeated him, gaining an audience with \"Gwynevere\" and the Lordvessel with which to begin their search for powerful souls.\nSmough's &lt;a href=\"Smough%27s%20Great%20Hammer\"&gt;ritual hammer&lt;/a&gt; was preserved as a relic by Gwyndolin and protected in his manor when &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt; rose from the ruins of Anor Londo."}
