{"id": "131239", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131239", "title": "Exile Greatsword", "text": "The Exile Greatsword is a &lt;a href=\"Curved%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;curved greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by the &lt;a href=\"Exile%20Watchdog\"&gt;Exile Watchdog&lt;/a&gt; that wields it in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nWidely regarded as one of the most powerful &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; weapons in the game, the Exile Greatsword brings tremendous raw damage to the table.\nPossessing the standard curved greatsword moveset, this weapon has a steep Strength wielding requirement as well as a non-negligible &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; wielding requirement, meaning that players must invest a large amount of stats in order to even use this weapon in the first place. However, the investment is well worth it, as it has a very high Attack Rating even among all ultra weapons, and competes with the &lt;a href=\"Harald%20Curved%20Greatsword\"&gt;Harald Curved Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; for being the most powerful curved greatsword.\nThis weapon's main drawback is that it is by far the heaviest curved greatsword in the game, meaning that even with high &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; investment the wielder will be unable to stack as much heavy armor to increase &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; as compared to wielding any of the other curved greatswords. However, should this hurdle be overcome, the Exile Curved Greatsword is capable of inflicting staggering amounts of damage to any foe unfortunate enough to be hit by it.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with standard &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;br&gt;\nVideos.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
