{"id": "135188", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135188", "title": "Exile Set", "text": "The Exile Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt; for a total of 13,500 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once the player has defeated the two &lt;a href=\"Exile%20Watchdog\"&gt;Exile Watchdog&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt; who guard the way to the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nWeighing on the higher end of the heavy armor sets, the Exile Set is a very well-balanced armor set.\nWith very good physical resistances, the Exile Set is notable for lacking a weakness to &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage. Its elemental resistances are only moderate for its weight, but it is very resilient against &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. It also boasts extreme resistance to &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;status effects&lt;/a&gt;, most notably against &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; despite having comparatively low resistance to &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nMost importantly, the set has solid &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; to go with its weight, making it a very good armor set to complement large &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; weapons."}
{"id": "133801", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133801", "title": "Exile Watchdog", "text": "The Exile Watchdogs are a pair of in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nTwo identical humanoid enemies in the &lt;a href=\"Exile%20Set\"&gt;Exile Set&lt;/a&gt; who guard the ruins leading to the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;. One wields an &lt;a href=\"Exile%20Greatsword\"&gt;Exile Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; whilst the other uses a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Club%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Great Club&lt;/a&gt; and can cast healing &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;miracles&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;, near the ladder that leads to the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep%23Bonfires\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. Only two appear in the game, one wielding a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Club%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; and the other a &lt;a href=\"Exile%20Greatsword\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt;.\nBoth Watchdogs guard the entrance to the old ruins that give access to the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;. This structure dwells on the farthest shore of the marsh, on a stretch of dry land found to the right of the second &lt;a href=\"Great%20Crab\"&gt;Great Crab&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Great%20Club%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;club&lt;/a&gt;-wielder usually stands post near a small staircase at the entrance, and the &lt;a href=\"Exile%20Greatsword\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt;-wielder awaits inside, although in rare occasions he can be seen patrolling outside the ruins.\nStrategy.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Great%20Club%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;club&lt;/a&gt;-wielding Watchdog will usually approach the player first and it is recommended to lure him away from the ruins to avoid alerting the other. He is significantly slower with his attacks, although he can perform a leaping smash from long range. He will attempt to heal when low on HP but this can be interrupted as it takes a few seconds for the process to complete. Be wary of his &lt;a href=\"Target%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Target Shield&lt;/a&gt;, as it can be used for parrying. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Exile%20Greatsword\"&gt;curved greatsword&lt;/a&gt; warrior will primarily attack by performing his weapon's &lt;a href=\"Spin%20Slash%20%28Curved%20Greatsword%29\"&gt;Spin Slash&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, leaving himself open to attack once he has finished. He will also occasionally buff himself for increased defense, although this can be interrupted with a &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;. At some point, he may also take out a &lt;a href=\"Daggers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; and hold it in his left hand for quick-opening attacks. He may also try to kick the player frequently if they keep their shield up.\nIf the player uses an &lt;a href=\"Ember\"&gt;Ember&lt;/a&gt; in this area, they should be cautious when fighting the Watchdogs. Not only will members of the &lt;a href=\"Watchdogs%20of%20Farron\"&gt;Watchdogs of Farron&lt;/a&gt; invade if playing online, but &lt;a href=\"Yellowfinger%20Heysel\"&gt;Yellowfinger Heysel&lt;/a&gt; will also invade if the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Sage\"&gt;Crystal Sage&lt;/a&gt; has not yet been defeated. A careless or unlucky player could end up having to fight up to four powerful enemies at once.\nAlternatively, if you summon &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Knight%20Hodrick\"&gt;Holy Knight Hodrick&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;a href=\"Mound-makers\"&gt;mad phantom&lt;/a&gt;, he can easily solo the two Watchdog NPCs, although be careful, as he can also attack you if you get close to him. Safely lure him to the NPCs and he can defeat them quickly.\nIf you do not wish to fight them via conventional means, then run up the stairs where they are first encountered and begin climbing down the ladder. Hang near the top and they will both likely fall to their deaths. Do not hang too close to the top or you can still be hit and knocked down the ladder, ensuring an instant death."}
{"id": "130410", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130410", "title": "Exploding Bolt", "text": "Exploding Bolts are a type of &lt;a href=\"Ammunition%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEffect.\nDeals &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage in small surrounding area on impact."}
{"id": "173165", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=173165", "title": "Explorer", "text": "The Explorer is one of the &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%202\"&gt;Dark Souls 2&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt has no particular specialty, with only high &lt;a href=\"Adaptability\"&gt;Adaptability&lt;/a&gt; and an above average &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; being notable. It is, essentially, a &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Deprived&lt;/a&gt; with some extra stats, some bonus items, and a Dagger. \nAs their &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt; is the only weapon they start out with, with not even a spell to help them, it is imperative to pick up a second Dagger in &lt;a href=\"Things%20Betwixt\"&gt;Things Betwixt&lt;/a&gt; on the first side path fore more Durability. Is is possible to wield the &lt;a href=\"Morning%20Star%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Morning Star&lt;/a&gt; from the cliffs in &lt;a href=\"Majula\"&gt;Majula&lt;/a&gt; two-handed with 2 more points in &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and one more point in &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Crossbow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Light Crossbow&lt;/a&gt; can be found atop a wall in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Fallen%20Giants\"&gt;Forest of Fallen Giants&lt;/a&gt; and only need 1 more point in Strength to wield with two hands. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Traveling%20Merchant%20Set\"&gt;Traveling Merchant Set&lt;/a&gt; is only a bit better than the &lt;a href=\"Imported%20Set\"&gt;Imported Set&lt;/a&gt; and has no &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; but the hat increases &lt;a href=\"Item%20Discovery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Item Discovery&lt;/a&gt; slightly, which is a solid benefit early on.\nThe lone &lt;a href=\"Pharros%27%20Lockstone\"&gt;Pharros' Lockstone&lt;/a&gt; can be used to unlock 1 (and only one, since it is a consumable) &lt;a href=\"Pharros%27%20Contraption\"&gt;Pharros' Contraption&lt;/a&gt;. Of the first two Contraptions to be found in the game, the first one is below a trapped room with ballistae in the Forest of Fallen Giants and used to get the &lt;a href=\"Chloranthy%20Ring\"&gt;Chloranthy Ring&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Slab%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Titanite Slab&lt;/a&gt;, and the second one is found one a small platform up halfway up the first set of stairs in &lt;a href=\"No-man%27s%20Wharf\"&gt;No-man's Wharf&lt;/a&gt; where it is used turn on the lights and scare away all the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Stalker\"&gt;Dark Stalker&lt;/a&gt;s in the area. \nFor restocking the items, &lt;a href=\"Merchant%20Hag%20Melentia\"&gt;Merchant Hag Melentia&lt;/a&gt; carries more &lt;a href=\"Lifegem\"&gt;Lifegem&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Witching%20Urn\"&gt;Witching Urn&lt;/a&gt;s and 1 more Pharros' Lockstone, &lt;a href=\"Laddersmith%20Gilligan\"&gt;Laddersmith Gilligan&lt;/a&gt; has &lt;a href=\"Aromatic%20Ooze\"&gt;Aromatic Ooze&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Wood%20Bolt%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Wood Bolt&lt;/a&gt;s are sold by &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Lenigrast\"&gt;Blacksmith Lenigrast&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Repair%20Powder%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Repair Powder&lt;/a&gt;s are sold in limited quantities by Blacksmiths and infinitely by one late-game merchant, &lt;a href=\"Prism%20Stone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Prism Stone&lt;/a&gt;s are sold by &lt;a href=\"Sweet%20Shalquoir\"&gt;Sweet Shalquoir&lt;/a&gt;, and 5 more &lt;a href=\"Rusted%20Coin\"&gt;Rusted Coin&lt;/a&gt;s are sold by &lt;a href=\"Magerold%20of%20Lanafir\"&gt;Magerold of Lanafir&lt;/a&gt;. \nTheir high Adaptability gives them 9 i-frames when starting out, and they only need 2 more points in the stat to improve that to 10 i-frames. \nStarting Equipment.\nThe Explorer also starts with a variety of items: a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Quartz%20Ring\"&gt;Spell Quartz Ring&lt;/a&gt;, 20 &lt;a href=\"Wood%20Bolt%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Wood Bolt&lt;/a&gt;s, 8 &lt;a href=\"Witching%20Urn\"&gt;Witching Urn&lt;/a&gt;s, 4 &lt;a href=\"Aromatic%20Ooze\"&gt;Aromatic Ooze&lt;/a&gt;s, 5 &lt;a href=\"Prism%20Stone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Prism Stone&lt;/a&gt;s, 2 &lt;a href=\"Rusted%20Coin\"&gt;Rusted Coin&lt;/a&gt;s, 1 &lt;a href=\"Repair%20Powder%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Repair Powder&lt;/a&gt;, and 1 &lt;a href=\"Pharros%27%20Lockstone\"&gt;Pharros' Lockstone&lt;/a&gt;. \nAs with all starting classes in Dark Souls 2, the &lt;a href=\"Imported%20Set\"&gt;Imported Set&lt;/a&gt; worn before the character creation can be found unequipped in the character's inventory. "}
