{"id": "147403", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=147403", "title": "Eygil", "text": "Magus Eygil is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nMagus Eygil was a loyal follower of the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Iron%20King\"&gt;Old Iron King&lt;/a&gt;. He sought to grant &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; a will of its own, and thus he created the &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Dance%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Dance of Fire&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Snake\"&gt;Fire Snake&lt;/a&gt;, the latter which he actually managed to make it behave like a snake, writhing toward its prey with a mind to strike.\nAn enormous &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Keep%23Bonfires\"&gt;idol&lt;/a&gt; overlooking his &lt;a href=\"Old%20Iron%20King\"&gt;master&lt;/a&gt;'s dwelling in the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Keep\"&gt;Iron Keep&lt;/a&gt; depicts him in the shape of a massive, flame-breathing , with several bullhead statues decorating the rest of the place. Similar statues can also be found later in &lt;a href=\"Brume%20Tower\"&gt;Brume Tower&lt;/a&gt;. In addition, certain enemies only encountered in these two areas drop the &lt;a href=\"Minotaur%20Helm\"&gt;Minotaur Helm&lt;/a&gt;, which may also be related to the magus. Whether this was his real form or just how he was portrayed is unknown."}
