{"id": "131575", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131575", "title": "Eygon of Carim", "text": "Eygon of Carim is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". He is voiced by , who also voices the &lt;a href=\"Cage%20Madman\"&gt;Cage Madman&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nEygon wears &lt;a href=\"Morne%27s%20Set\"&gt;Morne's Set&lt;/a&gt; and wields &lt;a href=\"Morne%27s%20Great%20Hammer\"&gt;Morne's Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt; along with the &lt;a href=\"Moaning%20Shield\"&gt;Moaning Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlot.\nEygon is first encountered guarding the cell where &lt;a href=\"Irina%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Irina&lt;/a&gt; is being held. He has an initially negative disposition toward the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;Ashen One&lt;/a&gt; but agrees to ally himself with the Ashen One after Irina is freed from her cell. He makes it clear that the alliance is only valid for as long as Irina is kept safe and warns them that he will make them pay if her safety is at risk. He can then be summoned for the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Sage\"&gt;Crystal Sage&lt;/a&gt; fight.\nIf the player kills Irina, Eygon will be waiting for them in the area outside of &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; and immediately become hostile. If any &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dark&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;miracles&lt;/a&gt; are purchased from Irina after giving her a forbidden tome, he will kidnap her to \"save\" her from corruption and become hostile outside Firelink.\nAvoiding purchasing any dark miracles from Irina will enable the player to summon Eygon for the &lt;a href=\"Dragonslayer%20Armour\"&gt;Dragonslayer Armour&lt;/a&gt; boss fight. His corpse, containing his weapons, can then be found in Irina's old cell in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Morne%27s%20Set\"&gt;his armor&lt;/a&gt; will be available for purchase from the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt;."}
