{"id": "6724", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6724", "title": "Faith (Dark Souls)", "text": "Faith is a &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nFaith is an attribute used to meet requirements for melee weapons, Talismans, and spells; Faith softcaps are 30/50. Similar to Intelligence, the amount of damage you deal and the amount of HP you heal from healing based Miracles will correlate with the Talisman you are using rather than your overall point investment into Faith. Faith is also a weapon modifier, increasing magical\u00a0damage for unique weapons (see Weapon Scaling)\u00a0any weapon upgraded down the &lt;a href=\"Divine%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Divine&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Occult%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Occult&lt;/a&gt; paths. Faith also serves to boost your magic defense. You will want to meet but not exceed the requirements to use spells, weapons, and Talismans.\nFaith also increases the lightning damage of the &lt;a href=\"Dragonslayer%20Spear\"&gt;Dragonslayer Spear&lt;/a&gt; and the physical damage of the (cursed) &lt;a href=\"Greatsword%20of%20Artorias%20%28Cursed%29\"&gt;Greatsword of Artorias&lt;/a&gt;.\nWeapon scaling.\nThe following are\u00a0weapons\u00a0that scale with faith, and their level of scaling, when not upgraded. Weapon scaling may change when upgraded."}
{"id": "51933", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51933", "title": "Faith (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Faith is a &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nThe primary purpose of raising Faith is to increase one's &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; Bonus; it also slightly increases the player's &lt;a href=\"Cast%20Speed\"&gt;Cast Speed&lt;/a&gt; and total &lt;a href=\"HP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt;, in addition to one's &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; Bonuses (however, the Dark bonus is only in conjunction with one's &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;). &lt;a href=\"Sacred%20Chimes\"&gt;Sacred Chimes&lt;/a&gt; scale with Faith."}
{"id": "130194", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130194", "title": "Faith (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Faith is a &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\" that increases attack damage with Faith-based weapons and as well as increased damage output with spells such as &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Miracles&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pyromancies&lt;/a&gt;.\nFaith increases damage done by weapons and catalysts through the use of a &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; mechanic. A letter denoting a weapons specific scaling properties is noted beneath the weapon's required faith stat. The letters range in order of effectiveness from E, D, C, B, A, and S.\nWeapons and catalysts with an E rating for scaling will receive a poor benefit from investment in faith while weapons with an S rating receive the greatest benefit.\nNote: the term Catalyst refers to any medium used to cast spells.\nAs is with every other stat in the game, it also has indirect bonuses such as increasing the player character's flat damage absorption. In this case, Faith governs the players flat defenses against &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nSoft caps.\nDepending on the catalyst, weapon and &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infusion&lt;/a&gt;, leveling Faith to certain thresholds will maximize its potency with those tools.\nMost weapons that inflict innate &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage, or which inflicts &lt;a href=\"Physical%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; damage based off Faith, such as the &lt;a href=\"Dragonslayer%20Greataxe\"&gt;Dragonslayer Greataxe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wolnir%27s%20Holy%20Sword\"&gt;Wolnir's Holy Sword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sunlight%20Straight%20Sword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sunlight Straight Sword&lt;/a&gt; will reach peak efficiency at 40 Faith; in a special case, this also applies to the &lt;a href=\"Crucifix%20of%20the%20Mad%20King\"&gt;Crucifix of the Mad King&lt;/a&gt;, which inflicts Dark damage scaling primarily from Faith. Weapons that have been infused with a &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Gem\"&gt;Lightning Gem&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Blessed%20Gem\"&gt;Blessed Gem&lt;/a&gt; also soft-cap their respective damage types at 40 Faith.\nIf a weapon inflicts innate &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; or Dark damage, like the &lt;a href=\"Gargoyle%20Flame%20Spear\"&gt;Gargoyle Flame Spear&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Hand%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark Hand&lt;/a&gt;, Faith will improve the respective elemental damage, alongside &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;, to a soft-cap of 40 for each stat. For infusions with a &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Gem\"&gt;Chaos Gem&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Gem\"&gt;Dark Gem&lt;/a&gt;, the soft-cap becomes 30 Faith alongside 30 Intelligence.\n&lt;a href=\"Sacred%20Chimes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sacred Chimes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Talismans%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Talismans&lt;/a&gt; used for casting Miracles will see very strong returns from Faith investment. Almost all such catalysts require leveling Faith to a minimum of 18 before &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; begins to increase, and this continues to improve the strength of the catalyst up until 60 Faith is reached. For most Faith catalysts, the rate of Spell Buff improvement falls off after 45 Faith.\nFor catalysts that specialize in casting Pyromancies, Dark &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sorceries&lt;/a&gt; and Dark Miracles, the scaling and soft-caps behave differently. As like their melee counterparts, &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20Flames%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pyromancy Flames&lt;/a&gt; will improve up until 40 Faith is reached, alongside 40 Intelligence. For specialized Dark catalysts like the &lt;a href=\"Izalith%20Staff\"&gt;Izalith Staff&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Caitha%27s%20Chime%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Caitha's Chime&lt;/a&gt;, this cap is instead 45 Faith and 45 Intelligence. &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Chime\"&gt;Crystal Chime&lt;/a&gt; also soft-caps at these values, however its scaling falls off noticeably past 30 Faith and 30 Intelligence."}
