{"id": "4634", "revid": "357122", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4634", "title": "Fall Control", "text": "Fall Control (\u843d\u4e0b\u5236\u5fa1) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Griggs%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Griggs of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; for 1,500 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; after he is rescued from the lower &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Burg\"&gt;Undead Burg&lt;/a&gt;, provided that the player has 10 &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; or higher.\nEffect.\nFall Control nullifies non-lethal &lt;a href=\"fall%20damage\"&gt;fall damage&lt;/a&gt;. It also drastically reduces falling &lt;a href=\"stun\"&gt;stun&lt;/a&gt;, allowing players to move and attack more quickly after a long fall. However, Fall Control will not trigger if players jump off a ledge that would automatically kill upon impact; certain heights will always kill players, regardless of whether or not they have Fall Control. If the sorcery runs out of time during a fall, players will not benefit from the damage reduction or falling stun elimination upon reaching the ground.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "48145", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48145", "title": "Fall Control (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Fall Control is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral Information.\nThe best method available for surviving long falls. It will negate all &lt;a href=\"Fall%20damage\"&gt;damage from falling&lt;/a&gt;, unless the fall is great enough to instantly kill the player. This makes it superior to items that merely reduce falling damage, as Fall Control can be used to safely traverse all but the longest of drops. \nThe duration of this spell depends on Intelligence and will range from 59 seconds at 10 int when the spell is spiced down all the way up to 113 seconds at 22 Intelligence where the duration scaling is capped.\nAttunement Milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:\nDuration Scaling Information.\nDuration values are listed in seconds. Base duration of this spell only depends on Intelligence. Base duration shown as well as values with the &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest&lt;/a&gt; variants applied and pieces of &lt;a href=\"Northwarder%20Set\"&gt;Northwarder Set&lt;/a&gt; applied. "}
{"id": "177343", "revid": "53502897", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=177343", "title": "Fall damage", "text": "Fall damage is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is the damage inflicted to characters and enemies after falling a certain distance onto a surface.\n\"Dark Souls\".\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", fall damage removes a percentage of the character's maximum &lt;a href=\"Health\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; depending on the units of height fallen and the character's current &lt;a href=\"Equip%20Load\"&gt;equip load&lt;/a&gt;.\nNon-lethal fall damage can be negated by using the &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fall%20Control\"&gt;Fall Control&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Dark Souls II\".\nIn &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;, fall damage deals damage through a function of the distance fallen and the current equip load percentage.\nDamage from a fall is determined by these formulas:\nWhere the Effective Height is a function of the physical height and the player's equip load percentage:\nIf Equip load % is 100% or lower:\nIf Equip load % is over 100%, to a maximum of 120%:\nAny height equal or greater than 19.5m is a guaranteed lethal fall. Otherwise, the maximum damage taken is 1945HP.\nThe pit in Majula is about 15.4m, meaning the damage on 0% equip load is about 1357 HP.\nFall Reduction effects/equipment can lower the effective height by these amounts (but do not prevent guaranteed deaths due to height):\n&lt;a href=\"https%3A//docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1xElPzW8_86nAVZsY_I9a6INGW8NiY-XaLWlzZ_1HhTk/edit%3Fusp%3Dsharing\"&gt;Datasheet that allows calculations of Dark Souls II Fall Damage&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "137600", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=137600", "title": "Fallen Knight", "text": "The Fallen Knight is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nAn enemy clad in the &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Knight%20Set\"&gt;Fallen Knight Set&lt;/a&gt;. Can be dangerous if he is not dealt with before facing the &lt;a href=\"Brigand\"&gt;Brigand&lt;/a&gt; a bit further.\nUses a variety of combat mechanics, including switching between holding a &lt;a href=\"Bandit%27s%20Knife%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; in his left hand or wielding his &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword\"&gt;long sword&lt;/a&gt; with both, throwing &lt;a href=\"kukri\"&gt;kukri&lt;/a&gt;s at the player, and frequently using the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Stance%20%28Straight%20Sword%29\"&gt;Stance&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\nFound near the beginning of the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;, at the end of a partially concealed slope to the left of the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep%23Bonfires\"&gt;first&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; and guarding the &lt;a href=\"Paladin%27s%20Ashes\"&gt;Paladin's Ashes&lt;/a&gt;. Will attack from behind if the player continues onward, most likely while fighting the &lt;a href=\"Brigand\"&gt;Brigand&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nThe Fallen Knight can be very dangerous against unprepared players. His fighting methods are somewhat similar to &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Knight%20Hodrick\"&gt;Hodrick&lt;/a&gt;'s. He dwells hidden at the end of a slope located to the left of the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep%23Bonfires\"&gt;first&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; upon arriving to the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;, and is intended to surprise the player from the rearguard while they are engaging the &lt;a href=\"Brigand\"&gt;Brigand&lt;/a&gt;. Even alone, this enemy can be a major threat due to his advanced combat mechanics and high resilience.\nWhen he switches to his &lt;a href=\"Bandit%27s%20Knife%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt;, raise a &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; with good &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;; upon hitting it, he will stagger and become open for a counterattack.\nHe frequently performs his sword's &lt;a href=\"Stance%20%28Straight%20Sword%29\"&gt;Stance&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in an attempt to &lt;a href=\"Guard%20Break\"&gt;break the player's guard&lt;/a&gt;. If successful, he will mercilessly follow with a &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;riposte&lt;/a&gt;, which in many cases will mean the end of the battle. On the other hand, this attack is the key to defeat him easily. When he approaches with his sword wielded with both hands and pointing forward, lure him into attacking and retreat, making him miss and leaving him open for attack.\nHe often throws &lt;a href=\"Kukri\"&gt;Kukri&lt;/a&gt;s at the player, although he's prone to fall for these kinds of attacks too, so hurl back some throwable knives at him whenever the occasion opens."}
{"id": "131314", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131314", "title": "Fallen Knight Armor", "text": "The Fallen Knight Armor is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Knight%20Set\"&gt;Fallen Knight Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nFound along with the rest of the set in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;. In the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices%23Bonfires\"&gt;Crucifixion Woods&lt;/a&gt; swamp area, it is found on a corpse before the ladder to &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, where the two &lt;a href=\"Exile%20Watchdog\"&gt;Exile Watchdog&lt;/a&gt;s stand guard."}
