{"id": "135189", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135189", "title": "Fallen Knight Set", "text": "The Fallen Knight Set is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;medium armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;. In the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices%23Bonfires\"&gt;Crucifixion Woods&lt;/a&gt; swamp area, it is found on a corpse before the ladder to &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, where the two &lt;a href=\"Exile%20Watchdog\"&gt;Exile Watchdog&lt;/a&gt;s stand guard.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Fallen Knight Set is an armor set that possesses an unorthodox array of defenses.\nUnlike other plate armor sets of its weight class, it boasts a surprising resistance against &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage, and has very respectable tolerance to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. Like most other plate armor sets, it is somewhat weak to &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nHowever, the compromised cloth parts of the armor render it vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; damage, something that the vast majority of plate armor sets are quite strong against, and has a particular vulnerability to &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage as well. It also has rather poor resistance to status effects, as it is comparatively easy to inflict &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; than with other plate armor sets. And finally, it provides lower than standard &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; for its weight, making it a poor choice for players who which to wield weapons with &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; frames."}
{"id": "131327", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131327", "title": "Fallen Knight Trousers", "text": "The Fallen Knight Trousers are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". They are part of the &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Knight%20Set\"&gt;Fallen Knight Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nFound along with the rest of the set in the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt;. In the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices%23Bonfires\"&gt;Crucifixion Woods&lt;/a&gt; swamp area, it is found on a corpse before the ladder to &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, where the two &lt;a href=\"Exile%20Watchdog\"&gt;Exile Watchdog&lt;/a&gt;s stand guard."}
{"id": "140169", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140169", "title": "Falling Bolt", "text": ""}
{"id": "159381", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=159381", "title": "Falling Bolt (Dragonslayer Greataxe)", "text": "Falling Bolt is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThe wielder holds the axe high above their head and charges it with &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;. After a short delay, they slam it to the ground, inflicting heavy damage to any enemy in front and knocking them down. The attack inflicts the weapon's full Attack Rating as damage upon impact, as well as a large area thundershock for 1.7 times the weapon's Lightning component.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nThis skill is one of the most destructive single attacks in the game, allowing the wielder to bring immense power crashing down on any target in front of them. It has a relatively long windup, but is difficult to interrupt and deals damage in an area, which can fell groups of enemies should they congregate in front of the player. The windup means that it is best used against unaware or stationary targets, such as when sneaking up on an enemy or punishing a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;boss's&lt;/a&gt; recovery frames after dodging their attack. While it drains immense stamina and &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt;, the knockdown allows it to be used on the same target repeatedly, which will almost assuredly guarantee killing anything the wielder sets their sights on. \nOnline gameplay.\nThe long windup of this skill makes it easy to roll through and punish with a backstab, so attempting to use it on a wary opponent is not recommended. Catching another player from around a blind corner, or when they're distracted by an ally, can quickly turn the tables in an invasion due to the immense damage wrought by the axe."}
{"id": "159382", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=159382", "title": "Falling Bolt (Dragonslayer Swordspear)", "text": "Falling Bolt is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThe player charges the spear with &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;. After roughly 2 seconds, they will thrust the spear skyward, calling down a bolt of lightning on the targeted foe; this bolt deals 200% of the weapon's Attack Rating as Lightning damage. The spear will then be buffed with 80 Lightning damage for 35 seconds.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nDue to the long windup of this skill, it is best used to begin a fight with the skill rather than trying to cast it in the midst of battle. Against an unaware enemy, they will take tremendous damage from the bolt, weakening them to be more easily cleaned up by the spear's attacks, moreso with the inclusion of the buff. After striking a foe with the bolt, the buff can be used to more easily defeat subsequent enemies when fighting a group.\nOnline gameplay.\nUnless the enemy player is distracted or otherwise unaware, hitting them with the bolt can be extremely unreliable. However, it is still a good way to begin an engagement as the buff will augment the spear's attack power and make it more effective in combat.\nThe upward thrust can be &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parried&lt;/a&gt;, oddly enough, though should an enemy be close enough to do so they will usually simply attack instead, as the skill does not provide a great amount of &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt;."}
