{"id": "88763", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=88763", "title": "Faraam, God of War", "text": "Faraam (\u30d5\u30a1\u30fc\u30ca\u30e0) is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nFaraam is the god of war and main deity who was worshipped in the kingdom of &lt;a href=\"Forossa\"&gt;Forossa&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs the country was in a situation of constant conflict with other lands at its borders, \"war\" influenced their culture and their religion which in turn reinforced its warrior mentality, making their deity a central figure for their army and society. The priests of Faraam and Forossan sages were those who led the knights of the land into battle. They were wise men who obtained their title and role only after completing a rigorous journey of hardship to the north and were thus called \"Northwarders\" and worshiped as the agents of Faraam. The most important order among the Forossan knights, the Lion Knights, wore &lt;a href=\"Faraam%20Set\"&gt;heavy armor&lt;/a&gt; named after their god of war which made them recognizable and famous, depicting a knight fighting an ancient archdragon on the helmet and that were blessed directly by Faraam, making them quite resistant against fire. "}
{"id": "31336", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31336", "title": "Faraam Armor", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Faraam Armor\u00a0is a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Faraam%20Set\"&gt;Faraam Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nLooted from a corpse near King's Gate &lt;a href=\"bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Drangleic%20Castle\"&gt;Drangleic Castle&lt;/a&gt;. From the King's Gate bonfire, enter the room on the right. Defeat all the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Soldier\"&gt;soldiers&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ruin%20Sentinels\"&gt;sentinels&lt;/a&gt; on the left side of the room in order to open the far left door. In this room is a collapsible floor, which will break and drop you on a corpse containing the Faraam set. Be careful of the sentinel, which will drop down after you. There are two adjacent caves, one containing a bonfire and the other &lt;a href=\"Darkdiver%20Grandahl\"&gt;Darkdiver Grandahl&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nRequires &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt; per upgrade.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
