{"id": "47662", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47662", "title": "Felkin the Outcast", "text": "Felkin the Outcast, also known as\u00a0Felkin the Hexer,\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Merchants%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;merchant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". He is voiced by , who previously voiced &lt;a href=\"Laurentius%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Laurentius of the Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Crestfallen%20Merchant\"&gt;Crestfallen Merchant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nFelkin the Outcast is a sorcerer who has devoted himself to the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; and the powers of &lt;a href=\"Hexes\"&gt;Hexes&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found before the first &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Huntsman%27s%20Copse\"&gt;Huntsman's Copse&lt;/a&gt;, and will train in, and sell to the player, Hexes if they have an &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; level of 8 or above. If the player does not have the required stats, he will dismiss them and request to be left alone. If the player speaks to him with Intelligence and Faith levels at 20, he will give you the &lt;a href=\"Hexer%27s%20Set\"&gt;Hexer's Set&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Sunset%20Staff\"&gt;Sunset Staff&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0He will still speak to the player if the player re-specs with a &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Vessel\"&gt;Soul Vessel&lt;/a&gt;.\nFelkin has a prominent stammer. He has little patience for those who don't have the talent for Hexes, and will dismiss any who do not display such. However, should someone even hint at skill in hex magic, he will give them everything they need to embrace &lt;a href=\"the%20Dark\"&gt;the Dark&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrangely enough, if\u00a0Felkin is attacked, rather than casting hexes at the player, he will actually cast &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; with his Sunset Staff.\nFelkin also uses the &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Rapier\"&gt;Chaos Rapier&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Shield\"&gt;Chaos Shield&lt;/a&gt;, should he choose to fight the player in melee combat.\nLore.\nFelkin, at one point, was an aspiring sorcerer. He traveled to the most renowned &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; schools across the land to learn &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Sorceries&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Miracles&lt;/a&gt;, and Pyromancies, but none of them interested him. He was on the verge of giving up his life of sorcery, when the Dark called to him, and he took up Hex magic. Ever since then, he has been deeply enthralled in the Dark and its teachings, and travels the land sharing his knowledge with anyone who could practice it."}
{"id": "139724", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=139724", "title": "Female Undead Merchant", "text": ""}
{"id": "126092", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=126092", "title": "Fencer Sharron", "text": "Fencer Sharron is a &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;dark spirit&lt;/a&gt; exclusive for \"\".\nDescription.\nFencer Sharron is a melee-based &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;dark spirit&lt;/a&gt;, capable of &lt;a href=\"Power%20Stance\"&gt;power-stancing&lt;/a&gt; her &lt;a href=\"Puzzling%20Stone%20Sword\"&gt;Puzzling Stone Sword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Fang\"&gt;Spider Fang&lt;/a&gt;. Due to the nature of the Puzzling Stone Sword, she can attack from a longer distance than initially apparent. Most of her combos are very quick and designed to stun-lock the player, often killing them if she manages to connect a couple of successful attacks. If the player opts to raise a shield, she'll be prone to perform a &lt;a href=\"Guard%20Break\"&gt;guard break&lt;/a&gt; and follow with a barrage of slashes in return.\nStrategy.\nIn the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Iron%20Keep\"&gt;Iron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, due to the area's layout, a good strategy is to lure her into running around one of the staircases and attack her every time she is about to reach a corner. If she manages to injure the player, they can just drop down and heal while waiting for her.\nAt the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Aerie\"&gt;Dragon Aerie&lt;/a&gt;, one can easily defeat her by luring her back to where the first dragon is fought. Once there, one must simply kite her until she falls into one of the holes in the floor.\nA good strategy is to bring a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt;, hold it with both hands and perform a strong attack to smash her into the ground. Trying to land another hit while she is recovering can be risky, as she may roll away, allowing her to retaliate with a quick barrage of attacks. To ensure a hit, the player may wait for her around a corner and attack her as she closes in, then find another corner where to hide in and repeat the process until she is defeated."}
{"id": "139368", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=139368", "title": "Festering Starved Hound", "text": ""}
{"id": "150132", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150132", "title": "Filianore", "text": "Filianore (\u30d5\u30a3\u30ea\u30a2\u30ce\u30fc\u30eb) is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nFilianore is located in &lt;a href=\"Filianore%27s%20Rest\"&gt;Filianore's Rest&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28location%29\"&gt;the Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlot.\nFilianore is guarded by the members of the &lt;a href=\"Spears%20of%20the%20Church\"&gt;Spears of the Church&lt;/a&gt; covenant. They prevent trespassers from disturbing her slumber. Once the player defeats the Spears of the Church, they can enter the Filianore's chamber and touch the broken shell she is embracing. Doing so will awaken Filianore and transport the Ashen One to an endless, empty desert resembling that particular scene in the opening cinematic of the game, containing ruins of the Ringed City. While the exact nature of this location is unknown, Filianore's decayed corpse is found on the bed within her tower in the desert.\nDescription.\nFilianore is a large woman with long, dark hair. She wears long, white robes and a silver circlet. She rests eternally on a bed, embracing a cracked shell which resembles an egg.\nAfter the \"egg\" shatters, Filianore's body suddenly becomes worn and dry, with hollowed eyes and consumed appearance. \nLore.\nFilianore is the last daughter of &lt;a href=\"Gwyn%2C%20Lord%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Gwyn, Lord of Sunlight&lt;/a&gt;. Her sacred symbol is a crest of young grass.\nUnlike the other deities who resided in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Age of Fire&lt;/a&gt;, she did not live there. After having won the war against the dragons, her father Gwyn \"gave\" her as a gift to the &lt;a href=\"Pygmy%20King\"&gt;Pygmy Lords&lt;/a&gt; together with a &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28Location%29\"&gt;magnificent ringed city&lt;/a&gt; at the edge of the world. Before leaving her in the Ringed City, Gwyn promised her that he would come back for her some day.\nThroughout the millennia that followed in the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Age of Fire&lt;/a&gt;, the Pygmies continued to worship Filianore as a goddess, building a &lt;a href=\"Church%20of%20Filianore\"&gt;church in her name&lt;/a&gt; with her as the matriarch. Even the &lt;a href=\"Pygmy%20King\"&gt;Pygmy Lords&lt;/a&gt; who possessed the Dark Soul and ruled the city relied on her for salvation.\nAt a certain point Filianore would have fallen into a deep sleep hugging a &lt;a href=\"Vagrant\"&gt;Vagrant&lt;/a&gt; egg, causing the appearance of a space-time barrier that isolated the Ringed City from the effects of the fading of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; on the rest of the world. The order of the &lt;a href=\"Spears%20of%20the%20Church\"&gt;Spears of the Church&lt;/a&gt; would thus be founded, which would employ knights with the aim of protecting the princess's slumber when her church was compromised by a trespasser and maintaining the city's state of isolation and containing the Dark Soul within it, receiving &lt;a href=\"Filianore%27s%20Spear%20Ornament\"&gt;Filianore's Spear Ornament&lt;/a&gt;s as proof of the fulfillment of their duties."}
