{"id": "62872", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=62872", "title": "Fiorenza", "text": "Fiorenza is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nFiorenza was the wealthiest merchant in all of &lt;a href=\"Volgen\"&gt;Volgen&lt;/a&gt;'s history, a man known for using his riches to buy artifacts of luxury and rare collector's items. Although it was an object whose existence was only confirmed by ancient books, the rich merchant managed to replicate the &lt;a href=\"Avelyn%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Avelyn&lt;/a&gt;, a crossbow and a priceless work of art at the same time, a weapon resembing a musical instrument. He also sought the &lt;a href=\"Engraved%20Gauntlets\"&gt;Engraved Gauntlets&lt;/a&gt;, a rare and precious piece of armor said to bring good fortune to their wearer, for his entire life, but failed to obtain them, as a rich man from &lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Cove%20Tseldora\"&gt;Tseldora&lt;/a&gt; preceded him. Despite contributing to the development of his city's technical capabilities to satisfy his hobby, Fiorenza ended up consumed by it. He was ruined by his expense accounts and exhausted his wealth after years of excessive debauchery"}
