{"id": "129921", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=129921", "title": "Fire Keeper (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Fire Keeper is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe is voiced by .\nLocation.\nThe Fire Keeper can always be found tending the &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; or sitting on the stairs in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThe Fire Keeper tends to Firelink Shrine and serves the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;Ashen One&lt;/a&gt; throughout their long and arduous journey. She is a blind maiden of unknown origin; she was, at the time, the current &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper\"&gt;Fire Keeper&lt;/a&gt; that tended to the flame when the Ashen One arrived at the Firelink Shrine to fulfill their duty. She dons a white crown that covers her eyes, and a black robe, as well as black gloves. Like all fire keepers, she can transform souls into raw power.\nShe allows the player to upgrade their &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stats&lt;/a&gt; individually in exchange for a determined amount of &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; per level.\nShe can also cure &lt;a href=\"dark%20sigil\"&gt;dark sigil&lt;/a&gt;s the player has accumulated either by leveling up with &lt;a href=\"Yoel%20of%20Londor\"&gt;Yoel&lt;/a&gt; or by taking part on the ritual in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally, she will also heal their &lt;a href=\"Hollowing%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;hollowing&lt;/a&gt; level, thus restoring their physical appearance, when provided with a &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper%20Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire Keeper Soul&lt;/a&gt;. The cost for healing each dark sigil is directly related to the player's soul level.\nIf given the &lt;a href=\"Eyes%20of%20a%20Fire%20Keeper\"&gt;eyes of the first Fire Keeper&lt;/a&gt;, she sees a world without fire, and is frightened by the mere thought of it. Even so, she is willing to end the cycle permanently if the Ashen One requests it. If the Ashen One chooses to realize her dream, she will be summoned to the &lt;a href=\"Kiln%20of%20the%20First%20Flame%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Kiln of the First Flame&lt;/a&gt;. At that time, she will hold the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; in her hands and let it die out, thus unlocking the &lt;a href=\"Endings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29%23End%20of%20Fire\"&gt;End of Fire&lt;/a&gt; ending. If the Ashen One chooses to succumb to their desire, and kill her during the ritual; the power of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; would fall to their hands.\nThe Fire Keeper can also be talked to, and her dialogue changes throughout the course of the game.\nShe will psychically respond to most &lt;a href=\"Gestures%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;gestures&lt;/a&gt; performed by the player.\nIf killed, she will always respawn at Firelink Shrine, stating that as a Fire Keeper, she cannot die."}
{"id": "135977", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135977", "title": "Fire Keeper Gloves", "text": "Fire Keeper Gloves are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper%20Set\"&gt;Fire Keeper Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nCan be found on a corpse by dropping off the left side of the bridge before the elevator in the tower containing the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper%20Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire Keeper Soul&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;. The tower may be accessed by purchasing the &lt;a href=\"Tower%20Key%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Tower Key&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt;."}
