{"id": "3762", "revid": "357106", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3762", "title": "Fire Surge", "text": "Fire Surge is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;, down the well near &lt;a href=\"Phalanx\"&gt;Phalanx&lt;/a&gt; there will be a series of narrow passages guarded by &lt;a href=\"Bonewheel%20Skeleton\"&gt;Bonewheel Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s. Follow the available passage (don't bother with the illusory walls for the sake of straightness) and up a flight of stairs, there is a non-aggressive &lt;a href=\"Engorged%20Zombie\"&gt;Engorged Zombie&lt;/a&gt;, killing it will yield this pyromancy. Coming from the sewer entrance, you'll have to reveal the 1st illusory wall, and then continue down the previous path.\nGeneral Information.\nFire surge is essentially a flamethrower; holding down the casting button will cause a the player to emit a continuous stream of fire. Fire Surge has next to no starting or ending lag. Players can walk while casting this pyromancy. Each hit has a fire attack power of 0.55 times the Pyromancy Flame's magic adjust.\nOverview.\nIt is easy to run out of casts with this pyromancy without moderation; however, 80 casts is usually enough to last at least one or two engagements. It is not very popular in PvE as it does not stagger and its fairly low damage allows monsters to retaliate. In PvP, Fire Surge is occasionally popular for punishing slower opponents or finishing off players with low HP."}
{"id": "133538", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133538", "title": "Fire Surge (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Fire Surge is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Cornyx%20of%20the%20Great%20Swamp\"&gt;Cornyx of the Great Swamp&lt;/a&gt; for 1,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nEmits a constant stream of fire, with each tick inflicting 0.67 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst as\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nUses.\nSingle player.\nDue to Fire Surge having to be channeled to sustain damage on a target, it will rapidly drain &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; from the player's pool. As the FP drains much faster than the pyromancy actually hits, it is advisable to use this pyromancy in short bursts, or to catch an opponent off-guard, then follow up with a more robust pyromancy, such as &lt;a href=\"Great%20Combustion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Great Combustion&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Bed%20Vestiges\"&gt;Chaos Bed Vestiges&lt;/a&gt;. It can also be used at close range to finish off opponents at low health.\nIt is able to stagger enemies, but is not recommended for use against heavily armed, or larger enemies. Additionally, it will always stun enemies that have unique fire damage stagger animations, such as &lt;a href=\"Corpse%20Grub\"&gt;Corpse Grub&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Starved%20Hound\"&gt;Starved Hound&lt;/a&gt;s and the &lt;a href=\"Pus%20of%20Man\"&gt;Pus of Man&lt;/a&gt;, for the full duration. This makes it an effective tool for taking down these enemies when paired with more powerful means of attack.\nOnline gameplay.\nBecause of its quick casting time and the ability to immediately cancel out of it with a roll, this spell can be useful for inflicting small but quick chip damage. In particular, it is ideal for destroying &lt;a href=\"Tears%20of%20Denial\"&gt;Tears of Denial&lt;/a&gt; users immediately upon proccing it, especially after a successful critical attack, as it is virtually impossible to avoid taking damage from this spell even by immediately rolling.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "3751", "revid": "357107", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3751", "title": "Fire Tempest", "text": "Fire Tempest is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral Information.\nFire Tempest has twenty \"uses\" per slot. A full cast of Fire Tempest will expend 17 of these \"uses\"; attempting to cast Fire Tempest again will result in a much weaker spell. Using Fire Tempest causes many (17 in a full cast) pillars of fire to erupt from the ground in a large area around the player. The spell has a fire attack power of 3.9 times the Pyromancy Flame's magic adjust and most enemies that get hit by it will be knocked back, possibly into another flame pillar.\nFire Tempest has a very long windup time that can be shortened through improving the Dexterity stat. Fire Tempest and its cousins also have a distinctive sound accompanying its casting, which makes it difficult to surprise human enemies with. It may be canceled or interrupted if the caster is hit, in which case not all 17 casts will be used. "}
{"id": "56953", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56953", "title": "Fire Tempest (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Fire Tempest is a &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nLike its variant from \"Dark Souls\", Fire Tempest is a nearly identical, but stronger version of &lt;a href=\"Firestorm%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Firestorm&lt;/a&gt;;\u00a0casting it causes pillars of flame to erupt in a random pattern around the player. Unlike its \"Dark Souls\" counterpart, however, it suffers from the disadvantage of having fewer casts than Firestorm.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
